title: tomato sauce dip
directions: Dice tomatoes, onion and peppers.
Mix all ingredients.
Serve with chips.
(Can leave peppers out or not use so many.)

title: no bake - no sugar cheese custard
directions: Blend egg and gelatin in bottom of blender.
Wait 1 minute, then add boiling water.
Cover and blend until all gelatin is dissolved; add cottage cheese.
Cover and blend until mixture is smooth; add milkshake mix, sweetener and skim milk.
Cover and blend.
Pour into 6 custard cups.
Sprinkle with nutmeg. Refrigerate until set.

title: hello dollies
directions: Place in layers in a 9 x 9-inch or 9 x 12-inch baking dish. Melt oleo in dish first.
Then layer starting with graham cracker crumbs.
Pour condensed milk over all.
Do not stir.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: potato casserole
directions: Boil cubed potatoes until tender; drain.
Add mushroom soup, butter, milk and onion.
In casserole dish, pour half of mixture. Top with cheese.
Pour remaining mixture over cheese.
Add another layer of cheese.
Bake at 425° until cheese melts.

title: dilled fish salad
directions: Place 1 to 1 1/2 inches water in 10-inch skillet.
Add onion, lemon, parsley, bay leaf, salt and peppercorns.
Heat to boiling; reduce heat.
Arrange frozen fillets in single layer in skillet. Cover and simmer until fillets flake easily with fork, 4 to 6 minutes.
Remove fillets; break into large pieces.
Refrigerate until chilled, 30 to 60 minutes.
Prepare Cucumber-Dill Sauce. Toss with fillet pieces.
Refrigerate at least 1 hour before serving.

title: blueberry sour cream coffeecake
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Grease an 8 or 9-inch round cake or pie pan.
Rinse blueberries with cold water and drain.
Combine muffin mix, sour cream, milk and egg in medium bowl.
Stir until ingredients are moistened.
Spread half of batter into pan. Combine blueberries and preserves in small bowl.
Spread half of blueberry mixture on top of batter.
Spread remaining batter over blueberry layer.
Spread remaining fruit on top, avoiding edges. Bake for 30 to 35 minutes for 8-inch pan, 25 to 30 minutes for 9-inch pan or until golden brown.

title: mustardy fried chicken
directions: Wash chicken breasts; sprinkle with salt and pepper.
Mix eggs and mustard together in small bowl.
In separate bowl, combine cheese and flour; mix well.
Dip chicken in egg mixture, then roll in cheese mixture until evenly coated.
Lay chicken on waxed paper or foil for 10 minutes to allow coating to set.
Saute chicken on both sides in hot oil for 15 to 20 minutes or until tender.

title: 5 hour stew
directions: Put in covered roasting pan or cast-iron Dutch oven.
Bake at 250° for 5 hours.
(Don't peek!)

title: scones
directions: Stir together flour, sugar, baking powder and salt.
Cut in butter until crumbly.
Mix in eggs and milk.
Knead dough gently on a lightly floured surface.
Roll or pat dough into 1/2 inch thick rounds.
Bake at 400° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: mexican chicken
directions: Debone chicken;
saute
onions
in small amount of oleo. Do not brown.
Add soups and 1 can chicken broth.
Mix well and add chicken and
green
chilies.
Cook
minutes on low heat. Grease glass loaf
pan
with
oleo; line bottom with tortillas. Pour alternate
layers
of sauce, cheese and tortillas.
Finish with cheese on top.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: crabmeat pie
directions: Combine first 4 ingredients.
Add remaining ingredients.
Pour into pastry lined 9-inch pie plate.
Bake at 350° for about 40 minutes or until pie crust and crabmeat are golden brown.

title: gingerbread cake
directions: Mix brown sugar, oleo and flour thoroughly. Save 1 cup for topping. To remaining mixture, add all other ingredients. Mix until damp. Pour into 13 x 9 x 2-inch greased pan and sprinkle dry mixture on top. Bake at 350° to 375° for 45 minutes. Cool slightly and serve. Serves 12.

title: chicken benzoni
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Coat bottom of casserole with olive oil and 2 to 3 tablespoons of margarine.
Place in oven until margarine melts.
Bread cutlets with crumbs and arrange in casserole.
Slice mushrooms and dice onion and spread over cutlets.
Pour chicken broth over cutlets.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes (depending on thickness of cutlets).
Lay slices of cheese over entire casserole and bake 10 minutes until cheese melts.
Easy one-dish casserole that also freezes well.

title: swiss potato gratin
directions: Wash potatoes well and trim away any discolored spots or eyes. Slice thin and drop into a pot of cold, heavily salted water. Set over high heat and bring to a boil.
Boil potatoes for 1 minute.
Drain and rinse with cold water.
Drain again and pat dry.

title: parmesan bread
directions: Dissolve yeast in warm water in a large mixing bowl; let stand 5 minutes.
Stir in 2 cups flour and next 7 ingredients.
Beat at medium speed with an electric mixer for 2 minutes.
Gradually stir in 1/3 cup Parmesan cheese and remaining 1 cup of flour.
Cover and let rise in warm place for 1 hour or until double.
Punch dough down and spoon into greased 2-quart casserole (you don't have to knead).
Brush with remaining butter and sprinkle with remaining cheese.
Cover and let rise until double.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until golden brown.
Cool in casserole for 10 minutes.
Remove and cool.

title: crab stuffed mushroom caps
directions: Melt butter in heavy skillet until hot.
Add mushrooms and saute for about 5 minutes.
Combine cream cheese with remaining ingredients and mix well.
Remove mushrooms from skillet.
Drain on paper towels.
Fill with crab meat mixture and place on lightly greased baking dish.

title: make your own shake 'n bake mix
directions: Mix together. Store in tightly covered container in refrigerator.
Equals 20 store bought packages.

title: meat loaf
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Stir ground beef together in a large bowl with 2 well beaten eggs.
Add milk, chopped onion and pepper. Add 1/2 cup ketchup to mixture.
Continue to mix.
Gradually add crushed crackers and garlic powder to the mixture.
Mold with your hands to desired size.
Place in molded loaf pan or in a cake pan. Set aside.
Salt and pepper now (if desired).

title: million dollar cookies
directions: Blend all ingredients well.
Butter bottom of a figured or glass with a design; dip in sugar.
Make dough into small balls and press on ungreased cookie sheet with glass.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: chicken and rice
directions: Wash rice, sprinkle in roaster, already greased.
Place chicken or chicken breasts on rice and add salt.
Mix dry soup and liquid soup and water in separate pan and heat until well mixed.
Pour chicken over chicken and rice.
Bake 1 1/2 hours at 350°.

title: banana bread
directions: Cream shortening and sugar.
Beat eggs and mix into shortening and sugar.
Mix dry ingredients and add to first mixture along with bananas.
Put in greased loaf pans.
Bake at 350° in a 5 1/2 x 3 x 2-inch pans for 40 minutes or in 7 1/2 x 3 1/2 x 2-inch pans for 1 hour.

title: banana bread
directions: Mix bananas and buttermilk; set aside.
Cream butter and sugar.
Add eggs, one at a time.
Beat well.
Add dry ingredients and milk and banana mixture alternately to the creamed mixture. Pour into greased and floured 9 x 5 x 3-inch loaf pan.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour.

title: quick banana nut bread
directions: Cream sugar and oil; add beaten egg to mixture.
Add biscuit mix, bananas and nuts.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: peanut butter pie
directions: Combine all ingredients and pour into crust.
Refrigerate until completely chilled.

title: 24 hour potatoes
directions: Boil potatoes with skins on just until fork-tender.
Peel and put through ricer, or grate on the larger hole side of a grater. Put into casserole which has been sprayed with Pam.

title: secret almond kiss
directions: Unwrap Kisses. Heat oven to 375°.

Beat butter, sugar and vanilla until fluffy. Add flour, almonds and almond extract. Chill. Use about 1 tablespoon to wrap around the kiss. Cover completely. Place on an ungreased cookie sheet. Bake 10 to 12 minutes until set but not browned. Cool slightly. While warm, roll in xx sugar. Cool completely, then roll again in xx sugar.
Store in an airtight container. Yields 36 cookies.

title: ro-tel chicken
directions: Saute onion and green peppers in butter until tender.
Use broth to cook spaghetti; drain and save some broth to moisten casserole.
Mix all ingredients together and put into two 9 x 13 x 2-inch casserole dishes.
Bake, covered, 1 hour at 375°.
These may be frozen before baking.

title: chocolate cake
directions: Mix flour, sugar, cocoa, baking soda and salt.
Add remaining ingredients.
Bake in ungreased pan for 45 to 50 minutes at 350°.

title: rice salad
directions: Prepare whipping cream with sugar and vanilla.
Note; may substitute nonfat vanilla yogurt for vanilla and cream, and use substitute sweetener for sugar.
Fold in rice, cherries and pineapple.
Chill.

title: too-good to be no-fat chocolate cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Assemble a 10-inch spring-form pan. Spray bottom and sides with cooking spray.
Dust with cocoa.
In a medium bowl, sift together cocoa, flour, baking powder and baking soda.
Set aside.
In a large bowl, with an electric mixer, beat egg whites, brown sugar, yogurt and vanilla until well blended, about 1 to 2 minutes on medium speed.
Mix in dry ingredients by hand until just moistened.
(Batter will not be smooth.)
Pour batter into prepared pan and bake about 35 minutes or until toothpick inserted in center comes out clean.
Cool in the pan on a wire rack for 15 minutes.
Then use a knife to loosen sides of cake from the pan.
Remove ring and cool completely on a rack.
Serve cake on the metal bottom of the pan.

title: 3 layer refrigerator dessert
directions: Mix flour, butter and pecans.
Press into 10 x 13-inch pan and bake in 350° oven for 20 minutes; cool.
Mix cream cheese, sugar and Cool Whip.
Spread on cooled crust.
Mix puddings and milk for 2 minutes, then spread on 2nd layer.
Cover with Cool Whip, chopped pecans and shaved chocolate squares or Hershey bar.
Chill overnight or several hours.

title: old fashion bread pudding
directions: Mix together and bake at 350° for about 30 minutes.
Before baking, sprinkle a little butter around the edges and sugar on top then bake.

title: coleslaw
directions: Chop cabbage in blender with water and drain.
Chop carrots, pepper and celery with water and drain.
Drain ingredients for about 1 to 2 hours.
Whisk mayonnaise, sugar and pickle juice; add to chopped ingredients.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Mixture should be creamy.
If not, add more mayonnaise.

title: whoopie pie cake
directions: Combine first 5 ingredients and mix according to cake mix package directions.
Divide batter in half and place into 2 wax paper lined cookie sheets.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.
Cool. Beat 2 egg whites until stiff; set aside.

title: cream cheese squares
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients together and press into a 13 x 9-inch cake pan. Next mix the last three ingredients together and put on top of first ingredients.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until brown.

title: fay's zucchini walnut bread
directions: Beat eggs.
Gradually beat in sugar and oil.
Combine dry ingredients.
Add to the egg mixture alternately with zucchini. Stir in walnuts.
Pour into a greased and floured bread pan.
Bake at 350° for 50 minutes. Let stand for 10 minutes before taking out of the pan.

title: ho ho bars
directions: First Layer:
Make cake mix according to directions on box. Pour into large cookie sheet (16 x 11-inches).
Bake 15 to 18 minutes.

title: banana-rum coolers
directions: Place banana slices on a baking sheet.
Cover and freeze until firm.
Combine banana and 1/4 cup milk in container of an electric blender; top with cover and process until smooth.
Add remaining 3/4 cup milk, ice cubes and remaining ingredients; process until smooth.
Pour into chilled glasses.
Serve immediately.

title: iced tea
directions: Empty contents of tea bags into a 1-quart preserving jar.
Add water and stir briskly.
Screw jar lid down tight so jar will not leak when turned upside-down.
Set jar in sunny window and leave until liquid is as dark as strong coffee.
How long this will take varies on the intensity of the sun, but allow anywhere from 4 to 8 hours.
Also, turn jar several times as tea brews or whenever you are passing by.
Strain tea through a small fine sieve into a clean 1-quart jar.
Screw lid down tight and store in refrigerator.

title: orange balls
directions: Mix together and roll into small balls.
Roll in canned coconut.
Can be frozen.

title: layered fudge
directions: Combine first 4 ingredients.
Stir over low heat until melted. Spread 1/2 of mixture on large cookie sheet (jelly roll pan, 17 x 10-inch).
Chill until set.

title: *lazy baklava
directions: Mix all ingredients together until dough slides off the sides of the bowl.
Pat into a 9 x 13-inch pan. Bake at 350° for 40 minutes or until nice and brown.

title: fruit dip
directions: Mix sugar, eggs, orange juice, lemon juice and lime juice in medium saucepan and cook, stirring constantly until it comes to a rolling boil.
Remove from heat and chill well.
Fold in large Cool Whip.
Serve with your favorite fruits.

title: fresh apple cake
directions: Mix dry ingredients together.
Beat eggs and add apples and oil to dry ingredients.
Mix well, then add vanilla and pecans.
Bake in a Bundt pan or loaf pan at 350° for 55 minutes or until toothpick comes out dry.
Do not mix with an electric mixer.

title: refrigerator bran muffins
directions: Spray muffin tin.
Mix together flour, bran, baking powder, cinnamon, nutmeg and salt.
Mix egg white, milk, brown sugar, raisins and oil.
Add to dry ingredients.
Store in refrigerator for 3 days.
Bake at 400° for 15 to 20 minutes.
Makes 12 muffins. 154 calories, 4 g. fat.

title: triple maple pecan cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In large mixing bowl, mix first five ingredients on low speed until smooth.
In medium bowl, combine flour, soda and salt.
With wooden spoon, stir flour mixture into first mixture until well mixed.
Refrigerate for 30 minutes.

title: quiche lorraine
directions: Layer bacon, cheese and onions in bottom of baked pastry shell. Blend eggs, milk, salt, sugar and pepper.
Pour over bacon mixture. Microwave on High-medium (70%) 12 to 14 minutes, rotating dish once or twice, if needed.

title: german country breakfast
directions: In a medium heavy frying pan, melt half of the butter over moderate heat.
When the foam subsides, add the bacon.
Fry, stirring occasionally for 8 to 10 minutes, or until the bacon is crisp and brown and has rendered most of its fat.
Add the onion, sausage and potato slices with the remaining butter and fry, stirring frequently, for 8 to 10 minutes, or until the vegetables are lightly browned and the sausage is heated thoroughly.
Stir in the salt, pepper and cheese.
Pour the eggs over the bacon and vegetable mixture and cook, stirring to incorporate it with the vegetables, until the eggs are lightly scrambled.
Remove the pan from heat.
Turn the mixture out into a warmed serving dish. Sprinkle with the chopped chives and serve immediately.

title: microwave ham brunch strata
directions: In a large mixing bowl, beat eggs.
Add remaining ingredients and stir lightly until mixed.
Pour into 9-inch round or 1 1/2-quart shallow casserole dish.
Refrigerate overnight. Microwave at 70% power (Medium-high) for 20 to 25 minutes until center is set.
Give 1/2 turn halfway through cooking.
Let stand 5 minutes.
Serves 6.

title: lemon meringue pie
directions: Cook until thickened.
Pour into baked pie shell.
Top with meringue made from 2 egg whites.
Brown in quick oven.

title: fruit dip
directions: Mix together and chill. Serve with fresh fruit.

title: rhubarb cake
directions: Combine rhubarb and sugar. Let stand while preparing cake.

title: betty salad
directions: Clean lettuce and spinach; mix together.
Place 1/3 of lettuce/spinach mixture in a large glass salad bowl.
Layer 1/3 of bean sprouts, bacon, eggs and mushrooms.
Put another 1/3 of each ingredient and continue until final 1/3 of each ingredient is added.
Toss just before serving.
Can add dressing before tossing or serve on the side.
Makes 8 to 10 servings.

title: cinnamon diamonds
directions: In a mixing bowl, cream shortening and sugars; beat in milk, egg yolk and vanilla.
In a small bowl, stir together the flour, cream of tartar, baking soda, cinnamon and salt; add to creamed mixture.
Blend well.
Spread in a greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking pan.
Bake at 350° for 12 to 15 minutes, or until done.
Cool in pan.
Sift powdered sugar atop.
Cut into diamond shapes.
Makes 1 1/2 to 2 dozen.

title: squash casserole
directions: Grease casserole dish.
Sprinkle 1/2 stuffing mix on bottom. Combine other ingredients.
Pour into casserole dish.
Top with remaining stuffing mix.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: spaghetti sauce
directions: Brown ground beef in skillet.
Mix all ingredients in crock pot.
Cook for 6 to 8 hours.
Remove onion and bay leaves.
Serve over hot spaghetti.

title: california chicken
directions: Sprinkle onion soup on bottom of 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Put pats of butter over onion soup.
Pour rice on top of onion soup. Pour chicken broth over rice.
Put pats of butter on top of chicken and sprinkle with paprika.
Bake, uncovered, at 325° for 45 minutes.
Cover with aluminum foil; turn off heat but leave in oven for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: trudie's coconut pie
directions: Preheat oven to 425°.
Beat egg yolks slightly.
Add milk; blend.
Combine sugar and flour; add to egg mixture.
Blend in butter and coconut.
Beat egg whites and fold into mixture.
Pour into unbaked pie shell and bake approximately 25 minutes.
Remove from oven and top with meringue.

title: peanut butter and jelly sandwiches
directions: Take peanut butter and jelly and spread on bread.
Put both sides of bread together.
Makes 1 sandwich.
Enjoy your sandwich.

title: pizza hot dish
directions: Brown the ground beef; drain.
Add pepper and onions and saute with the meat.
Add soup and spices.
Simmer for 15 minutes over low heat.
Cook noodles; drain.
Grease a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Pour noodles into bottom of pan.
Pour meat mixture over the noodles, sprinkle cheese on top, then the mushrooms.
Cover with foil and bake at 350° for 35 minutes.
Remove foil and bake another 10 minutes.
Let sit 5 minutes before serving.

title: mustard-baked pork chops
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Make bread into crumbs in a blender or food processor. Melt butter.
Combine crumbs, 1/2 teaspoon salt and 1/4 teaspoon pepper.
Stir in butter.
Coat both sides of pork chops with mustard.
Put in shallow roasting pan.
Distribute crumb mixture over chops and pat lightly so it clings.
Bake until browned, about 30 minutes.

title: orange glazed chicken
directions: Heat oil in a large saucepan on medium-high heat. Add chicken. Cook on both sides until browned.
Move chicken to side of skillet.
Add carrots and celery. Cook and stir until carrots are tender-crisp.

title: individual pizzas
directions: Split open muffins; spread on some sauce with a spoon (or skip the sauce if "red" stuff is not in favor).
Top with whatever looks good or is on hand.
Preschoolers love to make and eat their creation.
Put on cookie sheet and bake in 375° oven until heated through, 5 to 8 minutes.

title: blossoms
directions: Shape into balls.
Roll in granulated sugar.
Bake in a preheated 375° oven for 8 minutes; remove from oven and top each cookie with a Hershey Kiss, pressing firmly.
Place back in oven and bake 2 to 3 minutes longer.
Makes about 60 cookies.

title: potato cheese soup
directions: In large saucepan, add potatoes and onion to 1 cup lightly salted boiling water.
Cover and cook until potatoes are tender. Mash potatoes slightly; do not drain.
Measure mixture and add enough milk to make 5 cups.
Blend melted butter, flour, parsley, salt and pepper.
Stir into potato mixture and cook until thickened and bubbly.
Add cheese and cook until cheese is melted.
Serves 4 to 5.

title: streusel topped apple custard pie
directions: Preheat oven to 425°. Arrange apples in prepared pastry shell. In medium mixing bowl, beat eggs; add sweetened condensed milk, margarine cinnamon and nutmeg. Mix well and pour over apples.
In medium mixing bowl, combine sugar and flour; cut in margarine until crumbly.
Stir in nuts; sprinkle over pie. Place in oven. Bake 10 minutes. Reduce oven temperature to 375° and continue baking 35-40 minutes or until golden brown.

title: dreidels
directions: Place a marshmallow on the end of your toothpick, leaving maybe a half-inch of space.
Take a Hershey's Kiss and place it just below the marshmallow.
You will have a dreidel that is edible.
The toothpick serves as the spinner!

title: low-fat pound cake
directions: Spray 9 x 5 x 3-inch loaf pan with Pam and flour lightly. Beat margarine until fluffy; add sugar and beat well.
Add egg substitute and beat until blended.
Combine flour and next 3 ingredients; add to creamed mixture alternately with yogurt, beginning and ending with flour mixture.
Mix just until blended after each addition.
Stir in flavoring.
Spoon batter into prepared pan.
Bake at 350° for 65 minutes until comes out clean. Cool in pan on rack for 5 to 10 minutes.

title: sweet tomato sauce
directions: Combine all ingredients and cook until thick (almost as thick as catsup).
While hot, seal into cans.
It has to be watched while cooking, as it will stick and scorch.
Cooks well in a large crock-pot.

title: eclairs
directions: Combine the pudding and milk.
Beat at low speed for 2 minutes.
Stir in Cool Whip until blended.
In a 9 x 13-inch dish, alternate layers of graham crackers and filling twice.
Top with crackers, then spread frosting on top.
Refrigerate.

title: guacamole dip
directions: Combine avocado, tomato, and onion.
Season with garlic powder, Worcestershire sauce and Tabasco to suit your taste.
Add enough mayonnaise just to moisten.
Chill and serve.

title: easy raspberry squares
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Lightly butter an 8-inch square pan.
Mix all ingredients, except jam, until crumbly.
Press 2 cups of this mixture into bottom of pan.
Spread jam to within 1/4-inch of edges.
Sprinkle remaining crumb mixture over top and lightly press it into the jam.
Bake 35 to 40 minutes.
Cool completely before cutting.

title: hawaiian pineapple banana bread
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Combine flour, sugar, soda, cinnamon and salt in a large bowl; stir in nuts.
Combine remaining ingredients in separate bowl; mix well.
Pour wet mixture into dry mixture, stirring just until dry ingredients are moistened.
Put in 2 loaf pans.
Bake 1 1/2 hours or until done.
Cool in pans 10 minutes.
Yield:
2 loaves (oh, it's so good).

title: kansas watermelon pickles
directions: Trim green and pink from rind and cube.

title: old fashioned egg pie
directions: Mix egg yolks, milk, sugar, oleo, nutmeg and vanilla real well.
Fold in stiffly beaten egg whites. Sprinkle nutmeg on top. Bake in an uncooked pie crust for 45 minutes at 250° to 300° or until firm.

title: collard greens with neckbones
directions: Boil neckbones in large saucepan.
Remove neckbones from broth.
Add greens to broth.
Cook on low heat until tender.
Add bacon drippings, red pepper and season with salt and pepper. Serves 4 to 6.

title: shrimp jambalaya
directions: Place oil and flour in a skillet; cook until light brown to make a roux.
Saute onion, bell pepper and garlic cloves together. Place tomatoes, hot water, catsup and shrimp in a large pot.
Add roux, saute and 2 teaspoons Tony Chachere seafood seasoning.
Stir constantly while adding ingredients.
Place over medium heat and bring to a boil.
Lower heat and simmer for 1 hour or longer.
Add 1 1/2 cups cooked rice, 1 tablespoon parsley flakes and 1 tablespoon green onion tops, chopped.
Mix well and heat 5 more minutes.

title: italian baked fish
directions: Place fish in large baking dish.
Mix all ingredients and pour over fish.
Bake 45 minutes at 350°.
Do not cover dish while baking.

title: w. va. hot milk cake
directions: Cream eggs and sugar real good.
Add flour, salt, vanilla and almond flavoring.
Heat milk and margarine to boiling point, then add to other ingredients.
Add baking powder last; mix well.
Pour into greased and floured either tube or loaf pan.
Bake for 1 hour at 350°.

title: pecan-crusted chicken cutlets
directions: Mix together 2 tablespoons mustard, the melted butter, 1/2 teaspoon salt and 1/8 teaspoon pepper. Brush mixture all over chicken; coat with ground pecans. Place on waxed paper-lined baking sheet and refrigerate for 15 minutes.

title: deviled crab
directions: Thaw crab meat.
Sort crab to remove any bits of shell; leave crab meat in chunks.
Combine eggs, mayonnaise, Worcestershire sauce, onion and hot pepper sauce.
Stir in crab.
Spoon into 6 or 8 crab shells, coquilles or individual serving dishes.
Combine crumbs and melted butter and sprinkle atop filling.
Bake in 350° oven for 15 to 20 minutes or until bubbly and brown.

title: people puppy chow
directions: Place the peanut butter, oleo and chocolate chips in pan on stove until melted.
Stir in cereal.
Pour mixture into powdered sugar in a large bowl or container and shake to coat.
This mixture makes a very large amount.

title: grape jelly
directions: Bring beet juice, lemon juice and Sure-Jell to a boil.
Add sugar; boil 5 minutes.
Remove and add Kool-Aid.
Pour into jars and seal.

title: ham roll appetizers
directions: Mix cream cheese, sour cream and green onion.
Spread on flour tortillas.
Place thinly sliced ham on and roll up tight.
Place in refrigerator until ready to serve.
Slice and serve.
May be served with salsa.

title: chocolate pound cake
directions: Cream margarine, Crisco and sugar.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each.
Sift dry ingredients including cocoa. Add alternately with milk and vanilla, beginning and ending with dry ingredients.
Grease and flour angel food cake pan.
Pour batter into pan and gently press nuts on top.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour.

title: sugared peanuts
directions: Combine the peanuts, water, and sugar in a medium saucepan. Cook over medium high heat until water evaporates and the peanuts begin to look sugary.
Be careful not to burn the peanuts.
Spread on flat pan and bake at 300 degrees for 25 to 30 minutes, stirring after 15 minutes.
Allow to cool.

title: banana pudding
directions: Mix first 5 ingredients together; beat with electric mixer until smooth and creamy.
Use 13 x 9-inch glass dish. Layer wafers, sliced bananas and pudding mixture; repeat, ending with pudding mixture.
Decorate top with wafers.
Refrigerate.

title: spice bread
directions: Put warm milk and yeast in bowl with fat and sugar.
Beat well.
Sift flour, spices and salt.
Add to yeast mixture.
Beat well.
Add marmalade and eggs.
Beat well.
Put into a warm place to rise.
Punch down and put into bread pan or make into rolls. Let rise again.
Bake at 450° for 15 minutes.

title: chocolate indians
directions: Beat eggs. Add sugar and melted margarine. Mix flour and cocoa. Add to egg mixture. Add nuts, vanilla and cinnamon. Pour into greased 9 x 9 pan. Bake at 325° for 20 to 30 minutes. Sprinkle with powdered sugar. When cool, cut into bars.

title: chocolate nut balls
directions: In heavy 2-quart saucepan, cook undiluted milk and chocolate chips over medium heat, stirring until chocolate is melted and mixture is smooth.
Remove from heat.
Add crushed wafers, sugar, 1/2 cup nuts and orange juice; mix well.
Let stand at room temperature for 30 minutes.
Shape into balls 1-inch in diameter. Roll in remaining nuts.
Refrigerate 1 hour or until firm.
Yields 4 dozen.

title: meat balls snack
directions: Mix all ingredients, except barbecue sauce.
Roll into inch size balls.
Brown in oil in pan.
When browned, simmer in barbecue sauce for 1/2 hour.
Can be served with toothpick from crock-pot and recipe may be doubled for large crowd.

title: processor french bread
directions: Dissolve the yeast and sugar in the warm water.
While yeast proofs, measure the unbleached flour, bread flour and salt into processor bowl.
Turn processor on; add yeast mixture.
Process until ball of dough forms, then process 40 seconds more.
(If ball doesn't form, add a few drops of water.
If dough sticks to the sides too much, add a tablespoon of flour.)
Remove dough; place in plastic bag.
Expel air and close top (allow room for dough to expand).
Let rise until doubles.
Punch down, reclose bag and refrigerate for 8 hours or up to 5 days.

title: b~b~q pork chops
directions: Mix all pour over pork chops.
Cover.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: cinnamon me cookies
directions: Preheat oven as per cookie package.
Give each child 2 slices from cookie roll, 1 to 1 1/2 inches thick.
Roll out the first letter of both their first and last names.
For small children, have their letters drawn on cardboard for them to follow.
Rub hands in flour as needed.
Place letters on ungreased cookie sheet and brush with melted butter.
Sprinkle with sugar and cinnamon mixture.
Bake as per package directions and serve with milk!

title: chili
directions: In skillet cook ground beef and onion until done.
Pour off drippings.
Add chili powder, catsup, salt and black pepper.
Mix well and simmer for 15 minutes.
Can be used for hot dogs, hamburgers or chili beans.

title: red velvet cake
directions: Cream sugar, butter and vanilla until fluffy.
Cook flour and milk in double boiler.
Let cool and blend together on low speed.

title: pumpkin spice cookies
directions: Combine flour, soda, salt and pumpkin pie spice. Blend sugars with electric mixer; add butter and beat to a grainy paste.
Add pumpkin, egg and vanilla.
Beat at medium speed until light and fluffy.
Add flour mixture, raisins and walnuts.
Blend at low speed, just until combined.
Drop by rounded tablespoonfuls on ungreased cookie sheet, 1 1/2 inches apart.
Bake in preheated 300° oven for 22 to 24 minutes or until brown around the edges.

title: pound cake
directions: Mix sugar and oil. Cream together and add eggs, one at a time. Add flavoring.
Mix in flour and milk.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Blend all ingredients.
Pour into 2 greased loaf pans.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour.
Cool; remove from pans.

title: festive sweet potatoes
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Mash sweet potatoes, blending with milk and margarine until smooth.
Season to taste with salt and pepper. Turn into baking dish.
Place marshmallows around top of sweet potatoes covering completely.
Bake for 25 to 30 minutes. Marshmallows should be puffed up and browned.
Serve immediately as marshmallows will collapse quickly.

title: blueberry crunch
directions: Mix margarine (melted), nuts and flour together.
Press evenly into a baking dish.
Bake at 350° until browned.
Let cool, then mix cream cheese, powdered sugar and Cool Whip.
Spread over crust evenly.
Top with blueberry pie filling.

title: vinegar pie
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Pour into unbaked pie shell; bake at 300° for 1 hour.

title: great grandma's cheese cake
directions: Butter and flour bottom of spring-form pan.
In 1 bowl (large), blend room temperature, cottage and cream cheeses.
Add and blend sour cream; set aside.
In another bowl, beat eggs lightly.
Add sugar, butter, cornstarch and flour, beating after each addition.
Beat this until fluffy, then add to cheese mixture.
Fold in carefully.
Add vanilla and lemon juice without beating.
Pour into pan.
Place in preheated 350° oven.
Bake for 1 hour.
Turn off oven and let to cool in oven for 2 hours.
Put in refrigerator for 24 hours.

title: lime cottage cheese salad
directions: Mix together and congeal.

title: onion roasted potatoes
directions: Preheat oven to 450°.
In large bowl add all ingredients and mix well until potatoes are evenly coated.
Pour into shallow baking dish and bake, stirring occasionally, for 40 minutes or until potatoes are tender and golden brown.
Makes 8 servings.

title: homemade goo-goos
directions: Melt chocolate chips, butterscotch chips and peanut butter in a heavy saucepan over low heat. When barely melted, pour over marshmallows and peanuts; mix. Drop by spoonfuls on wax paper or on a foil-lined cookie sheet. Refrigerate to harden. Makes about 3 dozen.

title: baked mashed potatoes
directions: Peel, boil and drain the potatoes.
In large bowl, beat the potatoes until smooth.
Add the sour cream, cottage cheese, onion salt and pepper and beat again to mix well.
Ignore the lumps from the cottage cheese.
They will disappear in the baking.
Spread the potato mixture in the well-greased 13 x 9-inch baking dish.
Top with butter and sprinkle with paprika.
At this point, you can go ahead and bake the potatoes or you can refrigerate them for up to 24 hours.
Bake in a 350° oven for 1/2 hour (45 minutes if they have been in the refrigerator).
Serves 10 to 12.

title: t.v. mix
directions: Melt butter.
Pour over other ingredients which have been mixed together.
Place in a large shallow pan.
Bake at 275° for 45 minutes.

title: apple and yam casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Combine apple pie filling and sweet potatoes in a buttered 7 x 11-inch baking dish.
Dot with butter; sprinkle lightly with apple pie spice and chopped nuts.
Bake for 30 minutes, until bubbly.
Serves 8.

title: apple pie
directions: Pare, quarter and the half each quarter.
Place in a large bowl and sprinkle with 2 tablespoons lemon juice over apples.
Mix sugar, flour and spices to taste. Sprinkle this over the apples to coat well.
Put mixture in pie crust.
Combine 1/2 cup sugar and 1/2 cup flour in a small bowl.
Cut in the butter until crumbly and sprinkle over apples.
Bake, covered loosely with foil, in a 425° oven for 1 hour.

Remove pie from oven. Drizzle 1/2 cup whipping cream over pie and bake another 15 minutes, uncovered (until golden brown). Remove pie from oven and drizzle another 1/2 cup whipping cream over the pie and cool it for 1 hour before slicing.
Serve plain, with cheese or with ice cream.

title: elephant stew
directions: Cut elephant into bite size pieces.
This should take about 2 months.
Add brown gravy to cover.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Cook over kerosene fire for about 4 weeks at 465°.
This will serve about 3,800 people.
If more guests should arrive, add 2 rabbits, but only if necessary, as most people do not like to find hare in their food!

title: peanut butter rice chex
directions: Melt butter, peanut butter and chips together over low heat. Coat Chex with mixture.
Put in bread sack or Ziploc bag.
Add sugar and shake to coat.

title: lasagna
directions: In large heavy saucepan, lightly brown beef and onion.
Add tomatoes, tomato paste, water, parsley, salt, sugar, garlic, pepper and oregano.
Simmer, uncovered, stirring occasionally for about 30 minutes.

title: bernice mingo's barbecue sauce
directions: Combine all ingredients in a saucepan.
Simmer 40 to 60 minutes.

title: uncle mike's pepper steak and pasta
directions: In a wok or large frying pan, heat oil over medium heat.
Add meat and cook, stirring constantly.
Add soy sauce and garlic and continue to stir.
Add onions and pepper and keep stirring.
Add tomato and cover pan for about one minute.
Remove cover and add drained pasta.
Stir well.
If pasta is too dry, add more oil or soy sauce.
Makes one serving.

title: barbecue sauce
directions: Saute onion with oleo.
Then add all other ingredients.

title: bun candy bar
directions: Melt the chips and peanut butter together.
Pour half the mixture into a large buttered pan.
Mix the butter, milk and pudding together and boil 1 minute.
Add the vanilla and powdered sugar to the pudding mixture and spoon over the first layer.
Add the nuts to the remaining chip mixture; spoon over the second layer.
Chill and cut into pieces.

title: cherry glaze
directions: Mix sugar and cornstarch in small pan.
Stir in cup of liquid. Cook, stirring constantly.
Bring to boil for 1 minute.
Remove from heat; stir in cherries and 4 drops of red food coloring.

title: cheesy cube steak
directions: In saucepan, combine ingredients, except steaks and cheese. Simmer for 10 minutes.
In heavy skillet, brown steaks in 1 tablespoon oil or spray skillet with Pam.
Pour sauce over steaks. Simmer 25 minutes.
Sprinkle cheese over steaks.
Cover until cheese melts.
I like to serve this with rice.

title: annie's chicken with artichokes
directions: Flour chicken.
Cook chicken in butter in large skillet.
Add artichokes and marinate; add mushrooms.
Remove pan from heat and add wine.
Return to heat and cook 2 to 3 minutes more.
Serve over rice.

title: hot lettuce
directions: Fry bacon and drain.
Mix flour with water, then add vinegar and sugar for a sweet and sour taste.
Add egg, then add to the fried bacon.
Cook and stir over medium heat until it bubbles. Pour over cut up lettuce; slice a hard-boiled egg over top.

title: tortilla bake
directions: Cook meat until brown; drain.
Add onion, pepper and chili pepper.
Cook about 5 minutes more.
Add soup; heat to boiling. Place layer of tortillas in ovenproof dish.
Pour soup mixture in layers with tortillas.
Sprinkle each layer with cheese.
Bake 45 minutes at 350°.

title: fruit cake dark
directions: Halve cherries, nut meats and dates.
Dredge fruits and nuts in 1/4 cup flour. Cream the shortening and sugar.
Add honey and eggs.
Beat well. Sift second amount of flour with dry ingredients and add alternately with fruit juice to creamed mixture. Beat thoroughly.
Pour batter over floured fruits and mix well.
Line 2 greased 3 1/2 x 7 1/2-inch loaf pans.
Line with wax paper, allowing 1/2-inch to extend above all sides of pan.
Pour batter into pans.
Don't flatten. Bake in low oven at 250° about 3 hours.

title: lime congealed salad
directions: Dissolve cream cheese in boiling water.
Add jello, pineapple, milk and nuts.
Congeal.

title: blackened seasoning mix
directions: Mix all and store in glass jar.

title: family pie
directions: Mix together smoothly the forgiveness, love and unselfishness. To blend these, use as much as needed of complete faith in God. Then add the wisdom and good nature for flavor.
Sprinkle generously with thoughtfulness.
This makes a wonderful family pie.

title: out of this world salad
directions: Pour water over jello and marshmallows.
Stir until marshmallows are partially melted.
Add crushed pineapple.
Chill until jelled.
Fold in nuts, cottage cheese and cherries.
Fold in whipped cream.
Chill until firm.

title: stuffed pepper soup
directions: In a large kettle, cook beef and drain. Add remaining ingredients and bring to a boil. Reduce heat; simmer,
covered, 1 hour or until rice is tender. Makes 20 cups.

title: bran muffins(note:  batter will keep in refrigerator for 6 weeks)
directions: Mix in very large bowl starting with salt and ending with Raisin Bran.
Grease muffin pans and fill to the top with batter. Bake at 400° for 20 minutes.

title: good corn bread
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients, then add enough buttermilk to make creamy.
Pour into greased iron skillet and cook at 450° until done.

title: salmon loaf
directions: Combine ingredients in order given.
Pack firmly into buttered loaf pan (I use Pam spray) and bake in moderate oven (350°) for 30 to 40 minutes.
Turn out onto platter and garnish with sliced hard-boiled eggs and sliced peppers.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: pancakes
directions: Combine dry ingredients.
Add eggs, oil, vanilla, yogurt and milk.
Add milk and yogurt until desired consistency.
Makes 10 to 15.

title: apple crunch
directions: Peel
apples
and
slice
thinly into well-greased pan. Combine
remaining ingredients and sprinkle over apples.
Bake 35 minutes in 350° oven.
Delicious and so easy to make.

title: scallop casserole
directions: Boil scallops 4 minutes; drain.
Saute onion in butter; add soup, milk and cheese.
Cook until cheese melts.
Place scallops in bottom of casserole, then string beans.
Add soup mix, sprinkle bread crumbs and 2 teaspoons butter on top.
Bake at 425° for 30 minutes.

title: pound cake
directions: Cream Crisco and sugar.
Add eggs one at a time.
Add milk and flour alternately.
Add flavoring and baking powder.
Mix well until creamy.
Bake in tube pan until pick comes out clean (1 1/2 hours).
Start out with cold oven.
Do not preheat.

title: marzetti
directions: Cut steak into bite-size pieces.
Heat until brown in a small amount of oil.
Cook onions with steak until tender.
Add mushrooms.
Place curly noodles on top of steak, onions and mushrooms.
Pour in 5 cups of tomato juice.
Simmer all in electric skillet or frying pan for about 30 minutes until noodles are cooked.
Top with grated cheese until melted.
Makes 8 servings.

title: ceviche
directions: Cut fish fillets into small pieces and put into glass or plastic bowl.

Squeeze juice and pulp from limes and add to bowl. Cover and let stand in cool (room temperature) place for one hour (or in refrigerator overnight), stirring occasionally to make sure all fish pieces are covered with lime juice.
The fish will turn white, as if cooked over fire.
Peel tomatoes.
Chop tomatoes, onion and jalapenos into small pieces.
Add vegetables, oil, vinegar and oregano to fish and stir.
Add salt and pepper to taste.
Serve chilled.

title: custard pie
directions: Mix beaten egg whites, salt and sugar; mix well.
Pour into pie shell.
Sprinkle with nutmeg.
Bake at 375°.

title: sauerkraut and sausage
directions: Cook over low to medium heat on top of stove or bake at 350° for an hour.

title: italian stuffing for chicken or turkey
directions: Mix all together in given order.

title: pineapple pound cake
directions: Cream shortening and butter; have it very soft.
Add sugar and cream well.
Add eggs one at a time beating thoroughly after each one.
Sift flour with baking powder and add one spoon at a time alternately with milk.
Add vanilla, stir in crushed pineapple juice and blend well. Pour into well greased and floured tube pan and place in cold oven.
Turn on heat to 325° and bake 1 1/2 hours or until cake tester comes out clean.
Let stand in pan a few minutes, then run knife around pan to loosen and turn on rack to cool.

title: lo-fat pumpkin cheese cake
directions: Cream the cheese, sugar, vanilla, pumpkin and spices together at medium speed until well blended.
Add egg and blend well.
Pour into graham cracker crust. Bake at 350° for 40 minutes or until center is almost set.
Cool.
Refrigerate for at least 3 hours. Serve with nondairy, low-fat whipped topping.

title: cheese roll
directions: Roll out Velveeta between waxed paper.
Mix remaining ingredients together.
Spread mixture in middle of Velveeta.
Roll up in loaf fashion.
Let stand in refrigerator 24 hours.

title: pineapple upside-down cake
directions: Melt 1/3 cup butter in heavy iron skillet.
Sprinkle 1/2 cup brown sugar over butter.
Arrange pineapple, putting maraschino cherries in center of pineapple.
Make batter and pour over. Batter:
Beat eggs 5 minutes.
Beat in all at once 6 tablespoons pineapple juice and vanilla.
Beat in all at once the flour.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes, according to oven.
Turn upside down and let set before lifting skillet.

title: ski chalet crab bisque
directions: Combine soup ingredients in large saucepan, stirring until blended.
Simmer over medium heat for 10 minutes.
Serve with croutons.

title: pumpkin cheese roll
directions: Make pumpkin roll first, greasing a 15 1/2 x 10 1/2 x 1-inch jelly roll pan.
Line with parchment or wax paper.
If using wax paper, flour paper, shaking out the excess flour; set aside.

title: peanut butter candy
directions: Boil sugar, milk and butter for 1 minute.
Stir in peanut butter, crackers and vanilla.
Drop by teaspoons onto wax paper.

title: poultry and greens salad
directions: Tear pre-washed greens into bite-sized pieces; add poultry. Add nuts and raisins.
Spread sprouts over top.
Add croutons and refrigerate to chill.
Just before serving, add Feta and good vinaigrette or your favorite dressing.

title: breakfast pizza
directions: Spread crescent rolls onto jelly roll pan.
Top with hash browns, ham and other toppings.
Pour egg mixture over entire area and top with cheese.
Bake at 375° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: earthquake cake
directions: Grease 9 x 13-inch pan well.
Combine coconut and pecans; spread in bottom of pan.
Mix cake as directed on box.
Pour over coconut and pecan mixture.
Mix together remaining ingredients and drop by spoonfuls over cake.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes.

title: chicken noodle soup
directions: Prepare the eggs and set aside.
Put all the vegetables into the soup kettle and cover with water.
Better to use more and cook down. You may need to add even more water when you add the noodles.
Cook until quite soft.
Break up the noodles and add. When they are done, add milk or cream to suit your taste.
Season. For amounts, use one nest of noodles and one egg per person.

title: christmas brew
directions: Put all ingredients into a crock-pot; turn on high until it reaches boiling point, turn to low and let simmer.

title: blondie swirls
directions: Melt butter in saucepan; add brown sugar and stir until combined.
Remove from heat and cool.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each addition.
Stir in vanilla.
Combine flour, baking powder and salt.
Add to sugar mixture, stirring well.
Stir in nuts and 1/4 cup chocolate chips.
Spread batter in greased and floured 13 x 9-inch pan.
Sprinkle with remaining chocolate chips.
Bake at 350° for 3 minutes.
Remove from oven and gently swirl batter with a knife.
Return to oven and bake additional 20 minutes.
Cool and cut into bars.
Makes about 2 1/2 dozen.

title: corn and broccoli bake
directions: Combine and put into a 1/2-quart buttered casserole. Mix 1/4 cup cracker crumbs and 5 tablespoons butter; sprinkle over top. Bake in 350° oven for 45 minutes.

title: zucchini bread-and-butter pickles
directions: Combine zucchini, onion, bell pepper, salt and ice.
Let stand 1 hour.
Combine remaining ingredients in kettle and heat to boiling.
Drain zucchini mixture well and add to syrup; let stand 1 hour.
Reheat to boiling, stirring occasionally with wooden spoon.
Pour into sterilized jars and seal.
Ready to serve after pickles have set overnight.

title: seafood casserole
directions: Saute bell pepper, onion, celery, garlic, onion and parsley in margarine until translucent.
Add crayfish, crabmeat or shrimp; cook 5 minutes.
Add mushrooms, soup, rice and sour cream.
Mix well.
Pour in greased casserole and bake at 350° for 45 minutes. Add cheeses on top last 15 minutes of baking.

title: mexican cornbread
directions: Mix all together.
Bake at 400° for about 45 minutes.

title: grandma's potato-rice souffle
directions: Prepare mashed potatoes.
Prepare Carolina rice.
Mix all ingredients well in large bowl.
Pour in large souffle dish/pan. Preheat oven to 400°.
Cook for approximately 40 minutes or until top light golden brown.
Serve as appetizer or side dish.

title: veg-all casserole
directions: Mix and top with crushed Ritz crackers.
Bake 30 minutes at 350°.

title: oreo cookie dessert
directions: Crush Oreos.
Line a 9-inch pan with most of the crushed cookies (save some for topping). Cream the butter and sugar.
Add egg; cream again. Add almond flavoring. Spread this mixture on crumbs.
Whip the cream with sugar.
Add vanilla and chopped pecans. Fold until well blended. Spread this on first mixture. Cover with rest of crushed cookies.
Let stand in refrigerator overnight.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: 7-up salad
directions: Drain pineapple; save juice.
Dissolve jello in 2 cups hot water.
Mash bananas.
Add 7-Up, pineapple and bananas to jello. Put into a 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan; chill until set.

title: super duper chocolate cookies
directions: Melt shortening and chocolate together.
Add sugar and vanilla and mix well.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating after each.
Sift together flour, baking powder and salt.
Add to chocolate mixture with nuts and mix well.
Chill dough several hours. Form into small balls and roll in confectioners sugar.
Bake at 350° for 12 to 15 minutes.
Makes about 6 dozen.

title: potato candy
directions: Boil potato. Cool and remove peel. Mash potato well. Add margarine, vanilla and powdered sugar a little at a time. Mix well. Add pecans into mixture. Roll into balls and set aside. Melt chocolate chips and paraffin in a double boiler over low flame. Dip rolled balls into chocolate and place on waxed paper to cool.

title: hash brown casserole
directions: Mix ingredients together at 350° for 45 minutes.
Top with cornflakes and butter.

title: red beet eggs
directions: Drain liquid from beets.
Add water, if necessary, to measure 1 cup. Combine beet liquid, vinegar, sugar, salt and pickling spices in small saucepan.
Heat to boiling, stirring constantly. Put beets and peeled eggs in a nonmetal bowl or jar.
Pour hot mixture over beets and eggs; cover tightly with plastic wrap or jar lid.
Refrigerate at least 24 hours.

title: vet bollen(fat balls)
directions: Cream sugar and eggs.
Add dry and liquid ingredients alternately.
Drop by tablespoons in hot oil.
Fry until golden and place on paper towels to drain.
Roll in granulated sugar while warm.
Use deep fryer or skillet at 400°.

title: tuna pasta salad
directions: In large bowl, mix dressing, dill weed and black pepper. Add remaining ingredients. Mix and chill. Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: broccoli salad
directions: Mix together first 4 ingredients; set aside.
Mix salad dressing, sugar, seasoning, vinegar and grease.
Combine all ingredients and toss together.
Let set 2 hours, then serve.

title: brown rice
directions: Blend and cook rice according to package directions, but instead of using prescribed amount of water, used soup and water to equal the prescribed amount.
Add mushrooms, if desired.
Boil on stove top.

title: curt's spaghetti sauce
directions: Add or subtract ingredients according to taste.

title: cheap and easy punch
directions: Mix all together and chill or freeze until slushy.

title: potato-corn flake casserole
directions: Over heat combine soup, cheese, sour cream, salt and onion until well blended.
Add potatoes and coat with mixture.
Place mixture in a greased 9 x 13-inch casserole dish.
Combine corn flakes with melted oleo and top mixture.
Bake uncovered at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: lava rocks
directions: Dice and layer potatoes in bottom of pan.
Dice thin layer of the onion and place on top of the potatoes.
Cover with seasoning (optional).
Cover with uncooked rice.
Crumble uncooked hamburger meat and cover the potatoes, onion and rice mixture.
Pat down evenly.
Add 1 can of Ranch Style beans and cover with tomato sauce.
Cover with aluminum foil and bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: spaghetti sauce
directions: Microwave on High for 10 minutes.
Reduce power to 40% (Simmer) for 2 hours.
Stir twice during cooking.
Add meat balls last hour.
Serve over spaghetti noodles.

title: peanut butter fingers
directions: In a bowl, cream the butter and sugar; blend in remaining ingredients, except chocolate bits, powdered sugar, peanut butter and canned milk. Spread in an 11 x 14-inch pan. Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes. Sprinkle with chocolate bits; let stand 5 minutes.

title: harvey wallbanger cake
directions: Mix all ingredients together and beat for 4 minutes.
Pour batter into well-greased and lightly floured Bundt or tube pan. Bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes.
Dust with confectioners sugar before serving.

title: frozen strawberry cake
directions: Combine ingredients in order listed.
Blend well.
Line your pan with wax paper.
Fill with mixture and freeze until firm.
Cut in squares and serve with whipped cream and nuts on top.

title: yankee cobbler
directions: Melt oleo or butter in an 8 x 8-inch square pan.
Add fruit and its juice.
(Peaches or cherries are best; but any fruit may be used, fresh or canned.)
Make a batter of the flour, milk, sugar, baking powder and salt.
Pour the batter over the melted butter and the fruit.
Bake at 375° for about 30 minutes (about 45 minutes for cherries).
Serves approximately 4 to 5 people.

title: lasagna (low-fat)
directions: Cook lasagna noodles until tender.
Brown ground meat.
In greased casserole dish, layer noodles, sauce, ground meat, cheeses and mushrooms.
Continue layering until all ingredients are used. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until cheese is melted.

title: sour cream and chicken enchiladas
directions: Mix sour cream, soup and cheese in medium saucepan. Heat until melted together. Take chicken and wrap in tortillas. Place in baking dish. Cover with mixture. Cook at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes or until bubbly.

title: baked beans
directions: Mostly drain pork and beans.
Add and mix all other ingredients.
Place bacon on top or in beans.
Bake at 325° for 1 to 2 hours.

title: two-minute hawaiian pie
directions: In a large bowl, combine the vanilla pudding mix, undrained crushed pineapple and sour cream; mix until well blended.
Pour mixture into pie crust.
Decorate with sliced pineapple and cherries and sprinkle with coconut.
Chill for at least 2 hours before serving.

title: cheesecake bars
directions: Stir together the first 4 ingredients.
Add melted butter; mix until crumbly.
Pat into ungreased 9 x 9 x 2-inch baking pan. Bake at 350° for 12 minutes.

title: mini pizzas
directions: Toast bread.
Spread sauce over the toasted bread.
Sprinkle cheese on top.
Add 3 pieces of pepperoni on each piece (if desired).
Put into the microwave for 45 seconds (for 2 pieces).

title: teriyaki meatballs
directions: Mix soy sauce, water, sugar, onion, garlic salt and onion.
Let stand 10 minutes.
Combine beef and bread crumbs.
Stir in soy sauce mixture.
Shape into balls, these may be fondued, broiled or fried.

title: pot pie
directions: In 3 quart oblong baking dish, combine soups, milk, thyme and pepper; stir in vegetables and chicken or ham.
Bake at 400° for 15 minutes.
Cut each biscuit into quarters.
Remove dish from oven; stir.
Top with biscuit quarters along the edge.
Bake 15 minutes longer or until biscuits are golden.

title: broccoli-cheese soup
directions: Chop up onion, celery, carrots and broccoli.
Saute in oleo. Add broccoli last.
Add flour and chicken broth.
Stir, about 2 minutes.
Add milk and heat until near boiling.
Add cheese, salt, pepper and cayenne.

title: spinach casserole
directions: Blend ingredients.
Place in greased 9 x 9-inch casserole. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: mother's punch
directions: Mix altogether and serve with a pretty ice ring.
Serves 75 to 80.

title: fresh strawberry pie
directions: Cook together jello, cornstarch, water and lemon juice.
Add red food coloring, if you wish.
Cool.
Pour over berries and stir gently.
Pour into baked pie shell.
Chill at least 4 hours. Serve with ice cream or whipped cream.

title: barbecue cups
directions: You will need 2 muffin tins for this recipe.

title: twinkie cake
directions: Place Twinkies cakes in the bottom of container.
Spread crushed pineapple (do not drain) over Twinkies.
Mix pudding as directed on box.
Pour pudding over Twinkies and pineapple. Refrigerate until pudding becomes firm.
Spread Cool Whip over top.
Store in refrigerator.
The longer the cake sits, the better it will be.

title: beefy vegetable soup(makes 8 to 10 servings)
directions: Cook beef and onions until brown.
Add vegetables, seasonings and liquid into large pot.
Don't add red wine until after soup has cooked for 45 minutes.
Before serving, add wine.
Heat and remove bay leaves.
Soup is enhanced with longer cooking time. Keeps well in refrigerator.
Also freezes well.

title: grape-nuts custard
directions: Dissolve Grape-Nuts in 1 cup warm water and drain.
Beat eggs; add milk and all other ingredients; blend.
Bake in casserole for 1 hour at 350°.

title: crunch torte
directions: Beat egg whites until frothy; add cream of tartar and beat until stiff.
Beat in vanilla flavoring.
Crush soda crackers lightly with rolling pin.
They should not be too fine.
Mix well with sugar.
Fold in egg whites.
Add nuts; pour into 9-inch pie pan.
Bake 30 minutes in slow oven (325°).
Cut into pie wedge. Serve with whipped cream or ice cream.
Serves 6.

title: pineapple sauce
directions: Mix brown sugar, cornstarch and salt in saucepan.
Stir in pineapple, lemon juice and mustard.
Cook over medium heat, stirring until thick.
Boil, stirring 1 minute.
Use on baked ham.

title: enchiladas
directions: Combine enchilada sauce and diced tomatoes. Pour in 9 x 13-inch pan just to cover bottom. On each flour tortilla spread spoonful of refried beans, top with spoonful of meat and sprinkle with a little of each cheese. Roll up and place in pan. Pour remainder of sauce and tomatoes over all rolled up tortillas. Cover with foil and bake at 350° for 30 minutes. Remove foil and cover with cheeses. Bake 5 to 10 minutes or until cheese melts.

title: swiss buttermilk biscuits
directions: In a large mixing bowl, thoroughly combine 3/4 cup flour, sugar, baking powder, salt and undissolved yeast.
Combine buttermilk, water and shortening in a saucepan.
Heat over low heat until liquids are very warm (120° to 130°).
Shortening does not need to melt.
Gradually add to dry ingredients and beat 2 minutes at medium speed of electric mixer, scraping bowl occasionally.
Add 3/4 cup flour and beat at high speed 2 minutes, scraping bowl occasionally.
Stir in cheese and enough additional flour to make a soft dough.
Turn out onto lightly floured board and knead until smooth, about 5 minutes.

title: potato salad
directions: Cook potatoes with the skins on until done but not soft.
Peel and dice potatoes and mix with eggs, onions and celery.
Mix remaining ingredients together and add to prepared vegetables.

title: white loaf bread
directions: Measure the water in a large bowl.
Sprinkle in the yeast and stir until dissolved.
Add sugar, Crisco shortening, salt and half the flour.
Beat well.
Add remaining flour and blend until smooth. Scrape batter from side of bowl; cover with a cloth and let rise in a warm place until double in bulk.
Stir down the batter and spread evenly in a greased loaf pan (9 x 5 x 3-inch).
Batter will be sticky.
Let rise in warm place until batter reaches 1-inch from top of pan.
Bake in moderate oven (375°) for 45 to 50 minutes or until brown.

title: ritzy broccoli
directions: Cook broccoli in water 5 minutes; drain well.
Combine soup, eggs, mayonnaise and diced cheese; mix well.
Add broccoli and pour into baking dish (cake pan).
Sprinkle on cracker crumbs and dot with butter.
Bake 30 to 35 minutes in a 350° oven.

title: chalupas
directions: Soak beans overnight.
Drain.
Put all ingredients into crock-pot.
Cover with water.
Cook on low temperature 8 to 10 hours.
Remove roast and debone.
Put meat back into pot and cook 1 more hour to improve flavor.

title: fruit dip
directions: Cream oleo with brown sugar.
Add sour cream, vanilla and cinnamon.

title: peanut butter bonbon
directions: Mix the first 3 ingredients together and roll into balls. Refrigerate 2 hours.
Dip in chocolate mix consisting of the chocolate chips and paraffin melted in a double boiler.
Put on cookie sheet lined with aluminum foil.
Put in refrigerator or freezer. (May be put in container in freezer until ready to use.)

title: mandarin orange salad
directions: Dissolve jello in boiling water.
Add enough water to juice from oranges to make 1 cup.
Stir into jello mixture.
Chill until thickened.
Fold in the sherbet and fruit.
Chill until firm.

title: sherried cheese spread
directions: In a small bowl, beat cream cheese with sherry until blended. Mix mustard with hot water.
Let stand for 2 minutes to develop flavor.
Stir into cream cheese mixture with Cheddar cheese.
Turn into small bowl.
Cover and chill until ready to serve.
Garnish with parsley.
Serves 50.

title: cardamom shortbread
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In a medium bowl, cream butter and sugar until fluffy.
Stir in oats and vanilla.
In a small bowl, sift together flour and cardamom.
Add dry ingredients to creamed mixture.
Stir until a soft dough forms.
Press into a greased 8-inch round shortbread mold or 9-inch round cake pan.
Bake 20 to 30 minutes or until light brown.
Cool in pan 10 minutes.
Loosen edges with a knife.
Invert onto a cutting board.
If necessary, tap edge of pan on cutting board.
Cut warm shortbread into wedges.
Cool completely.
Store in an airtight container.
Yield: 6 to 8 servings.

title: mama mayer's german potato salad
directions: In a medium skillet, combine bacon grease, flour, vinegar, water and sugar.
Cook until it begins to thicken, stirring often (about 2 minutes).
Add onions and crumbled bacon to gravy. Pour over potatoes and gently stir together.
Serve warm.

title: 7-up salad
directions: Prepare jello according to directions on package, substituting 7-Up for water.
Refrigerate until thick, not set.
With electric mixer add cream cheese, 1/2 whipped topping and optional fruit and marshmallows.
Refrigerate until set.
Garnish with remaining whipped topping, if desired.
Serves 6 to 10 people.

title: 3-beans baked beans
directions: Fry bacon.
Drain on paper towels and crumble.
Brown onion and pepper in a little of the bacon drippings.
Brown ground chuck and drain.
Mix all ingredients.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: lasagna
directions: Brown beef, onion, garlic and oregano in skillet.
Add soup, water and vinegar.
Simmer 30 minutes.
Arrange in 12 x 8 x 2-inch baking dish, three alternate layers of noodles, cottage cheese, meat sauce and Mozzarella cheese.
Top with Parmesan cheese.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Let stand 15 minutes before eating.

title: better than sex cakelubbock, texas
directions: Prepare cake mix as directed on package.
Cool.

title: dried apples cooked for pies
directions: Mix together and let sit overnight. And cook the next morning until tender. Put into jars and seal.

title: meal in a peel
directions: Bake potatoes for 1 hour in preheated 400° oven.
Cut potatoes in half and scoop out insides.
Place in a bowl.
Place shells on baking sheet and set aside.
Add margarine, tuna or meat, cheese soup, salt and pepper and mix well.
Spoon potato back in shells and place half a slice of cheese on top.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes or until filling and cheese are hot.

title: cordon blue
directions: Cover each half breast of chicken with slice of cheese, then ham.
Secure with toothpicks.
Melt butter in skillet and add chicken (ham side up); do not turn over.
Use medium heat.
Mix milk with soup and pour over all, stirring sauce around chicken occasionally.
Cover and cook 20 minutes.
Serve with chopped parsley.

title: garden vegetable salad
directions: Combine carrots and water in a 2-quart microwave-safe casserole.
Cover with lid.
Microwave on High for 3 to 3 1/2 minutes.
Add broccoli and cauliflower.
Cover and microwave on High for 4 to 4 1/2 minutes.
Uncover and cool slightly.
Drain juice into Italian dressing.
Mix well.
Combine all together. Mix lightly.
Cover and refrigerate for at least 3 hours or overnight.
Add radishes just before serving.

title: simpson's swiss steak
directions: Pound or rub in salt, pepper and flour on steak.
Brown in hot oil along with slices of onion.
Pile onions on meat.
Mix tomato sauce, a little water, and Tabasco sauce to taste.
Pour over steak.
Simmer, covered, about 1 hour.
Steak may be cut into serving size pieces before cooking if desired.

title: cappuccino mix
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Use 1 tablespoon per 6 ounce cup of hot water.

title: cereal cookies
directions: Cook sugar and syrup to full boil.
Add peanut butter.
Pour over cereal in buttered 13 x 8-inch or 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.

title: cheddar dill bread
directions: Combine flour and sugar.
Cut in butter until crumbled; stir in the cheese and dill.
In another bowl, beat egg and milk; pour into dry ingredients and stir just until moistened.
Batter will be very thick.
Pour into a greased loaf pan.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes until the bread tests done.
Cool in pan 10 minutes before removing to rack to cool.

title: pecan pie
directions: Mix first three ingredients.
Then add eggs, slightly beaten. Add other ingredients.
Pour in unbaked pie shell and cook for about 50 minutes at 300°.

title: chicken soup
directions: Boil chicken in large pot until cooked.
Remove chicken and dice into small pieces.
Add tomato sauce and vegetables to chicken stock.
Cook until tender.
Add chicken and noodles.
Boil 10 minutes.

title: baked eggplant parmigiana
directions: Wash eggplant; cut into 1/2-inch thick slices.
Combine egg with water; beat.
Dip eggplant into egg mixture, then into crumbs.
Saute in oil until brown and tender.
In lightly greased 2-quart casserole, place eggplant slices in layers, alternating with sauce, seasoning and cheese.
Bake at 375° for 30 to 40 minutes.
Serves 6.

title: almond tea
directions: Combine the boiling water and sugar.
Then add other ingredients.

title: wash-day cobbler
directions: In medium saucepan, heat fruit until boiling.
Meanwhile, melt margarine in a 1 1/2-quart casserole.
In medium mixing bowl, combine flour, 1 cup sugar, milk, baking powder and salt.
Pour batter into melted margarine.
Add hot fruit.
Sprinkle 3/4 cup sugar over entire casserole.
Bake in preheated 400° oven for 20 to 30 minutes.
Serve warm with vanilla ice cream.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: kim's chili
directions: Brown ground beef, sausage, and onion; drain and put back in pot. Add other ingredients and enough water to cover ingredients about 2 inches. Add chili powder and salt to taste. Simmer for about 1 hour.

title: boiled spice cake
directions: Boil first six ingredients for 20 minutes.
Let cool.
When cool, add flour, baking soda and nuts.
Bake in moderate oven (350°) until done.
Test with a toothpick.
Cake is done when the toothpick comes out clean.
Should be baked in loaf pans.

title: wild rice chicken or pork chops
directions: Brown chicken breasts or pork chops.
In casserole, mix all ingredients.
Place chicken or pork chops on top.
Bake covered 1 hour at 350°.
Uncover.
Bake 1/2 hour more.

title: chicken & broccoli au gratin
directions: Melt butter in skillet. Saute onions until transparent. Remove from heat. Stir in flour, salt, curry powder and pepper. Drain mushrooms, reserving liquid. Add water to make 1/2 cup liquid. Gradually stir into flour mixture in skillet. Blend in evaporated milk until smooth. Add mushrooms. Cook and stir over medium heat until sauce begins to thicken. Arrange broccoli spears and chicken on bottom of a 9x13 inch baking dish. Pour sauce over. Top with cheese. Bake at 375 degrees for 20 minutes, or until bubbly around edges. Cool 15 minutes before serving. Makes 6 servings.

title: pretzel salad
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Mix the first 3 ingredients and bake 8 minutes in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Remove and pat down.
Cool.

title: meat loaf barbecue style
directions: Mix beef, crumbs, onion, egg, salt, pepper and 1/2 can tomato sauce.
Put in loaf pan.
Combine remaining tomato sauce with rest of ingredients.
Bake at 350° for 1 1/4 hours.
After grease has cooked out, pour off, then pour sauce over loaf.
Return to oven to heat about 5 minutes longer.

title: crispy cookies
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Grease cookie sheet.
Stir in remaining ingredients.
Drop dough by rounded teaspoonfuls, about 2-inches apart, onto cookie sheet.
Bake until light brown, 10 to 12 minutes.
Makes about 4 1/2 dozen.

title: chicken and noodle casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients together (hold 1 package Cheddar cheese). Put mixture into pan, cover with bread crumbs and top with cheese.

title: hamburger stew
directions: In large skillet, brown ground beef.
Add onion, tomatoes, red beans and potatoes.
Simmer until potatoes are tender, even better the next day.
Salt and pepper to taste.

title: country captain chicken
directions: Mix flour, salt, paprika and pepper and coat chicken.
Brown in shortening.
Remove chicken and reserve drippings.
Add the onion, hot water, tomatoes, salt and pepper, thyme and sliced almonds.
Replace chicken in mixture and simmer for 1 hour or until chicken is tender.
Serve over rice, if desired.

title: crab rangoon
directions: Mix ingredients well.
Spoon into wonton or egg roll wraps and wrap or twist.
Shallow fry in wok or Dutch oven until golden brown.
Remove from hot grease and put in double paper bags or on paper towels to absorb excess oil.
Makes approximately 40 rangoons.

title: seven layer bars
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Layer all ingredients one at a time, in the order they are presented.
Bake for 30 minutes.
Let cool, and cut.
Quick and easy to make, also freezes well.

title: cream cheese cake
directions: Grease a 13 x 9-inch pan.
Mix first 3 ingredients together and spread in bottom of pan.
Combine last 3 ingredients with fork and pour over first layer.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: easy fudge
directions: Combine first 5 ingredients in a large saucepan.
Cook over medium heat until mixture comes to a boil, stirring constantly. Boil 5 minutes.
Remove from heat.
Add chocolate morsels and stir until melted.
Add nuts and vanilla, stirring well.
Spread in a buttered 8-inch square pan.
When cool, cut in squares.
Yields about 60 pieces.

title: old fashioned apple pie
directions: Heat oven to 425°.
Prepare pastry.
Mix the sugar, flour, lemon juice, cinnamon, nutmeg and salt.
Stir in apples.
Turn into pastry lined pie plate.
Dot with butter.
Moisten rim of bottom crust and place top crust with slits in it over filling. Fold edge of top crust under bottom crust, pressing to seal.
Bake until light brown and juice bubbles, 40 to 50 minutes.
Yields 6 servings.

title: mexican crab salad
directions: Blend salsa and sour cream.
Set aside.
Chop lettuce, olives, onions, tomatoes and crab meat.
Toss together.
Add cheese and chips.
Toss with the sour cream mixture.
Chill.
Enjoy!

title: southwestern stew
directions: In a 4-quart pot over medium high heat cook the turkey and garlic until the turkey is no longer pink, 5 to 10 minutes, stirring often.
Pour off the fat.
Add the tomato, corn, chili powder and cumin.
Bring the mixture to a boil.
Reduce the heat to low and cook for 15 minutes.
Add the macaroni and scallions and heat through.
Servings:

title: chicken casserole
directions: Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
I double and use 4 cups or more meat.

title: mini white castles
directions: Mix together and refrigerate the sour cream, soup mix and corned beef.
When ready to serve, place a dollop of beef mixture in the middle of the roll.
Add a sliced dill pickle and add top of roll. Microwave for only a couple of minutes. Serve hot.

title: skillet meat balls with vegetables
directions: Mix meat, egg, onion, bread crumbs, cornstarch, salt, pepper, ginger, nutmeg and milk in a large bowl.
Form into small (walnut size) balls.
Brown in melted shortening.
Pour onion soup and water over.
Cover and simmer 20 minutes.
Remove meat balls and add vegetables; cook until tender.
Return meat balls and mix well. Serves 6.

title: chicken loaf
directions: Place bread crumbs and margarine in a large bowl.
Add milk or broth that has been scalded and beaten until creamy.
Add onions and celery.
Add a few spoonfuls of hot mixture to eggs.
Mix and combine with mixture in bowl.
Add chicken and seasonings and pour into a greased loaf pan and bake in a 325° oven for about 45 minutes or until firm.
Let stand a few minutes, unmold and serve hot with a gravy made of chicken broth.

title: pecan pie
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Combine everything but pecans.
Add pecans and pour into 2 (9-inch) pie shells (uncooked).
Place whole pecans on top in circular design from outside to center.
Bake for 35 to 45 minutes until center is firm to touch.

title: lemonade cake
directions: Mix all ingredients except the lemonade and confectionary sugar and pour into a greased and floured 9 x 13 pan.
Bake for 35 minutes at 350°.
While cake is baking prepare a topping by combining the lemonade and confectionary sugar.

title: asparagus au gratin
directions: Cook asparagus partially.
Save 1 cup of asparagus water. Melt 2 tablespoons butter in pan.
Stir in flour and cook a moment.
Gradually add milk and reserved water to make a smooth sauce.
Simmer 15 minutes.
Add cream, ham, salt and pepper.
Pour over asparagus in a casserole dish.
Mix cheese and bread crumbs and sprinkle over sauce.
Dribble remaining butter over top of crumb mixture.
Bake at 425° for 20 minutes or until bubbly.

title: portuguese poached fish
directions: Place fish in electric skillet and cover with remaining ingredients.
When mixture has come to a boil, simmer, covered for 10 minutes.
Carefully remove fish fillets from the vegetable sauce and place on a serving platter.
Keep the fish warm by covering with foil while boiling down the sauce.
Turn up heat under the vegetables and boil quickly to reduce the mixture by half.
Pour sauce over fish and serve.
Makes 2 servings.

title: bird's nest
directions: Combine in a bowl shredded coconut and Rice Krispies.
Bring to a boil while stirring the corn syrup, brown sugar, peanut butter, and vanilla.
Remove from heat.
Stir in the Rice Krispies and the coconut.
Let it cool, then shape into bird's nest.
Fill with jelly bean "eggs."

title: sweet potato casserole
directions: Combine all ingredients, except topping, and place in buttered casserole.
Sprinkle topping mixture and bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Serves 8 to 10.

title: homemade eagle brand milk
directions: Mix in blender until smooth.

title: soupe au pistou
directions: Steam green beans 5 minutes.
Heat a little oil in a pot and saute onions; then add green beans and carrots; last add potatoes and zucchini.
Add to this 1 to 1 1/2 quarts water.
Simmer until vegetables are done.
Add macaroni.
During this time prepare the pesto:
Peel and cut up tomatoes and garlic.
Puree garlic, then add basil in a small food processor.
Slowly add tomato and then olive oil.
When the soup is done, take if off the heat and add pesto.
Serve with Parmesan cheese.
If the soup must wait, don't add pesto until ready to serve.

title: gingersnaps
directions: Mix ingredients; chill and roll in balls.
Dip in sugar.

title: easy microwave pudding
directions: *May use 1/2 teaspoon almond with 3 drops green food coloring for pistachio.

title: baked spanish rice
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In a 12-inch skillet fry the bacon crisp.
Drain on paper towels, crumble and set aside.
Pour off all but 2 tablespoons of the drippings.
In the hot drippings cook onion and green peppers for about 5 minutes or until tender, stirring.
Drain the tomatoes; add enough water to the tomato liquid to make 1 3/4 cups.
Cut up the tomatoes.
To the onion mixture add the liquid, tomatoes, tomato sauce, sugar and salt; heat to boiling.
Remove from the heat and stir in the rice.
Pour into a greased 1 1/2-quart baking dish.
Cover and bake at 350° for 35 minutes or until the rice is tender and the liquid is absorbed. Fluff the rice with a fork, sprinkle with the cheese, return to the oven and bake for another 5 minutes.
Garnish with the bacon.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Oil 4 one pound coffee cans.
Mix all ingredients together. Fill cans half full and bake at 350°.

title: apricot congealed salad
directions: Put entire can of pineapple in pan and heat with jello. Let cool.
Add	buttermilk
and
Cool
Whip.
Pour in mold and sprinkle with chopped pecans.

title: pizza rounds
directions: Brown beef and pork in skillet; drain fat.
Add spices, onion and sliced cheese.
Mix until cheese is melted.
Spread on rye bread.
Freeze on tray.
When ready to use, bake 10 to 12 minutes at 350°.

title: baked pork chops(one dish dinner)
directions: Grease a 9 x 12-inch baking dish.
Pour enough uncooked rice in dish to cover well (do not use Minute rice).
Lay pork chops on top of rice and season. Pour stewed tomatoes on top.
Cut up any large pieces.
Bake covered at 350° for 45 minutes to 1 hour.

title: meat loaf
directions: In a large bowl, combine everything but BBQ sauce; mix well. Shape into loaf on a baking pan and bake at 400° for 45 minutes or until done.
Remove from oven and cover with BBQ sauce.
Return to oven for about 15 minutes.
Rest meat loaf 5 minutes before serving.

title: peanut clusters
directions: Melt chocolate chips and peanut butter chips in microwave oven for 1 1/2 minutes or until chips are melted.
Remove from microwave oven.
Blend in nuts of your choice.
Drop by teaspoon on wax paper.
Cool.

title: easy moist white coconut cake
directions: Bake one cake mix according to package directions.
Add 1 package frozen coconut (thawed) to batter.
Mix sugar and milk. Bring to boil.
Remove from heat and pour over warm cake.
Top cake with Cool Whip mixed with frozen coconut (thawed).

title: sour cream corn bread
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Combine dry ingredients.
Combine egg, milk and butter.
Add with sour cream to flour mixture; stir until moistened.
Pour into an 8-inch square buttered pan; bake for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: blueberry gingerbread
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease 9-inch baking pan.

title: sweet potatoes(recipe came from a southern friend of mine.)
directions: Cook potatoes; drain and mash while still warm.
Add balance of ingredients (except marshmallows), as listed, stirring well after each addition.
Grease an ovenproof casserole; add mashed sweet potatoes.
Top with miniature marshmallows, just to cover top of the potato mixture.
Bake at 325° for 45 minutes.

title: chocolate chip banana bread
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Grease 2 regular loaf pans.
Mix flour, baking soda and salt; set aside.
In a large mixer bowl at medium speed, beat sugar, oil and eggs until blended.
Add bananas and beat until blended.
At low speed beat in flour mixture just until blended.
Stir in chocolate chips.
Pour into loaf pans. Bake 45 to 50 minutes or until wooden pick inserted in center comes out clean.
Remove from pans and cool.
No adjustments needed for high altitude.

title: johnniecake
directions: Do not use metal spoon or bowl.
Do not refrigerate.
On day 1, do nothing with starter.
On days, 2, 3, 4 and 5, stir with wooden spoon.
On day 6, add 1 cup flour, 1 cup sugar and 1 cup milk.
On days, 7, 8 and 9, stir with wooden spoon.
On day 10, add 1 cup flour, 1 cup sugar and 1 cup milk.
Stir and pour into 3 (1-cup) containers.
Keep one for yourself for future use and give the other 2 with a recipe to friends.
You will have 1 cup left.

title: chocolate heath delight
directions: Bake cake in 9 x 13-inch pan at 350° for 10 t 15 minutes; let cool.
Mix together the 2 puddings, milk and ice cream.
Put this on top of the cooled cake.
Put Cool Whip on cake.
Sprinkle with crumbled Heath bars.

title: five cup salad
directions: Combine.
For best flavor allow to chill an hour or so before serving.

title: chocolate carmelita bars
directions: Mix all together butter, brown sugar, water, salt, flour, oats and nuts.
Press 1/2 of dough into a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake 6 to 8 minutes at 350°.
Take out of oven; sprinkle chocolate chips over baked dough.
Spread hot caramel topping over chips.
Place dabs of last half of dough over top (cover with aluminum foil).
Bake 15 to 18 minutes at 350°.
Add 20.5 ounces of Braums hot caramel topping after baking.

title: quick and dirty miso soup
directions: Make fish broth by boiling the fish flakes in about a quart of water until the water is pale yellow and tastes fishy. Strain the flakes from the broth. Slice the scallions into very thin rounds; cut the tofu into small cubes and add both to the broth. When the scallions are soft (just a few minutes), add the miso and ginger. Heat (without boiling) to serving temperature.

title: spinach quiche
directions: Roll each pie crust into a 12 inch square; cut each square into 24 pieces.
Shape into balls and press in miniature muffin pans, that have been sprayed with cooking spray.
Cook margarine and onion over medium heat; add spinach and cook 2 minutes.
