Stir in worcestershire sauce, salt and pepper; remove from heat.
Whisk eggs and milk until blended; add cheese.
Add egg mixture to spinach; spoon into individual pie crusts.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: squash casserole
directions: Cook squash and onion in small amount of salted water until tender.
Drain off liquid.
Add 1/2 of bread crumbs, 2 tablespoons margarine, cheese, salt, pepper and egg.
Pour into buttered casserole dish and top with remaining bread crumbs.
Dot with remaining margarine.
Bake in a 375° oven for 10 minutes.

title: pecan pies
directions: Mix ingredients all together.
Pour equally into pie shells. Cook 1 hour at 300° or until the middle does not shake.

title: poppy seed chicken
directions: Boil and cut up chicken.
Mix soup and sour cream with chicken and pour in baking dish.
Top with Ritz crackers and poppy seed. Melt butter and pour over cracker crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: strawberry jell-o salad
directions: Dissolve Jell-O in 2 cups boiling water. Add berries with juice and pineapple (including juice). Mash bananas and whip them with a fork. Add to fruit mixture. Pour half of mixture in 8 x 8 dish and chill until set. Keep remaining half of mixture at room temperature. When the first half is set, spread with Cool Whip and cover with the remaining mixture.

title: cheese krispies(7 to 8 dozen)
directions: Cream margarine and cheese.
Add flour, salt and pepper.
Mix well; add cereal and mix with hands as the dough gets very stiff. Roll into walnut size balls and flatten with a fork.
Place on ungreased cookie sheet at 325° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: dad's saturday or sunday special(german pancakes)
directions: As a treat, my father and his father before him, frequently made the traditional German family pancakes when we were small children.
A tradition I have kept alive in my family.

title: sausage fondue
directions: Place cubed bread in the bottom of a 9 x 13-inch dish.
Top with grated cheese and meat.
Beat eggs with milk and mustard. Pour over bread cubes.
Refrigerate overnight or several hours. Before baking, dilute soup with 1/2 cup milk.
Pour over casserole.
Bake at 300° until set, about 1 1/2 hours.
Let set 10 to 20 minutes before serving.
Serves 12.

title: applesauce cheesecake
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
In medium bowl, beat cream cheese, sugar and eggs until smooth.
Stir in 1 cup applesauce and vanilla. Pour into graham cracker crust.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes or until center is just set.
Gently spread remaining applesauce over cheesecake.
Cool.
Refrigerate several hours.
Just before serving, sprinkle with graham cracker crumbs.
Garnish with fresh fruit if desired.
Makes 8 servings.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Beat together the first 4 ingredients.
Combine dry ingredients and add.
Mix well, then add pineapple, zucchini, walnuts and raisins.
Pour into 2 greased and floured bread pans. Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: carrot cake
directions: Mix as for any cake.
Bake in floured cake pans at 350° for about 25 minutes.
Cool and frost.

title: peanut butter blossoms
directions: Mix these ingredients to make the cookie dough.
Mix well and shape into 1 1/2-inch balls.
Roll in granulated sugar to coat the balls and place on a cookie sheet.
Bake on ungreased cookie sheet for 10 to 12 minutes at 375°.

title: sausage balls
directions: Mix all ingredients together and form into small balls.
Bake at 400° until brown, 12 minutes.
(If they are not brown, I turn on the broiler for a few minutes.)

title: pineapple crisp
directions: On low heat, melt margarine in a frying pan.
Add bread cubes until bread is lightly browned, about 15 minutes.
Mix remaining ingredients together in a bowl.
Pour into baking dish and add bread to top of pineapple mixture.
Bake in 350° oven for 45 minutes or until brown and the mixture is set.

title: tamale bean casserole
directions: Drain olives and corn.
Add all other ingredients as is.
Put all ingredients in baking pan and mix well.
Bake at 300° for 1 hour.

title: peach cobbler cake
directions: Place peaches in well-buttered 10 x 6 x 2-inch baking dish. Drizzle honey over peaches.
Blend cake mix and buttermilk until smooth; pour over peaches.
Bake at 400° for 20 to 25 minutes (top will crack).
Serve warm with butter pecan ice cream.

title: gelatin ribbon loaf
directions: Place lime and raspberry jello in separate bowls.
Add 3/4 cup applesauce to each one.
Stir until well blended.

title: deviled eggs
directions: Cut peeled eggs lengthwise into halves.
Slip out yolks into a bowl.
Mash with a fork.
Mix in salt, mustard, pepper and mayonnaise.
Fill the egg whites with the yolk mixture, heaping slightly.
If desired, sprinkle paprika over top of each egg. Arrange eggs on a large serving plate.
Cover and refrigerate no longer than 24 hours.
Makes 6 servings.

title: beef and macaroni casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 425°.
Cook onion in melted butter in skillet. Brown meat. Add spices and tomatoes. Cook for 3 minutes.
Pour cooked macaroni into greased casserole dish.
Spoon meat mixture over the macaroni and add tomato sauce and cheese bits.
Mix well and sprinkle with grated cheese.
Bake 30 minutes.

title: chicken-ala-orange
directions: Pound chicken with kitchen mallet until flat.
Squeeze orange; pour juice into honey.
Set aside.

title: peanut clusters
directions: Melt chocolates. Pour in peanuts. Spoon on waxed paper.

title: oyster stew
directions: Simmer oysters, liquid and butter for 3 minutes, until edges curl.
Scald milk in a separate saucepan.
Add oysters and seasoning.
Heat, but do not boil.
Serves 2.

title: pepper relish
directions: Grind vegetables, add salt and let stand overnight.
Rinse vegetables.
Mix the rest of ingredients with vegetables.
Simmer 3 minutes.
Makes about 8 pints.

title: hamburg soup
directions: Brown ground beef and onion in Dutch oven.
Drain.
Dissolve bouillon cubes in hot water.
Add to ground beef and onion, along with remaining ingredients, except pasta.
Bring to a boil and boil for 1 minute.
Cover and simmer until potatoes are tender. Cook pasta according to directions on package.
Add to soup when potatoes are done.
Simmer a few minutes longer and then serve. Salt and pepper to taste.

title: brownies
directions: Mix all ingredients. Bake in a 9 x 13-inch pan at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: stuffed cabbage - small ones
directions: You will need toothpicks.

title: apple pie
directions: Combine apples, water, spices and butter in a sauce pan.
Bring to a boil, reduce heat and simmer 5 minutes.
Stir in gelatin, add pie filling mix and blend well.
Bring to a full boil.
Remove from heat and let stand 5 minutes.
Pour into pie shell.
Chill 4 hours before serving.

title: shrimp salad
directions: Clean and devein shrimp.
Bring 1/2 gallon of water, crab boil and 2 teaspoons of salt to boil.
Add shrimp and return to boil. Remove from heat.
Drain and ice down shrimp.
Drain shrimp again and chop coarsely.
Then add green pepper, celery, egg, parsley and mayonnaise.
Serve in tomato, avocado or lettuce cups.
Top with strips of pimiento.
Garnish with wedge of lemon.
Serves 4.

title: nancy's turkey salad
directions: Combine all ingredients and add enough Miracle Whip salad dressing to hold salad together.
Chill 4 to 6 hours.
Makes 6 servings.

title: spanish-style pork chops
directions: Trim excess fat from chops.
Melt margarine or butter in a 10-inch skillet.
Brown chops in hot margarine for 5 minutes.
Add water.
Cover and simmer for 20 minutes.
Snip tomatoes in can using kitchen scissors.
In a 2-quart casserole combine undrained tomatoes, uncooked rice mix, water, chopped green pepper and chopped onion.
Place browned chops on top of rice mixture.
Cover and bake in a 350° oven for 1 hour or until pork chops and rice are tender.
Let stand for 10 minutes before serving.

title: potato soup
directions: Stir-fry onion in butter in a heavy saucepan over moderate heat 5 minutes until limp; add potatoes, water, salt and celery salt.
Cover and simmer 10 to 15 minutes until potatoes are nearly tender.
Add milk, cream and pepper; simmer, uncovered, stirring occasionally 3 to 5 minutes until potatoes are done.
Sprinkle with parsley and serve.

title: english toffee
directions: Prepare nuts, 3 cups chopped coarse and 1 cup chopped fine. Save the finely chopped nuts for the topping.

title: bean salad
directions: Drain juice from all beans; rinse and drain.
Chop onion and bell pepper, or slice onion if you like.
Mix with beans.
Mix oil, sugar and vinegar and stir until sugar dissolves.
Pour over bean mixture and put in covered dish to marinate for 8 hours or more, stirring occasionally.

title: pot roast
directions: Place meat, vegetables, salt and pepper in crock pot with 1/4 to 1/2 cup of water, and cook on high for at least 4 to 6 hrs. or until tender. (Add 1 Tbsp. of Teriyaki sauce while cooking.)

title: cheese ball
directions: Chop fine onion greens.
Chop corned beef fine.
Mix all ingredients together and form a ball.
Serve on crackers or celery sticks.

title: chili sauce
directions: Cook the first 3 ingredients, then put through strainer.
Add the remaining ingredients.
Boil for about 1 hour, or until it starts to thicken.
Put into jars and seal.

title: jim's micro meat loaf
directions: Spray loaf microwave dish with nonfat cooking spray.
In medium bowl, combine all ingredients, except catsup; mix well. Bread crumbs and liquid may be adjusted as liquid in meats vary. Shape into loaf and place in sprayed dish.
Cover completely with plastic wrap.
Cook at Medium-high for 14 to 16 minutes. (Note: This recipe is for a microwave that is 700 watts on High. You may have to adjust your oven.)

title: overnight chicken casserole
directions: In a large bowl combine all ingredients together.
Put in a large casserole dish and refrigerate overnight.
Remove from refrigerator and mix well.
Top with bread crumbs, chips or Chinese noodles.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: kale soup(portuguese)
directions: Place potatoes, 1 carrot and olive oil in water. Cook over medium flame until potatoes are soft. Blend cooked carrot and potatoes. Add about 1/4 of the kidney beans. Add salt.
Bring the flame down. Add greens, sliced carrots and pasta.
Cook about 10 to 15 minutes until pasta and vegetables are tender.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Pour cranberries into the boiling water and boil approximately 15 minutes.
If all berries have not popped, mash them.
Remove from heat and while hot, add the jello, sugar and orange (rind and meat).
Let cool.
Add celery, pineapple and nuts.

title: butterscotch balls
directions: Combine the first 6 ingredients.
Add margarine.
Shape into balls.
Melt butterscotch chips and paraffin.
Dip balls into butterscotch mixture; drop onto waxed paper.
Yields 36 to 50 pieces.

title: italian cookies
directions: Cream butter.
Add sugar, flour, nuts and vanilla.
Roll a ball of dough the size of a walnut and flatten lightly.
Bake 10 to 12 minutes in 325° oven.
Roll cookies in powdered sugar while hot.

title: chocolate chip muffins
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Sift sugar, baking powder, salt and flour together.
Stir in the butter, egg and milk until blended. Fold in chocolate chips.
Fill muffin tins.
Bake for 20 minutes.

title: fried macaroni
directions: Boil macaroni, drain and cool.
Melt margarine in frying pan on low heat.
Add cooked macaroni and beaten eggs.
Cook until eggs are done.

title: little orange loaves
directions: Prepare batter from muffin mix according to package directions.
Stir in cranberry sauce and nuts.
Spoon into 6 greased (6 oz.) frozen juice concentrate cans.
Bake in moderate 375° oven for 30 to 35 minutes or until done.
Cool 5 minutes. Ease out of cans with spatula (cut end out of can).
Bread slices best second day.

title: lemon angel food cake topping
directions: Boil the first 3 ingredients until thick.
Beat the egg yolks; add the lemon juice.
Mix well.
Add this to the first mixture. Cool completely.
Fold in the whipped cream.

title: meat loaf
directions: Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: amish sugar cookies
directions: Mix all ingredients and form into balls, walnut size.
Flatten with bottom of glass dipped in sugar.
Bake in ungreased pan at 325° for 10 to 15 minutes.
This is a light cookie, watch so they don't burn.

title: carrot cake(yield 1 cake)
directions: Mix oil, sugar and eggs.
Add salt, soda and flour.
Mix well. Add cinnamon and vanilla.
Add nuts, pineapple and carrots. Blend well.
Bake at 350° in greased and floured 9 x 12-inch pan for 50 to 60 minutes.
It must feel done by touch.
Frost with Cream Cheese Frosting.

title: chicken and broccoli(with mushroom sauce)
directions: Cook broccoli according to package directions.
Mix margarine and flour together in pan.
Blend in chicken broth, stirring until thick and smooth.
Stir in mushrooms and their liquid.
Season to taste.
Place broccoli pieces in shallow baking pan.
Cover with chicken chunks and pour mushroom sauce over all.
Top with parsley and bread crumbs.
Bake at 375°, uncovered, 15 to 25 minutes, or until bubbly and brown on top.
This recipe may be made with asparagus.
Makes 4 servings.

title: cocktail meatballs
directions: Saute
bite size meatballs in butter (allow for shrinkage). Combine
jelly
and
ketchup
and
pour over meatballs. Simmer 30 to 40 minutes.
Serve with toothpicks.

title: chicken salad
directions: In large bowl, stir together mayonnaise, lemon juice, salt and pepper until smooth.
Add remaining ingredients.
Toss till well coated.
Cover and chill.
Makes 5 cups.

title: melinda's chili
directions: Cook meat. Drain. Add seasoning.
Cook until mixed good. Then put all other ingredients in crock pot. Add meat and let cook on low until ready to serve.

title: chicken and rice casserole
directions: Saut the celery and onion in the butter until soft, about 8 to 10 minutes over low heat. Remove from heat; stir in the broth and the instant soup mix. Mix in the chicken, rice and 1 1/2 c. cheese. Pour into a 9 x 13 dish. Sprinkle the remaining cheese on top. Bake at 375° for 30 minutes.

title: creamy chicken soup
directions: In stock pot, dissolve bouillon cubes in boiling water.
Stir in carrots, onions and celery.
Add chicken breasts.
Bring to a boil.
Simmer 20 minutes, covered, until rice is cooked.

title: cream of anything soup
directions: Make a roux of butter and flour, add milk and make a thick white sauce.
If cheese is wanted, add it here and whisk to melt. Mix in meat or vegetables and stir until smooth.
Add broth and season to taste.
I make broccoli soup out of this or cauliflower soup.

title: mother goose popcorn
directions: While popcorn is popping, combine coloring, sugar, water and margarine in a saucepan. Bring to a boil for 2 minutes.
Take off stove and add extract. Pour over popcorn. Mix well and serve.

title: easy overnight coffeecake
directions: Combine pudding mix, brown sugar and pecans.
Generously grease one-piece angel cake pan with additional butter.
Separate frozen balls of dough and place them in the pan.
Pour the 1/2 cup melted butter over dough.
Sprinkle with pudding mixture.
Cover and set aside to rise overnight.
In the morning, preheat oven to 350°. Bake for 35 to 45 minutes.
Invert onto serving plate.
Serve warm, pulling dough apart to serve.
Yield 10 to 12 servings.

title: stewed tomatoes
directions: Cook all ingredients on low heat until a syrup forms.
Stir often so it won't stick.
Serve as a side dish with black-eyed peas, crowder peas, butter beans, etc.

title: 5 cup dessert
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Cover and chill for 24 hours.

title: quick cheese enchiladas
directions: Combine ricotta, three-quarters cup of grated Monterey Jack, onions, cumin, salt and eggs in a medium bowl.
Beat well to blend evenly.
Divide the mixture among the tortillas and roll the tortillas so both ends are open and the filling is enclosed.
If you use salsa, pour a little into a large, shallow, well-greased casserole.
Tip the casserole to coat all over the sauce.
Place rolled tortillas in casserole.
Sprinkle remaining cheese over the tortillas, then sprinkle with olives.
Pour one-half to 1 cup salsa over all, if desired.
Bake 20 minutes at 400°.

title: tennessee blackberry cobbler
directions: In an 8
x
1 1/2-inch baking dish, place blackberries. In small bowl,
combine sugar and flour.
Sprinkle over blackberries. Dot with butter.
Set aside.

title: baked pita chips
directions: Split pita bread rounds in half horizontally.
Lightly spray the cut side of each pita bread half with nonstick coating. Sprinkle lightly with onion or garlic powder or pepper.
Cut each half into 6 wedges.
Spread wedges in a single layer on a baking sheet.
(You'll need to bake chips in batches.)
Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes or until crisp.
Serve with salsa.

title: microwave roasted potatoes
directions: Peel,
wash
and
quarter potatoes.
Place in two quart casserole dish, with 1/2 cup water.
Cover with lid; microwave on High for 9 minutes.
Gently stir potatoes.	Microwave for 9 more minutes.
Drain water.
Melt butter over potatoes.	Salt and pepper.

title: best broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli pieces for about half of the time indicated on the package directions; drain.
Combine the soup, onion, lemon juice and mayonnaise; mix well.
In a casserole dish layer the broccoli, soup mixture and grated cheese; repeat layers.
Combine the melted margarine with the stuffing mix.
Sprinkle this over the casserole.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes, covered.
Uncover and bake for an additional 10 minutes.

title: pineapple cookies
directions: Cream margarine and sugar; beat in egg.
Stir in pineapple. Combine flour and baking powder and add to	pineapple mixture. Stir in chopped nuts.
Bake on cookie sheet for 10 to 12 minutes in 375° oven.

title: five cup salad
directions: You will need 5 cleaned and emptied glass salad dressing bottles (select unusual shapes).

title: frozen margarita
directions: In a 4-quart container, combine first 6 ingredients.
Freeze.

title: marion's oven curry stew
directions: Mix all ingredients except mushrooms together in a large casserole.
Cover and bake in 300° oven for 4 to 5 hours.

title: butterscotch pudding
directions: Boil the first 6 ingredients until thickened.
Add flour, sugar, 3 cups boiling water and eggs.
Mix together and bring to boil again.
Cool, then mix with nuts, banana and marshmallows.

title: fruit salad
directions: Cook pudding as stated on package, except use apple juice in place of milk.
Refrigerate until slightly cool, but not quite set.
Add fruit cocktail, pineapple chunks, bananas and grapes. Refrigerate until set.
Serve with lite Cool Whip as topping.

title: tuna mediterranean
directions: Cook macaroni and add to other ingredients mix well.
Mix in sour cream sprinkle with a little American cheese and oregano. Bake at 325° oven for 30 minutes.

title: raisin-spice cake
directions: Combine buttermilk and soda.
To the 2 cups sugar add the melted shortening, spice and vanilla.
Alternately add the combined milk, soda and flour to the sugar mixture.
Mix well after each addition.
Add raisins and nuts.
Bake at 350° until well browned, about 30 minutes.
Test with a toothpick.
Bake in a 9 x 13-inch greased pan.
Serve with whipped cream, if desired.

title: low-fat veggie pizzas
directions: Coat skillet with cooking spray.
Add onion and garlic; saute 1 minute and add mushrooms and carrot.
Saute 2 minutes; add cilantro.
Place tortillas on baking sheet; broil 1 minute.
Turn; broil another minute.
Top with beans, mushroom mixture and cheese.
Broil until cheese melts.

title: parmesan breaded chicken
directions: Combine first 5 ingredients in a shallow bowl.
Dip chicken in buttermilk and roll in bread crumbs-herb mixture.
Coat a baking pan with cooking spray.
Place chicken (bone side down) on pan. Bake, covered, at 350° for 25 minutes.
Remove cover and bake another 20 minutes or until done.

title: rice pudding
directions: Boil rice and water until water is absorbed.
Add cornstarch. Add milk and sugar; simmer until reduced to proper consistency. Add vanilla.

title: banana wafer pudding
directions: Heat milk and sugar (do not boil).
Whip eggs; add flour and whip until smooth.
Add a little hot milk, if needed.
Remove milk mixture from heat, pour in egg mixture, cook until smooth custard. Remove from heat, cool and add vanilla.
In a large bowl, alternate layers of wafers, bananas and custard.

title: olaf
directions: Cream shortening and sugar until light and fluffy.
Beat in water, yolks and lemon peel.
Work in salt and flour with hands to form smooth dough.
Wrap in wax paper.
Chill.

title: pork fried rice
directions: Beat egg well and scramble in large hot greased skillet or wok.
Break egg into pieces.
Add pork/ham and rice.
Stir-fry 5 minutes.
Add soy sauce and vegetables.
Stir-fry several minutes and serve hot.
Makes approximately 4 to 6 servings.

title: special dessert
directions: Cook first four ingredients in double boiler until thick.
Add drained oranges and pineapple.
Serve over cake and top with Cool Whip.

title: salami(beef, deer, bear, elk, moose)
directions: Mix well and refrigerate.
Knead well next 2 days.
Knead third day and form into 2-inch rolls.
Place on broiler rack and bake at 140° for 8 hours.
Turn every 2 hours.
It can be smoked for 8 hours at 140° in a smokehouse (omit liquid smoke).

title: fruit pie
directions: Swimming in the swimming hole in the South Fork River before it was all flooded by the dam.

title: apple crisp
directions: Place sliced apples in a 6 x 10-inch baking dish.
Combine remaining ingredients until crumbly with fork.
Pour entire mixture over top of apples, then sprinkle with nutmeg and cinnamon.
Bake 30 to 40 minutes at 350°.
Serve with cream and sugar or ice cream.

title: pizza meatloaf
directions: Lightly grease 9 inch pie plate.
Put turkey in pie plate. Pat down.
Place turkey in 350 degree oven.
Bake until turkey no longer remains pink, about 17 - 20 minutes. Drain liquid.

title: nutty fingers
directions: Cream the margarine and sugar; add flour, vanilla and nuts and blend well.
If necessary sprinkle it with cold water to get it workable.
Use 1 teaspoon of mixture to roll out in hand the finger-shaped confection.
Bake at 325° for 25 minutes.
Turn to broil for last few minutes to give crispness.
Cool, then roll in sugar.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Coat chicken with salt, pepper and flour mixture.
In a Dutch Oven or large deep pan put enough oil to brown the chicken. Remove chicken and drain oil from pan.
Put rice, mushroom soup, water, and salt and pepper, if desired, in the same pan.
Arrange chicken on top of rice mixture-cover and bake in 350° oven for about 1 hour or until rice is tender.

title: fresh apple cake
directions: Cream oil, eggs and sugar together.
Add sifted dry ingredients and vanilla.
Then add chopped apples and nuts.
Stir by hand.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Bake in Bundt pan.

title: barbecued pork sandwiches
directions: In a Dutch oven, combine meat, onion, chili powder, salt, water, catsup and vinegar.
Cover and simmer 4 hours or until the meat falls apart easily.
Skim off the excess fat.
With a slotted spoon, remove meat, reserving cooking liquid.
Shred the meat with two forks or a pastry blender.
Return to the cooking liquid and heat through.
Serve on hamburger rolls.
Makes 16 servings.

title: husband's delight
directions: Brown hamburger; drain, then add salt, pepper, sugar and tomato sauce. Let simmer for 15 minutes. Cream together the cream cheese and sour cream. Place in a baking dish. Place layer of egg noodles, then a layer of the cream cheese, sour cream mixture. Repeat and top with Cheddar cheese. Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: hearty black~eyed peas
directions: Bring first 6 ingredients and if desired jalapeno peppers to a boil and in a large pan. Cover. Reduce heat, and simmer for 1 hour or until peas are tender.

title: autumn soup
directions: Brown ground meat; drain and add onion.
Add 4 cups water, salt, carrots, potatoes and celery.
Cook 20 minutes.
Add tomatoes.
Cook 10 minutes.

title: cheese spread (ball)
directions: Mix all above until smooth. Form into a ball, roll ball in crushed walnuts if desired.
place in bowl.
Chill and serve with crackers.

title: chocolate pound cake
directions: Cream together the butter and shortening.
Add sugar and mix well.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating after each addition.
Add vanilla.

title: slow cooker chili
directions: In a large skillet, cook beef over medium heat until brown. Drain.
Transfer to a 5 quart slow cooker. Stir in the remaining ingredients.
Cover and cook on low for 6 hours.

title: carrot cake
directions: Prepare carrots and nuts.
Cream together the oil, sugar and eggs.
Combine flour, soda, cinnamon and salt, sift into the egg and sugar mixture.
Blend together well. Fold in carrots and nuts. Bake in a 9 x 13 greased pan at 300° for 1 hour.
Cool and frost.

title: spice bars
directions: Mix at medium speed until smooth.
Bake in 9 x 13-inch pan (greased).
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: jello salad
directions: Stir jello and water to dissolve.
Let set until it starts to thicken.
Add marshmallows.
Whip the whipping cream.
When whipped, add the cream cheese.
Fold in the celery, nutmeats and pineapple.
Add this mixture to the jello.
Pour into a salad ring.
Put into the refrigerator to set.

title: fudge brownies
directions: Heat the oven to 350°.
Grease the bottom only of a square pan, 8 x 8 x 2-inches, with shortening.

title: delicious cake(1 egg)
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease and flour 8 x 8 x 2-inch cake pan. Sift first 3 ingredients 3 times.
Work shortening until smooth and creamy.
Add sugar slowly; continue to work until light.
Add eggs and beat well.
Add flour mixture alternately with combined milk and vanilla in thirds, beating with spoon after each addition.
Turn into cake pan and bake in 350° oven for 30 to 40 minutes or until done.

title: vanilla wafer cake
directions: Crush vanilla wafers.
Add eggs, sugar, coconut, baking powder, margarine (melted), vanilla and nuts.
Mix well by hand.
Pour in well-greased tube pan lined with wax paper and bake 1 hour at 325°. Begin in cold oven.
Let cool in pan.
For Christmas Fruit Cake, add fruit cake mix.

title: boiled oatmeal cookies
directions: Put sugar, milk, butter and cocoa into pan.
Bring to a boil and let boil for 1 minute.
Remove from heat; add vanilla, peanut butter and oats.
Stir and drop by teaspoonfuls onto waxed paper.

title: raw apple cake
directions: Blend sugar and eggs.
Add flour, soda, salt and cinnamon. Beat in oil and vanilla.
Fold in apples and pecans.
Pour into greased and floured 13 x 9-inch pan.
Bake at 325° for approximately 1 hour.
Cool in pan 10 minutes and turn out.

title: sausage balls
directions: Mix all of the ingredients and make round balls 1 1/2 to 2 inches.
Bake on cookie sheet with foil on the cookie sheet.
Bake for about 20 minutes at 350°.

title: miracle whip cake
directions: Mix flour, cocoa powder, baking soda and salt together.
Add sugar and Miracle Whip.
Stir until it forms a paste, then add cold water and vanilla.
Pour into greased and floured 10 x 13-inch pan and bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: turkey meat loaf
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Combine all ingredients and press into a 9 x 5-inch loaf pan.
Bake 50 to 60 minutes.
Serves 6.

title: taco meat filling
directions: Brown beef and onion in skillet.
Drain excess fat.
Stir in remaining ingredients.
Simmer, covered, for 10 minutes.

title: crab dip
directions: Soften cream cheese and mix in all ingredients. Combine until well mixed.
Place into small ovenproof bowl or pan. Cook in 400° oven until light brown and bubbly, about 10 minutes. Serve with party rye bread.

title: chocolate slush
directions: First Step:
Blend flour, margarine and 1/2 cup pecans. Spread in bottom of baking pan. Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.

title: garbanzo stew and dumplings
directions: To make stew:
Simmer onion in margarine in pan.
Sprinkle flour over it and blend.
Add garbanzos and juice.

title: syrniki (cottage cheese balls)
directions: Combine all ingredients, except flour. Knead until stiff dough forms. Shape into small balls and roll in flour. Fry in oil for 3 to 4 minutes until golden brown.

title: ice cream
directions: Freeze with electric freezer.
Makes around 1 gallon.

title: pine mountain pesto(serves 7 to 8)
directions: You will need cheesecloth.

title: igloos
directions: Mix margarine (room temperature) and sugar.
Add pineapple, dates and nuts; mix well.
Let stand overnight.
Make into balls; place between butter cookies.
Frost with Cool Whip; add cherry on top.
Makes 21 Igloos.

title: baked pork chops
directions: Brown pork chops in a small amount of oil.
Pat dry with paper towels.
Place in a covered casserole dish.
Mix together the onion soup, cream of mushroom soup and water.
Pour mixture over pork chops.
Cover and bake 45 minutes to 1 hour at 350° until tender.

title: pork steak italiano
directions: In a skillet salt and pepper and brown the pork steaks on both sides.
Mix together the 1/2 teaspoon basil, onion salt and Ricotta cheese.
Spoon into a 12 x 9 x 2-inch greased baking dish. Place the browned pork steaks on top.
Mix together the tomato sauce, Italian seasoning, 1/4 teaspoon basil and water.
Spoon 2/3 of sauce mixture over pork steaks.
Cover and bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Top each steak with green pepper slices, some cheese and the rest of the sauce.
Cover and bake another 30 minutes. Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese before serving, if desired.

title: chocolate oatmeal cookies
directions: Cream shortening and sugar.
Add beaten egg, melted chocolate and vanilla.
Add oatmeal, sifted flour and baking powder.
Drop by teaspoons on greased cookie sheet and bake at 350°.
Makes 3 dozen.

title: chocolate pie
directions: Beat egg whites stiff with sugar and cream of tartar.
Bake in oven until brown at 350°.

title: apple muffins
directions: Mix the first 3 ingredients in a bowl.
In another bowl, mix the sour milk or buttermilk, baking soda, vanilla and salt. Combine these two mixtures alternately with the flour, mixing well after each addition.
Fold in the apples and pecans.
Pour into muffin pan (papers) and sprinkle melted butter on top. Bake at 325° for 30 minutes or until cake tester comes out clean.
Yields about 15 muffins.

title: corn and macaroni casserole
directions: Put both cans of corn in a casserole dish; fill one can with dry macaroni and add the 1/2 stick of butter.
Place chunks of Velveeta cheese in with the ingredients.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.
Stir occasionally to mix the cheese throughout. Makes a great dish for kids.

title: chicken paprika
directions: Flour chicken and brown in oil.
Remove to Dutch oven.
Brown the onions lightly, until golden.
Add to chicken.
Cover with remaining ingredients.
Simmer.
Stir occasionally until tender, about 45 minutes.
Serve with hot rice and broccoli.
Can be made the day before and heated in a moderate oven.

title: tuscon lemon cake
directions: Grease and flour
Bundt
pan
or
10 x 4-inch tube pan. Beat sugar and margarine in large bowl until light and fluffy. Beat in eggs 1
at
a
time.
Mix flour, baking soda and salt; beat into sugar mixture alternately with buttermilk until well blended. Stir
in
poppy
seed,
lemon
peel and lemon juice. Spread in pan.
Bake at 325° for 50 to 55 minutes.
Immediately poke holes in
top
of cake; pour about 2/3 of Lemon Glaze over
top.
Cool 20
minutes.
Invert
on
heatproof
serving plate.
Remove
from pan
and
spread
with
remaining glaze. Makes 16 servings.

title: hot dog chili
directions: Cook hamburger.
Place in crock-pot with all ingredients. Cook on low all day.

title: chicken divan
directions: Cook broccoli.
Prepare sauce by combining soup, mayo and cheese, beating until cheese is melted.
Place broccoli in bottom of ungreased casserole dish.
Place sliced chicken over broccoli. Pour sauce over all and sprinkle on lemon juice.
Combine crumbs and butter and sprinkle top of casserole with bread crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes until bubbly.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: easy scalloped potatoes
directions: Dilute milk with equal amount of water.
Slice potatoes.
Pour milk in bottom of greased baking dish.
Layer all ingredients and sprinkle each layer with flour.
Pour remaining milk over all until barely covered.
Cook by microwave on Medium or at 350° until tender.

title: wet coconut cake
directions: While cake is still hot, punch holes in it and pour mixture of milk and cream of coconut over top.
Top with Cool Whip. Decorate with cherries, nuts or chocolate chips.

title: orange-pineapple summer delight
directions: Mix all ingredients and refrigerate.

title: broiler icing
directions: Mix together well.
Spread on baked cake and place under broiler for 3 to 5 minutes.
Watch closely.

title: date pudding(christmas dessert)
directions: Mix dates, nuts and dry ingredients.
Add egg and mix.
Pour into oiled baking dish or pan. Bake in moderate oven at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes or until firm.
Serve hot or cold with plain or whipped topping. Serves 6 to 8 people.
Very rich dessert.

title: chocolate zucchini cake
directions: Beat eggs.
Stir in sugar, oil, vanilla, zucchini, almond extract and melted chocolate. Spoon in dry ingredients, nuts and dates.
Bake in a tube pan at 325° for about 1 hour or until done.

title: sweet potato praline pie
directions: Melt butter in a large, heavy saucepan. Add pecans and cook over low heat, stirring constantly, until butter is golden brown and pecans are toasted.
Remove from heat; stir in next 7 ingredients, mixing well.
Pour mixture into pastry shell. Bake at 425° for 10 minutes. Reduce temperature to 325° and bake an additional 45 minutes or until set. Cool on wire rack. Top with whipped cream.

title: beet salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Chill before serving.

title: santa's thumbprints
directions: Mix ingredients.
Roll into 1-inch balls, then roll into crushed nuts.
Place on cookie sheet, press thumb in middle of cookie and fill with jelly.
Bake at 350°.

title: chicken lynn
directions: Boil chicken until tender, seasoning to taste with salt and pepper.
Remove from broth; cut in bite size pieces and line bottom of casserole dish.
Mix the cream of chicken soup and the sour cream and pour over the chicken. Spread the crushed crackers on top.
Dribble the melted butter on the crackers.
Sprinkle the poppy seed over the top of the casserole.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: chicken and rice
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Mix 1 1/3 cups stuffing mix, peas, almonds, chicken, milk and soup in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Mix hot water with 2 tablespoons margarine and spread over all.
Shake 2/3 cup stuffing mix on top.
Bake for 25 minutes.

title: salty kosher dill pickles
directions: Pack cucumbers in quart jar with garlic clove, onions, dill stems or dill head and hot peppers, pods or sliced.
Add a pinch of alum to each jar.
Boil white vinegar and water, salt and sugar; pour boiling mixture over cucumbers and seal.
Pickles may be eaten in 2 weeks.

title: baked ziti
directions: Mix Ricotta, 1/2 of Mozzarella and ziti.
Grease 9 x 13-inch pan.
Pour 1 1/2 cups spaghetti sauce into it.
Put in noodle mixture.
Cover with rest of sauce.
Sprinkle on some Parmesan cheese.
Put in rest of Mozzarella cheese.
Bake 20 to 30 minutes at 350° or until brown.

title: swiss vegetable medley
directions: Reserve 1/2 cup of cheese and 1/2 cup onion rings.
Combine all other ingredients.
Bake in a Corning Ware dish at 350° for 30 minutes.
Top with reserved cheese and onion rings.
Bake 5 minutes more.

title: ham and cheese rolls
directions: Melt and stir margarine, mustard, poppy seed and garlic powder.
Slice rolls in half (like a bun).
Spoon mixture on both halves of bread.
Add one layer of cheese and 1 to 2 layers of ham.
Add onion, if desired.
Put top of bread back on and bake at 300° for 10 minutes.

title: pecan chocolate fudge deluxe
directions: Into a heavy, wide-mouthed saucepan, put 2 cups of granulated sugar, 1 cup of evaporated milk, a pinch of salt, butter the size of a walnut, 2 squares of bitter chocolate and a generous teaspoon of cocoa.
Cook over low heat until the sugar melts, then over a medium flame until the mixture thickens and heavily clings to the spoon.
(It must be really thick!)
Remove from heat; stir in a teaspoon of vanilla and let stand a few minutes.
Beat until the gloss is gone from the candy; stir in a cup or more of pecans, whole or broken.
Pour into a buttered pan; cut into squares when possible, with a knife dipped in hot water after each cutting.

title: whole wheat banana bread
directions: Combine first ingredients in a small bowl; stir well and set aside.
Combine sugar and oil in a medium mixing bowl; beat at medium speed of an electric mixer 2 minutes or until well blended. Add eggs; beat until light and lemon colored.
With mixer running at low speed, add flour mixture alternately with bananas, beginning and ending with flour mixture.
Blend well after each addition.
Pour batter into a 8 x 4 x 2-inch loaf pan coated with cooking spray; bake at 350° for 45 minutes or until a wooden pick, inserted in center comes out clean.
Cool 15 minutes in pan. Remove and let cool completely on wire rack.

title: lemon cake
directions: Mix cake mix, apricot nectar, sugar, oil and eggs until smooth. Bake at 325° until done.
After cake is taken out of oven and while still warm, pour mixture of lemon juice and confectioners sugar over cake (warm until confectioners sugar is melted).

title: gale's scotch shortbread
directions: Thoroughly mix butter and sugar.
Stir in 2 1/2 c. sifted flour.
Mix well with hands.
Knead for 5 minutes.
Spread evenly on a cookie sheet.
Prick with a fork.
Bake at 300 degrees for about 20 minutes or until light golden brown.
Cut warm, but leave in pan until cool.
Age for best flavor.

title: roast and gravy
directions: Cook roast in water on medium-high heat for 1 1/2 hours, adding water as needed.
Cook water out and add oil; brown on both sides.
Add flour; brown.
Add water over roast to make gravy, enough for desired thickness.

title: baked beans
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Pour into ovensafe pan.
Bake uncovered 40 minutes at 350°.

title: cherry pecan fruit cake
directions: Mix dry ingredients.
Stir in fruit.
Then add eggs, then pecans.
Bake in greased tube pan with wax paper in bottom of pan. Bake in 250° oven for 2 hours.

title: lasagna
directions: Brown meat with onions; add spices, tomato sauce and paste plus 1 cup water.
Simmer.
Cook noodles; drain and run cold water over them.

title: oriental stir-fry
directions: Saute celery and onion in 2 tablespoons margarine for 4 minutes on medium heat.
Add remaining ingredients and saute for 5 more minutes.
Serve over cooked rice (white or brown).

title: warm potato salad
directions: Cook potatoes in water to cover; drain.
Peel and cut into 1-inch cubes (or I leave peelings on, cut and steam potatoes). Combine with onions and dressing in bowl.
Sprinkle with paprika and chives.
Serve warm or at room temperature.

title: frankie baker's green enchiladas
directions: Fry tortillas in oil until limp.
Saute onion and layer ingredients into a greased casserole.
End with cheese on top. Bake 30 to 45 minutes at 350°.
This freezes well.

title: my mother's eggplant dressing
directions: Saute meat, onion, garlic and celery until light brown.
Peel eggplant; boil in salted water and drain.
Combine meat mixture, rice and eggplant.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Place in baking dish and bake in hot oven for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: frozen bananas
directions: Mix peanuts, wheat germ and sugar in a large mixing bowl. Insert 12 popsicle sticks into banana halves.
Roll bananas in nut mixture until thoroughly coated.
Place on cookie tray and freeze for at least 1 hour.
Serves 12.

title: walnut cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar; mix dry ingredients and alternate with milk (start with dry ingredients and finish with dry).
Add nuts to flour and fold in.
Bake for approximately 1 hour at 350°.

title: hot beef dip
directions: Saute onions in margarine.
Add milk and cream cheese.
Stir over low heat until cream cheese is melted.
Add remaining ingredients.
Heat thoroughly, stirring occasionally.
Serve hot with French bread slices or with French, whole wheat or rye bread cubes.

title: cherry torte
directions: Mix the
Eagle	Brand and lemon juice until thick.
Add the vanilla;
pour
into pie crust.
Top with cherry pie filling.

title: creamed spinach
directions: Cook chopped spinach as package directs for 45 minutes. Drain.
Set aside.
Saute onion in butter until tender.
Add flour and stir.
Add to cooked spinach.
Stir in crisp crumbled bacon. Season with dashes of nutmeg.
Pour into buttered casserole.
Bake in oven at 350° until heated through and bubbly.

title: potato soup
directions: Peel and dice potatoes and onion.
Boil in 5-quart pot with enough water to cover by an inch.
Season water with salt, pepper and garlic powder.
Once potatoes are well done and water has been reduced, add milk slowly.
Add cheese if desired and stir well.

title: peach salad
directions: Drain peaches and cut into bite size pieces.
Add cottage cheese, gelatin and Cool Whip.
Mix together well, refrigerate before serving.

title: sweet-sour pork
directions: Trim off excess fat.
Remove bones to make 1 1/2 pounds lean pork.
Cut	lean
meat
into 1/2-inch slices.
Cut slices into strips 2-inches long.
Sprinkle with salt.	Brown in oleo in skillet.
Add
water.
Cover; simmer 1 hour.
Drain pineapple. Combine
cup
pineapple juice and water.
Add brown sugar, ginger,
cornstarch,
vinegar and soy sauce.
Pour over meat. Cook
until
slightly thickened.
Cut green pepper into strips lengthwise.
Cut
the onion into thin crosswise slices. Add to meat.
Add pineapple chunks.
Bring to boil.
Cook for 5 minutes. Serve with rice.
Makes 4 servings.

title: shoo-fly cake
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients until crumbly; reserve 1/2 cup crumbs. Mix soda, molasses and 1 cup hot water.
Stir into remaining crumbs.
Spoon batter into layer cake pan.
Sprinkle with reserved crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.
Serve warm or cold.

title: chicken dressing
directions: Mix stuffing as directed. Place chicken in bottom of baking dish. Add soup (do not add water). Spoon dressing on top. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes, or until bubbly.

title: top of the line cole slaw
directions: Chop cabbage fine.
Chop carrots coarse.
Mix together.
Add salt, pepper and sugar; mix well.
Add purple cabbage and mix. Add mayonnaise.
Chill and serve.

title: unbaked chocolate balls
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Roll into buckeye size balls; insert a toothpick in each.
Chill in refrigerator.

title: coconut macaroons
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Lightly grease 2 cookie sheets.
In small bowl, with mixer at high speed, beat egg whites until soft peaks form.
Beating at high speed, gradually beat in sugar, 2 tablespoons at a time, beating well after each addition until sugar is completely dissolved.
Beat in vanilla and salt.
(Whites should stand in stiff, glossy peaks.)
With rubber spatula, gently fold coconut and flour into egg white mixture.

title: baked lima beans
directions: Day before, cover beans with water; refrigerate overnight. Next day, drain beans; put in large saucepan.
Cover with hot water.
Add 1 teaspoon salt.
Boil; reduce heat and simmer, covered, about 40 minutes or until beans are tender.
Drain. Reserve 6 slices of bacon for later.
Cut remaining bacon in 1/2-inch pieces; saute lightly.
Add onion.
Saute until onion is tender and bacon is browned.
In large bowl, combine beans, onion, bacon, tomato sauce, brown sugar, dry mustard, Worcestershire sauce, 1/2 teaspoon salt, oregano and 1/2 cup water.
Blend well. Turn into a 2 1/2 quart shallow baking dish.
Bake covered 30 minutes at 375°.
Remove cover and bake 15 minutes longer. Meanwhile, saute reserved bacon until crisp.
Drain.
Arrange over beans.

title: salad dressing for potato salad
directions: Mix the first 4 ingredients together.
Beat the eggs well. Add the water and vinegar.
Mix with dry ingredients and eggs; cook in double boiler until thick.
(Add equal amounts of Miracle Whip for salad.)

title: caramel icing
directions: Heat until all are melted together, then add powdered sugar to proper stiffness.

title: southern biscuits
directions: Sift dry ingredients into bowl.
Cut shortening in flour and mix with pastry blender.
(Will be coarse.)
Stir in milk and mix until dough leaves sides of bowl.
Pour out onto floured board and gently roll or pat to 1/4-inch thick or 1/2-inch for thicker biscuits.
Place on lightly greased cookie sheet, close for soft sides and 1-inch apart for crusty sides.
Bake 10 to 12 minutes at 450° or until desired brownness.

title: chocolate delight
directions: Cut flour and margarine together to resemble corn meal.
Add chopped nuts.
Pat in bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan.
Cook about 15 minutes at 350°.
Cool.

title: mexican corn bread
directions: In mixing bowl, combine dry ingredients.
Mix rest of ingredients; add to dry and stir just to mix.
Pour into 9-inch square pan or 16-inch skillet.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: really good hot beef
directions: Put roast in a 9 x 13-inch pan. Mix soups and water; pour over meat. Cover tight with foil and bake at 350° for 1 hour per pound. Pull with fork when done and serve on buns.

title: vinegar pie
directions: Mix all ingredients in a bowl.
Pour in pie shell and bake at 350° for 50 minutes.
Put cream or nuts on top.

title: quiche cajun(with crab and crawfish or shrimp)
directions: Sprinkle cheese evenly over bottom of pie shell.
Top with crabmeat and crawfish or shrimp, then green onions.
Mix beaten eggs, cream, salt and pepper.
Pour over mixture in pie shell.

title: cheese ball
directions: To soften cream cheese, place in microwave for 2 minutes on Power 5.
Blend it with the mayonnaise or Worcestershire sauce until it is smooth.
Add the rest of the ingredients and shape into balls.
Chill.

title: beef-vegetable soup
directions: Cover potatoes and carrots with water and cook over medium heat until tender (about 20 to 30 minutes).
Add all ingredients and cook on low heat for 30 minutes.
Great with corn bread!

title: stuffed crabs
directions: Saute onions, celery, garlic and bell pepper in margarine or oil until clear.
Add crabmeat, bouillon, salt, black pepper and cayenne.
Cook over medium heat about 15 minutes, stirring constantly.
Add green onions and parsley.
Cook 2 minutes and remove from heat.
Let cool.
Add eggs and Italian breadcrumbs and mix well.
Mixture should not be too moist or too dry.
Stuff crab shells with mixture.
(Use artificial or real crab shells.) Sprinkle top with Italian breadcrumbs and add pat of margarine. Bake in oven at 375° for 10 minutes or until brown.
Refrigerates and/or freezes well.

title: bacon wrapped chicken
directions: You will need toothpicks.

title: banana split dessert
directions: Stir and mix graham crackers and butter together and put in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Cream cream cheese and butter together; add egg and beat into creamed mixture.
Add powdered sugar.
Slice bananas lengthwise and put on top for layer.
Add pineapple, well drained and sprinkle on top of bananas.
Spread Cool Whip on top and refrigerate.

title: peanut butter balls
directions: Mix peanut butter, butter and 10x sugar.
Add 1 cup Rice Krispies and nuts.
Mix and roll into balls.
Let stand in refrigerator for 1/2 hour.
Melt chocolate chips.
Keep warm at all times.
Dip peanut butter balls in chocolate.
Place on pan to cool.
Store in refrigerator.

title: potato soup
directions: Peel potatoes and boil until just tender.
Drain and rinse with cold water.
In large pot, add soup and enough milk to mix soup, then add potatoes and add more milk to cover potatoes plus a little more.
Simmer on low-medium for 15 minutes.
Don't let it boil.
Add salt and pepper to taste.
Serve with shredded cheese on top and fried bacon, crumbled on top.

title: chocolite cloud cake
directions: Sift together flour, cocoa, sugar, baking soda, baking powder and salt.
Stir unti blended and add prunes, vanilla, Egg Beaters and milk.
Combine coffee and boiling water; stir until dissolved. Stir into batter until blended.
Bake in two 9-inch cake pans or 13 x 9-inch pan.
Bake 30 to 35 minutes at 350°.

title: applesauce-spice cake
directions: Combine all ingredients in large mixer bowl; blend well, then beat at medium speed of electric mixer for 4 minutes.
Pour into 2 greased and floured 8 x 4-inch loaf pans.
Bake at 350° for 50 to 55 minutes, or until cake tester inserted in center comes out clean and cake begins to pull away from sides of pan.
Do not underbake. Cool in pan 15 minutes.
Remove from pan; finish cooling on rack.

title: sensation salad dressing
directions: Shake well in quart jar.
Add salt and pepper to taste. Sprinkle with parsley.
Serve over lettuce or spinach.

title: pink salad
directions: In large mixing bowl mix jello and whipped topping well.
Add cottage cheese and drained pineapple.
Refrigerate until set.

title: lentil and applesauce soup
directions: Cover 1 pound of dried lentils with water 1 inch higher than lentils in large (4-quart or larger) pan.
Chop coarsely and add the carrots and celery.
Bring to a boil, then reduce heat, cover and simmer for about 1 1/2 hours or until lentils are soft.
During cooking, add 3 generous sprinkles of dried basil, beef bouillon cubes and onion and garlic powders to taste.
Stir to avoid sticking at bottom (4 or 5 times).
At end of cooking, add chunky applesauce to the soup and stir.
Taste.
If you want slightly darker, richer flavor, add Kitchen Bouquet.
Serve with French of Italian bread for lunch.
You have to try this to believe it!

title: banana cream pie
directions: Scald milk and cream.
Combine flour, cornstarch, sugar and salt.
Add to milk and cook until thickened, stirring constantly (up to 15 minutes).
Stir a small amount into beaten egg yolks. Add yolks to milk mixture.
Add vanilla.
Cook a few more minutes.
Slice banana onto bottom and sides of cooked pie shell. Pour in filling.
Cover with Saran Wrap and chill.

title: hamburger pie
directions: Brown hamburger; drain.
Combine hamburger, tomato paste, spaghetti sauce mix and 1/2 cup water.
Place crescent rolls in ungreased 9 x 13-inch pan and bake for 5 minutes at 350°.
Take out and layer hamburger mix and cheese 2 times.
Bake 15 minutes.

title: orange juice dessert
directions: Dilute orange juice with water.
Add marshmallows and heat until marshmallows dissolve.
Pour mixture into an 8 x 8-inch pan. Place in refrigerator to congeal.
Serve with whipped cream. Serves 9.

title: chicken noodle casserole
directions: Saute onions, celery, mushrooms, pepper and 1 stick margarine. Mix all other ingredients except 1/2 cup shredded cheese.
Mix well.
Pour into casserole dish and sprinkle with 1/2 cup shredded cheese evenly over mixture.
Bake at 350° for about 45 minutes.

title: hash brown potato casserole
directions: Place thawed potatoes in 9 x 13-inch baking dish; sprinkle lightly with salt and pepper. Mix together next 6 ingredients; pour over potatoes. Top with crushed cereal and drizzle melted oleo over all. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: marinade
directions: Blend ingredients together.
This is great on any type of meat.
Especially for the grill.

title: brown bread from boston
directions: Combine raisins and water in a small bowl; set aside to cool. Combine brown sugar, shortening, egg and molasses; beat well. Stir in salt, baking soda, flour and raisin mixture.
Stir in nuts.
Spoon into 4 greased 16 ounce cans.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until done.
Cool slightly before removing from cans. Yield: 4 small loaves.

title: hello dolly bars
directions: Melt margarine in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Add layer of crushed vanilla wafers.
Add layer of chips.
Add layer of coconut.
Add layer of walnuts or pecans.
Pour sweetened condensed milk evenly over other ingredients.
Bake 25 minutes at 350°.

title: meal in a skillet
directions: Brown ground beef in a large skillet.
Drain.
Add a layer of onions and potatoes, a layer of corn and layer of tomatoes.
Cover and let simmer 30 to 40 minutes.
Add grated cheese topping and let melt, if desired.

title: sweet potato biscuits
directions: Thoroughly mix together sugar, shortening and sweet potatoes. Sift together flour, baking powder and salt.
With pastry blender, cut sweet potato mixture into dry ingredients.
Turn out onto floured surface and knead lightly.
Roll dough out 1/2-inch thick, cut and place on cookie sheet.
Bake in 425° oven about 15 minutes until brown.

title: cocktail meatballs
directions: Mix first 7 ingredients well; roll into 1 inch balls and brown. Mix ketchup, A.1. sauce, margarine and brown sugar over heat. Add sour cream. Mix in to boil (cook well over low heat, about 15 minutes). Pour over meatballs and let marinate (works well in a crock-pot, low heat). Stir occasionally.

title: turkey in the straw
directions: Heat oil in skillet.
Add green pepper, onion and garlic; cook until tender.
Stir in seasonings and water; simmer 10 minutes. Add rice, turkey and ham; cover.
Cook over low heat for 25 minutes or until rice is tender, adding boiling water if needed. Add mushrooms with small amount of liquid; cook 5 minutes longer.

title: coconut-oatmeal cookies
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Drop on ungreased cookie sheet and bake 8 to 10 minutes in a preheated 350° oven.
Do not overbake cookies.

title: butterfinger dessert
directions: Mix 2/3 crumbs, margarine and crushed candy.
Press in 9 x 13-inch pan and chill.
Beat pudding and milk; add ice cream. Spread on cooled crust.
Top with whipped topping.
Sprinkle with remaining crumbs.
Chill.
I put in freezer.
Remove about 30 minutes before serving and keep in refrigerator.

title: vidalia onion casserole
directions: Saute onions in butter until transparent but not brown.
Add rice to boiling water and cook 5 minutes on low heat, covered. Place rice, onions and cheese in a 2-quart baking dish.
Combine well and stir in half and half. Bake 1 hour at 325°.

title: potato soup
directions: Saute onion in	butter.
To
cooked
potatoes,	add all ingredients except cheese and
heat.
Add
the cup of Velveeta cheese and 2 soup cans of milk.
Heat and serve.

title: rice pilaf
directions: Put boiling water, butter and dissolved cubes in baking dish. Add the rice.
Put in oven (covered); cook for 30 minutes at 350°. Stir.

title: egg custard pie
directions: Mix eggs, milk, sugar, salt and nutmeg well.
Pour into unbaked pie shell.
Cook until done at 325°.

title: pizza casserole
directions: Mix altogether in a large ovenproof bowl; bake covered with aluminum foil for 45 minutes and then uncovered for 15 minutes at 350°.

title: steak salad supreme
directions: Combine salad dressing, capers and mustard, stirring to blend. Add steak and toss with dressing until well coated.
Add tomatoes, onions and eggs; gently mix.
Cover and chill at least 2 hours or overnight.
Makes 4 servings.

title: coffee cake
directions: Beat egg whites stiff.
Add remaining ingredients.
Blend well.
Put in greased oblong pan.
Sprinkle brown sugar and cinnamon on top of batter.
Bake at 350° about 1/2 hour.
Add butter after taking out of oven.

title: strawberry shake
directions: Put the milk and juices into a blender.
Add banana pieces and strawberries one at a time.
Blend until the shake is smooth.

title: macaroni casserole
directions: Cook macaroni according to directions; drain.
Combine macaroni, soup, mushrooms, mayonnaise, cheese, onions, green pepper, pimento and salt; mix well.
Melt butter; stir in cracker crumbs.
Spread over top of macaroni mixture.
Bake at 375° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: cranberry punch
directions: Mix the ingredients together and heat in large pan, coffee maker or crock-pot.

title: sourdough biscuits
directions: Dissolve yeast in water; set aside.
Mix milk and oil; stir in yeast mixture.
Mix dry ingredients together; then add to liquid mixture.
May be rolled out immediately or let rise up to 2 hours. Place on a greased sheet.
Bake 15 to 20 minutes at 400°.

title: hot chicken salad
directions: Mix together and put into casserole dish.
Cover with Rice Krispies (crushed) and bake at 375° for 30 minutes.
Serves 10.

title: bean soup
directions: Brown meat, onion and pepper; drain.
Add beans, water and ketchup.
Heat until boiling.
Ready to serve.
Good with cornbread and green salad.

title: lime salad
directions: Combine jello and water and set aside.
Boil pineapple and sugar; add jello and water and set in refrigerator until it starts to jell.
Stir occasionally to keep pineapple from setting.
When set, add whipped cream and cheese.
Put in jello mold.
Serve.

title: low-fat vanilla pudding
directions: In a mixing bowl, combine all ingredients.
Beat on high speed for 2 minutes.
Spoon into serving dishes.
Chill.
Garnish with cherries or mint leaves, if desired.
Makes 6 servings.

title: yogurt cheese
directions: Line a colander with coffee filters or double thickness of cheesecloth.
Place colander on top of a bowl that is large enough to catch the whey liquid.
Pour in plain low-fat or nonfat yogurt. (Dannon is a good brand.
This won't work with brands that have modified food starch, vegetable gums or gelatin.)
Cover with plastic wrap and refrigerate overnight.
The next day, transfer yogurt cheese into covered container.
Refrigerate until ready to use.
Keeps one week.

title: blackberry jam cake
directions: Soak raisins for several hours in pineapple and juice.
Cream butter and sugar until fluffy.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating. Stir in jam.
Sift dry ingredients, add to creamed mixture.
Add buttermilk, add nuts, pour batter into 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan, wax paper lined.
Bake at 350° for 50 to 55 minutes.
Cool on rack. Dust with confectioners sugar.

title: barbecue beans
directions: Brown meat and onions lightly in small amount of oil.
Salt and pepper to taste; drain and mix with other ingredients.
Heat in oven 30 minutes at 350° or in crock-pot.

title: fried tenderloin
directions: Mix enough flour, salt and pepper to coat the tenderloin. Cook the meat slowly in a small amount of oil.
Turn frequently so as not to get crisp.
Cook until just barely done, being careful not to overcook.

title: cheese garlic biscuits
directions: Combine Bisquick, milk and cheese. With a wooden spoon, mix until soft dough forms.
Beat vigorously for 30 seconds.

title: boboli dip
directions: Mix cream cheese, sour cream and seasonings and spread in bottom of a 9 or 10-inch pie pan.
Spread 1/2 jar spaghetti sauce or 1 jar pizza sauce on top.
Spread pepperoni, green onions and green peppers over top of mixture.
Bake 10 to 15 minutes at 350° or until heated through.
Spread pizza cheese over top.
Bake until cheese melts.
Cut up Boboli crusts.
Brown 8 to 10 minutes on cookie sheet until crisp.

title: pumpkin chip muffins
directions: In a large mixing bowl, beat eggs, sugar, pumpkin and oil until smooth. Combine flour, baking soda, baking powder, cinnamon and salt; add to pumpkin mixture and mix well. Fold in chocolate chips. Fill greased or paper-lined muffin cups 3/4 full. Bake at 400° for 16 to 20 minutes or until muffins test done. Cool in pan 10 minutes before removing to a wire rack. Yield: about 24 standard-size muffins.

title: cream cheese pie
directions: Mix cream cheese and sugar until smooth.
Add vanilla.
Fold in whipped topping.
Beat until mixed.
Fold into graham cracker crust.
Top with cherries.

title: sweet potato pie
directions: Mix all ingredients and pour into the pie shell. Bake at 375° for 30 minutes. Delicious served with whipped cream.

title: christmas "bow" pasta
directions: Saute onion, broccoli, peppers and garlic in olive oil until tender.
Add tomatoes, wine and season.
Simmer 5 to 10 minutes. Add cream or milk and cheese.
Toss with bow tie pasta (1 to 1 1/2 pounds).
Decorate top with reserved broccoli and pepper.
Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese.

title: chocolate chip oatmeal cookies
directions: Place raisins in a little water and put in a microwave until soft.

title: easy caramel pecan rolls(makes 32)
directions: Combine pudding mix, pecans, sugar and cinnamon well.
Space half of bread unevenly on bottom of well-greased 9 x 13-inch pan. Pour 1/2 of melted butter or margarine over them and sprinkle with 1/2 of pudding mixture.
Place rest of pieces among first ones and cover with remaining butter and dry mix.
Let rise in a warm place until doubled (1 1/2 hours) or cover loosely and place in refrigerator overnight.
When risen, dough should reach top of pan.

title: sweet and sour cocktail wieners
directions: Heat mustard and jelly on low heat, stirring until smooth and blended. Add wieners; heat 3 to 4 minutes. Yields 50.

title: spinach dip
directions: Cook spinach about 10 minutes; drain and squeeze water out. Mix all ingredients together.
Then add spinach.
Serve with Wheat Thins.

title: strawberry jello salad
directions: Dissolve jello in 2 cups of hot water.
Mash cranberry sauce and mix into jello.
Put into refrigerator until jelled around the edges.
Add drained pineapple and nuts to mixture.
Return to refrigerator and let jell.

title: tuna fish casserole
directions: Heat mushroom soup with 1 can of water.
Layer potato chips (crushed) in a 13 x 9 x 2-inch casserole dish.
Sprinkle tuna over chips.
Layer more crushed chips.
Pour heated soup over this and bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Quick and easy!

title: short-cut hot fudge sauce
directions: Combine all ingredients in a 2-cup measure. Microwave at 50% (Medium) for 2 to 3 minutes or until the mixture is smooth, stirring once during cooking time.
(For thinner sauce, add more milk in small quantities.)
Serve sauce warm or cold.
Makes 1 cup.

title: stuffed cabbage
directions: Peel cabbage.
Place cabbage leaves into boiling water until tender and pliable.
Mix other ingredients thoroughly.
Form into balls and wrap with cabbage leaves.
Put cabbage rolls in 4-quart pressure cooker with 1/2 cup water.
Time for 15 minutes after pressure cooker starts jiggling.
Reduce pressure quickly by putting cooker under cold water.
Ready to serve.
Serves 24.

title: unbelievable venison
directions: You will also need 1 or 2 toothpicks per roll and pastry brush for lemon juice.

title: cole slaw
directions: Grate cabbage in bowl.
Add onion, mayonnaise, vinegar, salt and pepper.
Mix well; cover and put in refrigerator until serving.

title: banana bread
directions: Crush bananas and let stand until they turn dark.
Cream butter and sugar.
Add beaten eggs.
Add dry ingredients.
Add sour milk, flavoring and bananas.
Bake in a greased loaf pan in moderate oven 1 hour.

title: ranch vegetables
directions: Combine dressing mix and oil in large bowl.
Add frozen vegetables and toss.
Bake in casserole dish at 375° for 30 minutes, stirring every 10 minutes.

title: brandied fruit starter juice
directions: Combine all ingredients in a clean large jar.
Stir gently. Cover and let stand at room temperature 3 weeks.
Serve fruit over ice cream or pound cake, reserving at least 1 cup starter at all times.
To replenish starter add 1 cup sugar and one of the first four ingredients every one to 3 weeks, alternating fruits each time; stir gently.
Cover and let stand 3 days before using. Yields 6 cups.

title: crab dip
directions: Melt cream cheese in double boiler.
Mix in all else but crab. Stir well.
Add crab and mix well.
Keep warm when serving.

title: chicken spaghetti
directions: Cook chicken and cut into pieces or cubes.
Cook the spaghetti in the same chicken water.
Mix mushroom soup, chili powder or seasoning salt and cheese together.
Stir up with chicken and noodles.
Put in casserole dish.
Cook at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: mrs. baker's cheesecake
directions: To make the crust, spread butter thickly on pan and shake graham cracker crumbs to coat.

title: hot chicken casserole
directions: Debone chicken and crumble corn chips.
Mix with other ingredients.
Melt cheese and butter together and mix with ingredients.
Pour in large casserole dish and bake at 375° for 1 hour.

title: potato pizza
directions: In saucepan, boil water, tomatoes and oregano.
In a greased casserole, layer potatoes, powdered cheese from box, pepperoni, Mozzarella cheese and butter.
Make at least 2 or 3 layers.
Then pour boiled mixture over each layer.
Place lid on top of casserole.
Bake at 400° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: refrigerator rolls
directions: Scald milk.
Stir in sugar, salt and shortening.
Cool.
Soften yeast in water.
Add potatoes to milk.
Mix. Add yeast and eggs. Add half of flour.
Mix well.
Add rest of flour.
Knead until smooth.
Place in greased bowl, brush with oil and cover with plastic wrap.
Place in refrigerator at least 12 hours.
Remove from fridge 3 to 4 hours before shaping.
Shape.
Let rise.
Bake at 400° for 12 to 15 minutes.
Makes 3 dozen rolls.

title: chocolate chess pie
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Melt margarine, then mix all ingredients.
Pour into pie crust.
Bake for 30 minutes.

title: orange juice ice
directions: In medium bowl stir orange juice, sugar and lemon juice until sugar is dissolved.
Pour juice mixture into six custard cups, cover and freeze until firm, about 5 hours.
Remove ices from freezer.
Let stand at room temperature, about 10 minutes.

title: first quarter gusto
directions: Dump Wolf Brand chili (no beans) into medium saucepan (do not scrape grease from can).
Add corn, jalapenos, onion (chopped) and cheese.
Put crushed tortilla chips into big bowl.
Pour hot mixture over chips. Enjoy with cold beers and good game. Begin Rolaids at half time if consumed during first quarter.

title: cranberry-raisin pie
directions: For Filling:
Combine 1/2 cup boiling water and margarine. Stir until melted.
Stir in cranberries, raisins, sugar, flour and vanilla; set aside.

title: nacho dip
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Cook, uncovered, until cheese melts (approximately 15 minutes).

title: quick peach cobbler
directions: Melt butter in a 9 x 13-inch baking pan.
Combine sugar, milk and flour in bowl; mix well.
Pour over melted butter.
Spoon peaches over batter using syrup also.
Do not stir.
Bake at 375° for 40 minutes or until brown.

title: beef burgundy
directions: Saute mushrooms in butter.
Remove mushrooms and liquid; set aside.
Fry bacon until crisp; cut up.
Remove and set aside.

title: mock steak
directions: Pour soup mixed with milk over top and bake for 1 hour.
For extra goodness top each piece with Velveeta cheese and melt.

title: peach cobbler
directions: Melt butter in a deep baking dish.
Stir up batter and pour into melted butter, but do not stir.
Put sugared, sliced peaches on top, but do not stir.

title: pumpkin roll
directions: Mix eggs, sugar, salt, pumpkin and vanilla.
Add flour, baking soda and cinnamon.
Pour and spread evenly onto greased cookie sheet and bake at 350° for 15 minutes or until golden brown.
Dump immediately on terry cloth towel and roll up.
Place in freezer for 30 minutes or until cool.

title: marshmallow clouds
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Until you are ready to assemble the cookies just prior to baking, keep the marshmallows in the freezer; otherwise they will thaw too rapidly.
In medium bowl, combine flour, cocoa and baking soda.
Set aside.
Combine sugars in a large bowl.
Using an electric mixer, blend in butter, scraping down the sides of the bowl.
Add eggs and vanilla and beat at medium speed until light and fluffy.
Add the flour mixture and chocolate chips and blend at low speed until combined. Butter will be very stiff.
Gather 4 to 5 frozen marshmallows in the palm of your hand and cover them with a heaping tablespoonful of dough.
Wrap the dough around the marshmallows,
completely encasing them and forming a 2-inch diameter dough ball.
Place balls on ungreased baking sheets 2 inches apart.
Bake 8 to 10 minutes.
Cool on pan for 2 minutes, then transfer to a cool flat surface.

title: pudding cake
directions: Mix pudding as directed on the box.
Mix pudding with dry cake mix until smooth.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes in a 9 x 13-inch cake pan.
Sprinkle on top chocolate chips and nuts.

title: strawberry soup
directions: Blend or process through your food processor all ingredients until it is very smooth.
Strain through a fine sieve.
Chill and serve very, very cold.

title: 24 hour salad
directions: Layer in order given in large salad bowl.
Leave salad in layer.
Cover tightly for 24 hours in refrigerator.
Toss just before serving.

title: hash brown casserole
directions: Melt margarine and mix with soup, sour cream and then add hash browns.
Put in a 9 x 13-inch pan and bake at 350° for approximately 45 minutes.

title: poppy seed ham sandwiches
directions: Melt margarine. Add mustard, poppy seed, Worcestershire and onion (I use raw onion chopped for freshness). Remove rolls from packages; do not break apart. Slice through their centers horizontally. Put 2 tablespoons of the margarine mix into the bottoms of the foil pans and then place the "bottoms" of the rolls in the pans. Place 3 tablespoons of margarine mix on the halves. Put a layer of ham and then a layer of grated cheese. Place top halves over the cheese. Use remaining margarine mix on the tops (once again, use fresh onions here). Heat oven to 400° and bake for 10 minutes. Let cool and then cut.

title: carrot bread
directions: Add
dry
ingredients
to
liquid mixture and mix well. Bake at	350°
for 30 minutes.
Makes 6 small miniature loaves or 2 bread loaves.

title: apple salad
directions: Amounts of ingredients should be governed by personal preference.
Toss apples with celery, nuts, coconut and raisins. If apples are not sweet enough, add small amount of sugar.
May be served plain or with mayonnaise or sour cream.
Bananas, pineapple or other fruits may be substituted or added for variation.

title: cherry delight
directions: Mix all ingredients in a large mixing bowl together. Pour into 2 graham cracker pie crusts. Use one now and freeze the other for later if you wish.

title: granny's chicken and dumplings
directions: Boil chicken breasts.
Add salt and black pepper. Remove chicken and add chicken bouillon cubes to liquid.

title: lemon bars(another of kass's confections)
directions: Cream butter and brown sugar until fluffy.
Add flour and nuts and blend until mixture resembles coarse crumbs.
Reserve 1/2 cup mixture for topping.
Firmly press remainder into a greased 9 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Bake in a preheated 350° oven about 12 minutes. Immediately spread cheese filling over base.
Sprinkle with reserved crumb mixture.
Bake 30 minutes longer.
Cool.
Cut into bars.
Yields 32 bars.

title: hush puppies
directions: Combine all together and drop with teaspoon in deep fat at 300°.
Cook until brown.
Drain on paper towel.

title: yummy yams
directions: Boil sweet potatoes in a large pot of water until tender. Cool and refrigerate until cold.
Peel potatoes and slice lengthwise into 3 slices.
Line casserole dish (9 x 11-inch will work) with pats of butter, then layer with sweet potatoes, white sugar, brown sugar, cinnamon and butter.
Repeat the layers.
Add enough water to cover bottom of casserole dish (about 1/4 cup). Bake at 350°, uncovered, for 2 hours.
Top with marshmallows the last 5 minutes.
Watch closely to prevent marshmallows from burning.

title: peanut butter cookies
directions: Blend margarine, peanut butter, sugars and eggs.
Sift dry ingredients and add to mixture.
Mix well.
Roll into balls the size of a golf ball.
Press down with a fork coated with flour. Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.
For softer cookies, bake 9 minutes (depending on oven).

title: taco dip
directions: Set cream cheese on counter to soften about 1 hour.
Once it's soft, put in large mixing bowl with sour cream and taco seasoning mix.
Use electric mixer to mix until lumps are almost gone. Spread mixture in 9 x 13-inch cake pan.
Add lettuce, tomatoes, cheese and olives over mixture.
It's ready to dip your favorite tortilla chip in.
Refrigerate.

title: veggie bars(appetizers)
directions: Unroll crescent roll dough.
Place in a lightly greased (or spray with Pam) 15 x 10 x 1-inch jelly roll pan, pressing edges and perforations together to line bottom of pan. Bake at 350° for 7 to 8 minutes or until browned.
Cool.

title: aunt janny's dessert
directions: Heat whipping cream and sugar over low heat until sugar is dissolved.
Stir in sour cream and creme de cacao.
Pour into individual serving bowls (clear crystal and stemmed are best effect).
Refrigerate several hours.
When ready to serve, spoon a portion of thawed frozen red raspberries with their juice over the top.

title: homemade sauerkraut
directions: Mix together the cabbage and salt.
Cover with plastic, then put plastic bag with water in it to seal the crock.
Keep fairly warm and can or freeze after 6 weeks.
Very good.

title: heart smart cocoa kisses
directions: Preheat oven to 200°.
Line 2 large cookie sheets with foil. In small bowl with mixer at high speed, beat egg whites, cream of tartar and salt until soft peaks form.
At high speed, beat in cocoa and almond extract until blended.
Fold in almonds.
Drop mixture by slightly rounded tablespoonful onto cookie sheets. Bake 1 hour and 15 minutes or until set.
Cool on cookie sheets or wire racks 10 minutes.
With metal spatula, carefully loosen and remove kisses from foil.
Cool completely and store in tightly covered container.

title: two easy cake
directions: Mix all cake ingredients together.
Put in greased and floured 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: fruit medley
directions: In a bowl, combine everything but pecans!
Cover and refrigerate.
Just before serving, stir in pecans.
Yields 8 to 10 servings.

title: layered spaghetti bake
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Brown meat with green pepper and onion; drain.
Stir in Miracle Whip, tomato sauce, Parmesan cheese, oregano and pepper.
Cook for 2 or 3 minutes over low heat until thoroughly heated.
Place 1/2 of the spaghetti in 2-quart casserole.
Top with 1/2 of the meat mixture and 1/2 Cheddar cheese.
Repeat layers.
Bake for 30 minutes.
Makes approximately 6 servings.

title: pat's fruit salad
directions: Drain the oranges, pineapple and pineapple chunks.
Mix pie filling with all the other fruits and chill. Serve over lettuce or with cottage cheese and lettuce.
Makes about 10 good servings.

title: strawberry salad
directions: Mix jello and water together. Set aside. Mix frozen strawberries, crushed pineapple, gelatin and bananas together. Divide in half and add half to the jello mixture. Pour into 8 x 10 pan. Refrigerate jello mixture until firm. Remove from refrigerator and cover with sour cream. Pour the other half of the strawberry, pineapple, gelatin and banana mixture over the sour cream. Refrigerate overnight and serve. Great at Christmas.

title: marinated pork tenderloin
directions: Marinate 8 hours or overnight.
Best grilled for 20 minutes per pound or bake at 325° for 25 minutes per pound.
To serve, slice thinly.

title: vegetable lasagna
directions: In 12 x 8-inch glass dish, place unwrapped frozen block of spinach.
Microwave at Low for 12 to 14 minutes, breaking apart after 10 minutes or until thawed.
Drain.
In small bowl mix together tomato sauce, tomato paste, mushrooms, onion, oregano, basil, salt and garlic powder.
Spread 1/2 cup sauce over bottom of 12 x 8-inch dish.
Over sauce, layer half lasagna noodles placed lengthwise with spinach, half of cottage cheese, half of Mozzarella cheese and half of tomato sauce in dish.
Repeat layers with noodles placed horizontally.
Microwave at Medium-high for 19 to 21 minutes.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: banana pudding
directions: Mix milk, pudding and half of Cool Whip.
Layer bananas and cookies.
Pour mixture over bananas and cookies.
Top with whipped cream.

title: oven chicken(texas version)
directions: Into a large greased pan sprinkle dried beef which has been cut into small pieces.
Wrap each chicken breast in strip of bacon; lay on top of dried beef.
Combine sour cream and soup.
Pour over top of chicken.
Cook, uncovered, for 3 hours at 300°.

title: fruit dip
directions: Blend all ingredients well with mixer and refrigerate.
Serve with any fresh fruit.
If using strawberries or pineapple, use flavored cream cheese!

title: german chocolate cake
directions: Cream together shortening and sugar. Add egg yolks, beating thoroughly after each addition. Add buttermilk alternately with flour, salt and baking soda. Melt over low heat the German chocolate in 1/2 cup boiling water. Add vanilla and cool. Add chocolate mixture to batter. Mix well. Fold in 4 stiffly beaten egg whites. Pour into greased and floured pans. Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes. Makes 2 (10-inch) layers or 3 (8-inch) layers. When cake is cool, ice with frosting.

title: frozen coconut pound cake
directions: Preheat oven to 225°.
This is important!
Cream Crisco and sugar.
Sift together flour, salt and baking powder.
Blend in eggs, one at a time.
Add flour mixture and milk, adding small amount at a time.
Add flavoring.
Stir in with spoon the coconut. Bake in a 325° oven for 1 1/2 hours in tube pan.

title: baked cabbage
directions: Wash potatoes (don't peel).
Slice into 1/4-inch slices.
Cook in boiling, salted water until done.
Preheat oven to 400°. Grease a 2-quart casserole dish.
Place layer each of potatoes, cheese and bacon in casserole dish.
Pour on half of butter. Sprinkle with salt and pepper.
Repeat.
Heat in oven about 15 minutes.
Makes 8 servings.

title: lemon squares
directions: Mix these 3
ingredients and pat down well in bottom of sheet pan.
Bake at 275° for 10 minutes.

title: smoked turkey and black bean enchiladas
directions: Grease a 13 x 9 inch baking dish.
Mix all the enchiladas ingredients except tortillas in bowl.
Place 1/2 cup of the mix down center of each tortilla and roll up.
Place seam side down in baking dish.

title: marinated cauliflower
directions: Mix the cauliflower and black olives. Add any or all of the next 3 ingredients. Make a salad dressing of the remaining ingredients and pour over the vegetables. Marinate, covered, in the refrigerator for 12 to 24 hours. Stir several times while marinating.

title: bean salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Ready to serve but tastes better if refrigerated overnight for flavors to mix.

title: broccoli cornbread
directions: Spray a
9 x 13-inch pan with Pam.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes or	more.
Can
cook
in
muffin tins and freeze.
Can then heat in microwave.
Great with Cheese-Potato Soup.

title: blue cheese dip
directions: Mix together and refrigerate.
Serve with cup veggies or chips or crackers.
Keeps well.

title: pepperoni-cheese crescents
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Separate dough into 8 triangles.
Stretch each triangle slightly.
Place 3 slices pepperoni, slightly overlapping, in center of each triangle; top each with 1 tablespoon cheese.
Roll up, starting at shortest side of triangle, rolling to opposite point.
Place rolls point side down on ungreased cookie sheet; curve into crescent shape.
Brush rolls with beaten egg.
Bake at 375° for 10 to 14 minutes or until golden brown.
Serves 8.

title: raita
directions: Combine all ingredients and serve chilled as a dip or vegetable side dish.
Makes 2 1/2 cups.

title: peanut butter pie
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients.
Slowly add water to peanut butter. Blend smooth.
Slowly stir in yolks.
Add gelatin mixture.
Cook and stir until mixture thickens slightly.
Add vanilla.
Chill until partially set.
Beat egg whites to soft peaks.
Gradually add remaining sugar; beat until stiff peaks.
Fold into gelatin mixture.
Fold into whipped cream.
Slice banana into pastry shell.
Top with filling.
Chill until firm.

title: chicken pot pie
directions: In a 13 x 9-inch pan place chicken in bottom.
Add vegetables. Mix together soup and broth; pour over.
Salt and pepper to taste.
