title: cornstarch modeling mixture
directions: Mix salt and cornstarch in pan.
Gradually add 1/2 cup boiling water.
Heat over low heat, stirring constantly, until mixture is too stiff to stir.
When cool, knead until smooth.
This mixture can be colored with vegetable coloring if desired.
Add the coloring when you add the boiling water.

title: a.j.'s orange julius
directions: Combine all ingredients in blender about 30 seconds.
Makes 3 cups.

title: countdown casserole
directions: Spoon cheese spread into 9x12 pan and place in oven until cheese melts.
Stir in milk until well blended.
Stir in beef, vegetables, hash browns, 1/2 can french fried onions and seasonings.

title: festive fruit bars
directions: Melt margarine in a saucepan.
Remove from heat.
Add sugars and water; blend.
Stir in flour and baking powder.
Add egg and vanilla.
Beat well.
Add nuts and candied fruit.
Stir lightly to combine.
Pour into a 9 x 9 x 2-inch pan (rubbed with margarine). Bake in a moderate oven at 350° about 30 minutes.
Do not overbake. Yields 18 bars (1 1/2 x 3-inches).

title: fried ice cream
directions: Heat butter and sugar until melted in saucepan.
Add everything else, except ice cream; mix well.
Press 1/2 mixture into a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Spread ice cream over mixture.
Use large spoon to spread and press down.
Top with other half of mixture. Freeze.
Makes 8 to 12 servings.

title: mini meat loaves
directions: Partially cook the bacon.
Drain and reserve 2 tablespoons of drippings.
Set bacon aside.
Cook onion and garlic in reserved drippings until tender, but not brown.

title: bread and butter pickles
directions: Cover cucumbers, onions and salt with cold water. Set for 3 hours.
(Be sure to use glass or plastic bowl.)
Mix the remaining ingredients in a large saucepan. Simmer for 1/2 hour. Drain water from cucumbers. Place cucumbers in jars and top with hot liquid. Best if you wait a month before eating.

title: mango pineapple daiquiri
directions: In blender, puree ingredients.
Makes 5 servings.

title: spanish rice
directions: Drain whole kernel corn, cooked cauliflower, cooked broccoli and mushrooms.
Cut up large pieces of cauliflower.

title: sesame cookies
directions: Cream butter (margarine) and add sugar.
Beat until light and fluffy.
Add flour; mix until just combined.
Stir in sesame seed, coconut and almonds until mixed.
Divide dough into thirds.
Place one 1/3 portion on a sheet of waxed paper.
Shape into a long 2-inch diameter roll.
Repeat with remaining dough.
Wrap and refrigerate until firm.
Preheat oven to 325°.
Cut rolls in 1/4-inch slices.
Bake on ungreased cookie sheet for 30 minutes. Remove to wire rack to cool.
Makes 4 dozen cookies.
This recipe freezes well.

title: potato bacon soup
directions: Cut up bacon in small pieces and fry until crisp.
Remove and put in with milk and potatoes.
Cut up onion and fry in bacon grease until transparent.
Remove onions and add to soup.
A spoonful of bacon grease added to the soup helps flavor.

title: buckeyes
directions: Mix peanut butter, margarine, vanilla and sugar; chill; roll into small balls and chill again.
Place chocolate and paraffin or shortening in double boiler.
Dip balls in chocolate with toothpick.

title: cream cheese pound cake
directions: Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until done.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Mix together first 8 ingredients, then add pumpkin, butter and eggs.
Grease pans.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Makes 2 loaves.

title: mixed vegetable casserole
directions: Add celery, onion, mayo and cheese to mixed vegetables.
Place in baking dish.
Top with butter and cracker crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes until it bubbles.

title: vidalia onion relish
directions: Combine onion, sweet red pepper, garlic and salt in large nonmetal container.
Stir well.
Place ice cubes on top of onion mixture and let stand at room temperature 3 hours; drain well. Place onion in large pan.
Set aside.
Combine sugar and remaining ingredients in saucepan; bring to a boil, stirring until sugar dissolves.
Add to onion mixture.
Bring to a boil.
Boil 5 minutes.
Pack in hot jars.
Remove bubbles.
Process in boiling water for 10 minutes.

title: angel pasta
directions: Boil pasta until 2/3 done.
Set aside.
Steam broccoli and peppers.
Set aside.
Mince garlic and heat in frying pan until glazed.
Add mushrooms and tomato.
Cook until soft (mushrooms glazed).
Add broccoli and peppers.
Cook 1/3 more.
Add pasta. Toss and add dressing.
Serve with with cheese.
Garnish.

title: salmon croquettes
directions: Mix all ingredients together and form into 3-inch patties. Fry until golden brown on both sides.
Serve with homemade tartar sauce made with minced dill pickles, Miracle Whip salad dressing and lemon juice.

title: cranberry crescents
directions: Combine flour, yeast, and 1/4 teaspoon salt. Cut in margarine until mixture resembles coarse crumbs. Combine egg yolks, sour cream, and vanilla. Add to flour mixture, stir or knead to form a smooth ball. Divide into 8 portions. Cover, chill. Sprinkle work surface with powdered sugar. Roll each dough portion into an 8 inch circle. Cut into 8 wedges. Place one slightly rounded teaspoon of Cranberry-Prune filling near wide end of each wedge. Roll up, starting with wide end. Place point side down on ungreased baking sheet. Curve slightly to form crescents. Bake in 350 degree oven 18 to 20 minutes or until golden brown. While warm, drizzle with Sour Cream Icing.

title: cheese and corn chowder
directions: In a large saucepan, combine chopped potatoes, water, bouillon granules, red pepper and black pepper.
Bring to boil.
Reduce heat.
Cover and simmer about 10 minutes or until potatoes are just tender, stirring occasionally.
Stir in 2 1/2 cups milk and corn.
Mix together remaining 1/2 cup milk and flour; stir into potato mixture.
Cook and stir over medium heat until slightly thickened and bubbly.
Cook and stir for one minute more.
Add cheese; stir until melted.
Serve with parsley on top.
Makes four main-dish servings.
Great with cornbread and salad.

title: corn bread and chicken
directions: Cook the hen in boiling, salted water until tender. Drain and reserve 2 cups broth. Cool hen and remove chicken from bones. Cut into pieces and place in saucepan. Sprinkle with pepper. Add soup and reserve broth and heat to boiling. Mix flour with small amount of water and stir into chicken mix.
Cook until thickened, then pour into buttered baking dish.

title: penne all'arrabbiata or "weeknight spicy pasta"
directions: Puree tomatoes in a blender or food mill.
Heat oil in a medium skillet over low heat. Add garlic and red pepper.
Saute, stirring, until garlic turns golden.
Do not brown garlic. (This will take just a few minutes.)
Stir pureed tomatoes into the oil. Simmer stirring until sauce is slightly reduced and thickened, about 20 minutes.
Season with salt to taste.

title: cranberry pineapple salad
directions: Dissolve gelatin in boiling water.
Break up and stir in cranberry sauce.
Add pineapple, orange juice and lemon juice. Chill until partially set.
Stir in nuts.
Pour into an 11 x 7 x 2-inch pan or dish.
Chill until firm.
Cut into squares and serve on lettuce leaf and top with a dollop of Miracle Whip.
Makes 12 servings.

title: sugar-free fruit cake
directions: Mix cake mix (any flavor) according to package directions, substituting juice for water.
Fold in nuts and fruit to batter. Cherries should be rinsed and soaked in water.
Then rinsed again to remove sugar.
Pour batter in loaf pan.
Bake at 270° for 1 1/2 hours (I line pan in foil and I can lift it out.
Cool and wrap in same foil).
Tastes better after stored for a week or so in the refrigerator, well wrapped.

title: deborah collier's chewies
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add eggs (one at a time).
Add flour. Add vanilla.
Add nuts.
Bake 1/2 hour at 350°.

title: date and nut bread
directions: Put dates in mixing bowl and add boiling water in which baking soda has been dissolved.
When cool, add sugar, egg and then the flour, baking powder and salt.
Mix well with dates.
Add walnuts and vanilla.
Bake in greased medium loaf pan in 350° oven for 1 hour.
Beat after 24 hours.
Delicious with cream cheese!

title: cranberry-orange chutney
directions: Combine all ingredients in a large saucepan; bring to a boil. Reduce heat and simmer until berries begin to burst.
Chill until serving time.

title: better than sex
directions: Mix butter, flour and nuts, then press on bottom of 9 x 13-inch cake pan.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.
Mix the cream cheese and powdered sugar, then fold in large container of Cool Whip.
Beat until fluffy.
Spread on cooled crust.
Mix instant pudding and milk, then spread on top of cream cheese. When ready to serve, spread small container of Cool Whip on top of chocolate pudding and serve.
Keeps 7 days.

title: mock "fried chicken"
directions: Make a light paste with all of the ingredients, except tofu and oil.
Marinate tofu for a few minutes, turning occasionally.
Heat skillet with oil until hot.

title: lettie's red devils food cake
directions: Cream shortening and sugar well.
Add eggs and beat again.
Dissolve cocoa in hot water, add.
Add buttermilk alternately with dry ingredients which have been sifted together 3 times.
Add vanilla and food coloring and beat well again.
Makes 2 layers or may use 9 x 13 baking pan for a sheet cake.
Bake in 325° oven about 50 minutes to 1 hour.
This is great with a fudge or very rich chocolate icing.

title: jane's dessert
directions: Mix all ingredients and put in pie crust.
Chill for at least 6 hours.

title: rhubarb upside-down cake
directions: Place rhubarb in pan; sprinkle 1 cup sugar over top.
Mix together the remaining ingredients and pour over rhubarb.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: corn pudding(8 servings)
directions: Mix corn, flour, sugar, seasoning and green pepper.
Beat eggs until light.
Add to corn mixture.
Add milk.
Melt butter in a 2-quart casserole as you preheat oven to 350°.
Tilt casserole to coat sides with butter.
Stir in corn mixture.
Place in shallow pan of warm water.
Bake for 1 hour or until firm.
This dish can be prepared hours in advance and reheated, covered, for 30 minutes in a shallow pan of water in a slow oven.
Toasted almonds (slivered), mixed with chopped pimentos, make a delicious relish to serve with this dish.

title: rhubarb-strawberry crisp
directions: Mix strawberries, rhubarb, lemon rind, lemon juice, tapioca, cinnamon and salt.
Place in greased baking dish, 9 x 13-inch.
In food processor, pulse on and off until flour and brown sugar form crumb texture.
Add margarine and pulse a few times to mix.
Then add nuts.
Mix with fork, then sprinkle over top of fruit mixture. Bake at 375° for 45 minutes.

title: brunswick stew
directions: Combine first 4 ingredients in a large heavy boiler.
Bring to a boil.
Cover; reduce heat.
Simmer 2 hours or until meat is tender.
Remove meat, reserving broth.
Cool meat; skin, bone and coarsely chop meat.

title: fresh mushroom salad
directions: Blend all dressing ingredients together in food processor. Set aside.

title: how to make dumplings
directions: Add enough flour so that it can be rolled out.
Cut into 1-inch squares.
Drop into boiling broth.
Cook about 10 to 15 minutes.

title: mexican chili, hot! hot! hot!
directions: Add all ingredients and cook for 2 to 2 1/2 hours on low heat. Add water to keep at the consistency you prefer.
Serve with crackers or cornbread and enjoy.

title: chicken salad pie
directions: Sift flour and salt, cut in shortening.
Sprinkle water over mixture and stir with fork.
Form a ball.
Roll into a 12-inch circle on floured surface.
Fit into a 9-inch pie plate.
Fold edges over to form rim and flute.
Press chopped pecans into crust. Prick with fork and bake in preheated 400° oven for 20 minutes. Cool.

title: clemmy's hot crab & cheese dip
directions: In heavy sauce pan, melt butter, add cubes of cheese -- stir constantly.
Melt cheese until smooth. Add crab meat heat thoroughly serve with crackers or spoons (haha) SOOOOO
VERY GOOOD!!

title: buttermilk candy
directions: Mix all ingredients except pecans and cook until it forms a soft ball in water.
Beat until creamy and drop by teaspoons on wax paper.

title: chocolate delight
directions: Melt margarine.
Mix flour, margarine and pecans.
Press into a 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes; cool. Mix 1 cup Cool Whip, powdered sugar and cream cheese.
Spread over crust.
Mix both puddings with milk.
Spread over cream cheese layer.
Top with rest of Cool Whip.
Top with cherries.
Chill 2 to 3 hours.

title: potato bread
directions: Boil potato. While still hot, rub through sieve with Crisco. Add hot water and sugar to sieved potato; add salt.
In cup, dissolve 1 teaspoon sugar and 1/4 cup warm water; stir, then add yeast. Let stand a few minutes until yeast begins to rise. Combine potato mixture and yeast mixture.

Add 4 cups flour. Beat well. Let stand 5 minutes. Add rest of flour until dough does not stick to fingers. Place in greased bowl. Grease top of dough. Place in warm place to double. Work down; let rise again. Shape into loaves. Let rise to double. Bake at 400° for 50 minutes.

title: barbecue brisket
directions: Marinate overnight the brisket with liquid smoke, garlic and salt and pepper to taste.
Cook in covered container at 325° until well done.
Cover with barbecue sauce and heat for 30 minutes. Slice (thinly) against the grain of meat.
(This can be cooked in advance.
Place in freezer, then put barbecue sauce on and heat.)

title: springtime fruit salad
directions: Peel pineapple; cut into chunks.
Combine with remaining fruit in large bowl.
Combine orange juice, sugar, sherry and extracts in bowl.
Mix until sugar dissolves.
Pour over fruit; toss lightly.
Chill for 2 to 3 hours.
Makes 16 servings.

title: turtle cheesecake
directions: Note:
Best results when using T. Marzetti's old fashioned caramel apple dip.

title: broken glass torte cake
directions: Dissolve each flavor of jello in 1 cup of hot water separately.
Congeal.
Cut in cubes.
I congeal each in a plastic pint freezer container.

title: steak and gravy
directions: Put the steak and soup in a slow cooker and cook on high all day.
Stir occasionally to keep from sticking.
When done, the steak is very tender and makes its own gravy.

title: snack time cheese spread
directions: In a blender or food processor, blend or process the cottage cheese, milk, peanut butter, honey and cinnamon until well blended.
Put into a container.
Stir in raisins.
Cover and store in the refrigerator until ready to serve.
Spread on miniature rice cakes or toasted mini bagels for quick snack.

title: company corn bread
directions: In a saucepan, melt 1/2 cup butter.
Add flour and half and half.
Cook until slightly thickened.
Crumble in cheese; blend and allow mixture to cool.
Add whipping cream, egg and sour cream, blending well after each addition.
Add remaining butter (melted). Fold in corn meal.
Fold in ham.
Spread into 9 x 13-inch baking pan and bake in 350° oven for 50 to 60 minutes.

title: cowboy pinto beans
directions: In large bowl, place beans and water to cover 2 inches above them; set aside to soak overnight.
Or, to quick soak, place beans and water in 5-quart Dutch oven.
Heat to boiling over high heat. Boil beans 2 minutes.
Remove from heat.
Cover and let beans stand 1 hour.
After beans have soaked, drain in colander and rinse with cold water.

title: hot vegetable casserole
directions: Heat all of these ingredients and drain.
Fold into sauce.

title: budget beef burgundy
directions: Cook meat 4 hours on top of stove or in 350° oven.
In this mixture combine dry soup, wine and soup.
Serve with buttered noodles sprinkled with poppy seed, baked potato and toast.

title: waffle ice cream sandwiches
directions: Toast waffles in toaster.
When done, put 2 scoops ice cream on 1 waffle.
Put other waffle on as lid.
Roll in nuts or jimmies.
Enjoy!

title: almond poppy seed tea bread(very good!!)
directions: Warm until dissolved.
Brush on warm loaves.

title: sweet and sour meatballs
directions: Combine hamburger, milk, cracker crumbs, salt and pepper.
Mix well and shape into 1-inch balls.
Place in 9 x 13-inch pan. Combine onions, green peppers, vinegar, water, sugar, Worcestershire sauce and catsup.
Pour over meatballs.
Bake at 350° for 50 minutes or more.
Turn meatballs a couple times during baking and spoon the sauce over them.
Add pineapple and smoky links at end of baking time.
Bake 10 minutes longer to reheat all. Serve in fondue dish or pan to be kept warm.

title: apple cheese bake
directions: Place apples in a 10 x 13-inch dish.
Melt margarine.
Mix with cheese, flour and sugar.
Spread over the apples.
Bake at 325° for 30 minutes.
This is great with turkey or ham for a special holiday meal.

title: black bottom cupcakes
directions: Combine cream cheese, egg and sugar in a mixing bowl. Beat well. Add chocolate chips and stir until blended. Set aside.

title: coconut macaroons
directions: Mix together all ingredients.
Mold about one tablespoon of macaroons together.
Place onto a baking tray closely together. Be sure to spray the tray very well with Pam.
Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes or until lightly browned.
Makes about 30 to 36 cookies.
Will freeze.

title: cherry cheesecake tarts
directions: Bake pastry shells according to package directions. Meanwhile, in mixing bowl, beat cream cheese, sugar and extract. With a fork, carefully remove the circular top of each baked shell and set aside.
Remove any soft layers of puff pastry inside shells and discard.
Divide the cheese filling between the shells; place on a baking sheet.
Return to oven and bake 5 minutes; cool. Just before serving, fill each shell with pie filling.
Top with reserved pastry circles.
Dust with additional confectioners sugar.

title: pimento dip
directions: Cook all ingredients for 5 minutes.
Seal in small 1/2-pint jars.
When ready to use:
Mix 1 pint jar with two (8 ounce) packages of cream cheese.
May add more cream cheese to taste.

title: lib's party cheese ball
directions: Combine cream and cheddar cheeses mixing until well blended. Add all the remaining ingredients except for the pecans and mix well.
Shape mixture into ball and roll in chopped nuts.

title: sugar-free strawberry pie
directions: Combine pie filling, Jell-O, water, 2 packages of sweetener and butter flavoring.
Cook until thick and clear.
Let cool.
Cut up strawberries and add 2 packages of Equal sweetener.
Fold into cooled cooked filling.
Pour into graham cracker shell.
Top with Cool Whip.
Save some whole strawberries to arrange on top.

title: syrup-apple dumplings
directions: Heat to boiling; pour over dumplings.
What you need.

title: garlic cheese ball
directions: Mix cream cheese, butter or margarine and garlic salt; chill. Form chilled mixture into a ball.
Put pecans on a sheet of waxed paper.
Sprinkle with paprika if desired.
Roll cheese ball in nuts.
Let chill.
Serve with crackers.

title: coconut pie
directions: Blend coconut, eggs, butter, cornstarch, flavor, sugar, can of milk and water.
Pour mixed ingredients in pie shells.
Bake in a preheated oven at 350° for 45 minutes or until brown.

title: dutch spaghetti
directions: Saute onion, garlic and sausage and drain. Add mushroom, tomato sauce and spinach. Cut chicken into pieces. Add chilli powder and Velveeta cheese until melted. Toss with cooked spaghetti. Pour into greased dish. Bake for 45 minutes at 350°.

title: cheese cake
directions: Mix jello
and hot water;
cool.
Soften oleo and cream cheese.
Mix
graham
cracker
crumbs
and	soft oleo.
Save a little for top and put remainder in bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: brown sugar refrigerator cookies
directions: Line bread pan with wax paper.
Beat eggs well.
Add vanilla, sugar and butter.
Combine dry ingredients and add to egg mixture. Stir in nuts.
Pack dough into wax paper lined pan.
Refrigerate at least 2 hours or overnight.
Lift wax paper and dough from pan. Remove wax paper.
Slice dough 1/8 to 1/4-inch thick.
Place on ungreased cookie sheet and bake in 350° oven for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: chocolate delight
directions: Mix flour, butter and nuts well; bake in a 9 x 13-inch pan at 350° for 20 minutes.
Cool.

title: sandra's salmon loaf
directions: Add soup to salmon.
Add ReaLemon and crackers.
Shape into loaf.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Yields 6 servings.

title: ruby's peanut blossoms
directions: Combine all ingredients in mixer; except candy.
Mix at low speed until dough forms.
Shape into balls using a rounded teaspoonful for each.
Roll in sugar.
Place on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 375° for 10 to 12 minutes.
Top each cookie immediately with a candy kiss.
Press down firmly so cookie edge cracks.
Transfer to wire rack.
Cool until chocolate kiss is set.

title: taco dip
directions: Spread cream cheese on the bottom of quiche dish.
Top with remaining ingredients.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Serve with tortilla chips!
Enjoy!

title: french chicken stew(low-fat)
directions: Place chicken in a large saucepan; cover with cold water. Bring to a boil over high heat.
Cover, reduce heat and simmer 15 minutes or until done.
Drain chicken, reserving broth for another use.
Set aside.

title: buttermilk drop doughnuts
directions: Heat
oil
to 3 inches) in Dutch oven to 375°.
Mix flour, sugar, salt, baking powder, nutmeg and baking soda in a large bowl.
Add
oil,
buttermilk
and
egg;
beat with fork until smooth.
Drop batter
by teaspoon (do not make too large or they will not
cook
through)
into
hot
oil.
Fry about 3 minutes or until golden
brown
on
both sides; drain on paper towels. Immediately roll in sugar.

title: pickled herring
directions: Clean and split herring.
Soak overnight in water.
Then bone and skin; cut in small pieces.
Make a brine of vinegar, sugar and spices and pour over herring.
Add sliced onions.

title: nut bon-bon cookies
directions: Blend cheese and shortening.
Mix in, with hands, flour. Refrigerate overnight.
Roll out 1/8-inch thick on counter covered with confectioners sugar.
Cut into 1 x 3-inch strips.
Place walnut piece on each; roll up.
Place folded side down on baking sheet.
Bake at 350° for 15 to 17 minutes, until light brown. Sprinkle with confectioners sugar while warm.

title: coconut patties
directions: Combine sugar, milk and syrup.
Boil until forms soft ball stage.
Cool and beat.
Add coconut, nuts, butter and vanilla. Mix well.
Drop by teaspoonful on wax paper.

title: chef's salad
directions: Peel and chop eggs.
Wash, drain and tear lettuce coarsely into bite-size pieces.
Coarsely chop parsley; cut tomatoes into wedges. Combine these with onion, cheese and green peppers.
Toss lightly; chill.
Just before serving combine salt, paprika, vinegar and oil. Drizzle over salad, tossing lightly.
Makes 50 servings, about 1 cup per person.

title: pound cake
directions: Cream margarine and cream cheese.
Add sugar.
Cream real good.
Add flour and eggs a little at a time.
Add flavoring. Beat good.
Bake in tube pan 1 hour and 20 minutes in 325° oven.

title: party mix
directions: Preheat oven to 250°.
In open roasting pan, melt margarine. Stir in seasoned salt and Worcestershire sauce.
Gradually add cereals, nuts and pretzels, stirring until all pieces are evenly coated.
Bake 1 hour, stirring every 15 minutes.
Spread on absorbent paper to cool.
Store in airtight container.

title: applesauce jello
directions: Heat water and red hots until melted.
Add jello and applesauce.
Chill.

title: roman sponge
directions: Dissolve the jello in the boiling water.
When cold, whip to the consistency of whipped cream.
Add the whipped cream, macaroons and chopped nuts.
Set away to harden.
Serve garnished with cherries and macaroon crumbs.

title: paper bag chicken
directions: Wash and drain chicken.
Combine seasonings; rub inside and outside of chicken with seasoning mixture.
Place chicken in paper bag that is large enough that chicken is not crowded.
Be sure seam side of paper bag is on top.
Fasten bag end.
Place bag in a pan.
Bake for 2 hours in preheated 400° oven.

title: pork chop casserole
directions: Place pork chops in baking dish.
Cut up potatoes on top (sliced).
Slice onion on top of that.
Spoon cream of mushroom soup on top.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Cook at 350° for 1 hour in covered dish.

title: country style steak
directions: Flour steaks and brown in frying pan.
Place steaks in a large baking dish. Add the soup and 2 cans of water.
Do not mix. Cook, covered, for 1 hour.

title: taco salad
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Add salad dressing and, before serving, add Doritos.

title: milk glue(turn sour milk into glue)
directions: Will need saucepan, potholder, spoon, strainer and 2 small dishes.

title: peanut butter oatmeal cookies
directions: In a mixing bowl, cream shortening and peanut butter.
Add brown sugar, eggs and vanilla; mix well.
Combine oats, flour, baking soda and salt.
Add to creamed mixture and mix well.
Drop by rounded teaspoonfuls on ungreased baking sheet.
Flatten with fork.
Bake at 350° for 12 minutes or until done.
Makes 6 dozen.

title: gelatin cubes
directions: Put all packages of gelatin into a large bowl.
Slowly add water and stir until dissolved.
Pour into 9 x 13-inch baking pan; chill until firm.
Cut into squares or use cookie cutter shapes.

title: tomatoes vinaigrette
directions: Slice tomatoes; place in a serving bowl.
Sprinkle with 1/4 cup plus 2 tablespoons parsley.
Combine next 6 ingredients in a jar; cover tightly and shake vigorously.
Pour over tomatoes. Chill 3 hours.
Sprinkle with additional parsley, if desired. Yield: 8 servings.

title: yellow squash
directions: Slice and cook squash until tender.
Add butter, salt and pepper to taste.
Then beat eggs and milk.
Combine all together. Top with grated Cheddar cheese.
Bake in 350° to 400° oven until cheese is melted.

title: baked beans
directions: Brown hamburger, onion and green pepper in skillet; drain. Drain juice from one can of the pork and beans.
Mix all ingredients and pour into a baking dish.
Bake at 375° for 45 minutes.

title: vegetable beef casserole
directions: In 3-quart casserole, layer half of potatoes, carrots, celery, beans and onion.
Crumble half of uncooked beef over veggies. Sprinkle with 1/2 teaspoon each of thyme, salt and pepper.
Repeat layers.
Top with tomatoes.

title: squash casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients together and bake at 300° for approximately 30 minutes.

title: best-ever gingersnaps
directions: Combine 1 cup sugar, flour, salt, soda and spices; stir lightly.
Cut in shortening to resemble coarse crumbs.
Stir in molasses and egg.
Shape dough into 1-inch balls and roll them in sugar.
Place on ungreased baking sheet; bake at 350° for 10 minutes.
Remove from baking sheets immediately (cookies will firm quickly as they cool).
Yield:
about 4 1/2 dozen.

title: chocolate clay
directions: Combine all ingredients until it does not stick to your hands. Shape and then eat.

title: pineapple sheet cake
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Bake on sided cookie sheet at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: chocolate fondue
directions: In a fondue pan or saucepan, combine cream and corn syrup; heat, stirring constantly, until blended.
Add milk chocolate morsels; stir until morsels melt and the mixture is smooth.
Stir in vanilla.
Serve with fruit or cube cake.

title: mexican fiesta casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Mix Ro-Tel and cream of chicken soup. Layer 1/2 Doritos, 1/2 sliced onion, 1/2 beef and 1/2 cheese. Repeat with remaining 1/2 of ingredients.
Bake until cheese melts.
Top with more Doritos.

title: german chocolate upside-down cake
directions: Grease 13 x 9-inch pan.
Layer 1 can coconut, 1 cup chopped pecans and German chocolate cake mix (already mixed by package directions).
Beat together confectioners sugar, cream cheese and oleo (melted).
Spread over cake mix.
Bake for 45 to 50 minutes at 350°.

title: microwave tangy mustard cauliflower
directions: Remove leaves from cauliflower and wash.
Water that is on the cauliflower after rinsing is sufficient for cooking.
Place cauliflower in 1 1/2 qt. casserole dish and cover with glass lid or plastic wrap.
Microwave for 9 minutes on high.

title: green bean casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients together and bake in casserole dish at 350° for 45 minutes to 1 hour.
Last 10 minutes, place other half of onion rings on top to brown.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Dissolve gelatin in hot water.
Add cranberry jelly and cool. Beat with rotary beater until completely blended.
Mix in crushed pineapple and nuts.
Pour into 1-quart mold or ring mold.
Chill.

title: raspberry custard pie
directions: Fill bottom of 9-inch crust with berries.
Stir heated milk into egg mixture and put into pie immediately.
Preheat oven to 475°.
Bake for 5 minutes, then at 425° for 10 minutes.

title: crock-pot hot dogs
directions: Brown
hamburger.
Put all ingredients in a slow cooker or crock-pot.
Simmer an hour, then add hot dogs and simmer 2 hours. (You may brown hamburger; add ingredients and hot dogs and simmer all day
or
overnight.) The longer it simmers, the more delicious the dogs are.
Use hot dogs of your choice.

title: chicken and stuffing
directions: Place chicken breasts in a large baking pan or dish.
Take 2 cans of soup and mix with water the soup calls for.
Mix well and pour over chicken.

title: sweet cookies 1(koulourakia)
directions: Beat oil and sugar together for about 10 minutes.
Add eggs, one at a time, and beat well.
Add baking powder and vanilla and blend well.
Add enough flour to make a soft but not sticky dough. Shape and place on ungreased cookie sheets.
Brush with egg and water mixture.
Sprinkle with sesame seed, if desired.
Bake at 350° for about 10 to 12 minutes until done.

title: grandma's corn pudding
directions: Mix all together and put in casserole.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: seven layer salad
directions: Lightly cook peas, then layer in a 9 x 13-inch glass dish in the following order: lettuce, peas, celery, water chestnuts and onion.
Cover with Miracle Whip and sprinkle sugar on top. Sprinkle shredded cheese and bacon pieces over the top.
Make a day ahead and refrigerate until ready to serve.

title: swedish pork chops
directions: Dredge sliced potatoes and pork chops in flour.
Put a layer or two of sliced potatoes in casserole dish.
Put pork chops on top of potatoes.
Sprinkle with salt.
Add onions and another layer of potatoes.
Sprinkle with salt.
Pour water within an inch of top.
Cover and bake at 400° for 15 minutes.
Reduce heat to 350° and bake for 1 hour or until chops are tender.

title: spaghetti salad
directions: Mix all ingredients and serve.

title: pineapple juice punch
directions: Let sherbet and ice cream get to room temperature (10 - 15 minutes).

title: loaf bread
directions: In a large bowl, dissolve yeast in warm water.
Add honey or sugar, eggs, salt and oil to mixture and mix well. add flour and wheat germ (8 cups altogether).
Mix with spoon as long as you can, then finish mixing by kneading until smooth.
Replace in bowl, grease top, cover and let rise to double.
Bake at 375° for about 45 minutes.
Rub warm bread with butter.

title: chocolate zucchini cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar until fluffy.
Add eggs, one at a time. Beat well after each.
Stir in vanilla, orange peel and zucchini. Sift together dry ingredients and spices.
Add to butter mixture alternately with mix.
Stir well.
Add nuts.
Bake in 10-inch tube pan, greased and floured.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Cool in pan 15 minutes.

title: ranch pita triangles(appetizer)
directions: Combine softened butter or margarine with dressing mix. Spread 2 teaspoons butter mixture on each of 12 whole pitas and sprinkle with sesame seed.
Cut each pita into 6 wedges and bake at 350° until golden brown.
Very easy and good!

title: sweet sue's sugar cookies
directions: Mix shortening, sugar, eggs and vanilla together.
Sift flour, soda and salt together.
Add flour mixture slowly until all ingredients are blended smoothly and form a large ball of cookie dough.
Drop by spoonful on a greased cookie sheet 2 inches apart.
Dip the bottom of a glass in water and mash cookie dough. Cook at 350° until slightly brown.

title: sandy's frozen fruit salad
directions: Mix ingredients, pour in Bundt pan and freeze overnight.

title: krazy cake
directions: Put dry ingredients into a cake pan and mix.
Mix remaining ingredients into cake pan.
Bake 30 minutes at 350°.

title: chicken pie casserole
directions: Combine above ingredients and put in casserole dish. Add salt and pepper to taste. Bake at 350°, uncovered, for 35 minutes.

title: roulauden (rolled meat)
directions: Place oil in large pan, heat oil. Place sirloin on flat surface.

Cover each slice of meat with 1 tsp. of dry mustard, 1/2 tsp. of salt, 1/2 tsp of pepper, 1 Tbsp. of chopped dill pickle, 1/2 hard boiled egg. Place one slice of bacon on top of all of these ingredients and roll the meat.
Use toothpicks to secure the meat together. Place the cut side of meat down in the hot oil.
Brown on all sides of the meat.
When cooked remove meat from the pan, keep the meat warm.
Make a rue in the pan with 2 Tbsp. flour, add beef broth.
Cook until somewhat thick, about honey thickness and return meat to the pan.
Cover pan and simmer for 20 to 25 minutes.
Cool slightly, remove picks and serve with some of the sauce. This recipe is excellent served with Belgium potatoes and baby carrots.

title: earthquake cake
directions: Grease bottom only of a 10 x 14-inch pan.
Spread mixed pecans and coconut in pan.
Prepare the cake mix as directed on box and pour over nut mixture.
Mix the cream cheese, oleo, powdered sugar and vanilla.
Spoon over top of cake mix and bake for 45 to 50 minutes at 350°.

title: taco dip
directions: Brown meat and drain.
Put in pot with 1 tablespoon flour. Stir in sauce and cheese.

title: potato salad
directions: Wash and boil whole potatoes until done.
When cool, peel and dice or chip, putting into large bowl.
Sprinkle with sugar and vinegar; mix well and add salt and pepper, mixing again.
Add chopped eggs, onion, mustard and mayonnaise and mix well. Mayonnaise and mustard may need to be adjusted to taste.

title: cheesy refried beans
directions: Combine beans and salsa in medium saucepan.
Cook over medium heat, stirring occasionally, until hot and bubbly.
Spoon into serving bowl; sprinkle with cheeses.
Makes 4 servings. Cover and refrigerate any leftover Cheesy Refried Beans.

title: baked macaroni and cheese
directions: In 1 1/2-quart casserole, blend soup, milk, mustard and pepper.
Stir in macaroni and 1 1/2 cups cheese.
Bake at 400° for 25 minutes or until hot; stir.
Top with onions and remaining cheese; bake 5 minutes more or until cheese melts.
Makes about 4 1/2 cups.

title: blueberry salad
directions: Mix jello with hot water until dissolved.
Add whole can of pineapple and blueberry pie filling.
Chill until set.

title: calico beans
directions: Fry bacon.
Saute ground beef and onion in skillet.
Crumble bacon.
Add all ingredients together in a baking dish and bake at 350° from 40 minutes to 1 hour.

title: hamburger potato casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Heat oil in skillet; add ground beef, salt, pepper and onion.
Cook, stirring with a fork, to break up meat, until meat is browned and onion is soft.
Pour off drippings.
In a 2-quart casserole, alternate layers of meat, peas and potatoes.
Combine milk and soup; mix well.
Pour evenly over top.
Cover and bake for one hour.

title: pear mincemeat
directions: Simmer ingredients for at least 2 1/2 to 3 hours.
Ladle into hot, sterilized pint size jars.
Cover with 2-piece ring seals and process in boiling water bath for 25 to 30 minutes.
Makes 6 to 8 pints.

title: cantaloupe conserve
directions: Cook all together until thick.
Add one small jar maraschino cherries.
Seal in hot jar.
(Do not double.)

title: pineapple bread pudding with heavy whipped cream
directions: In a bowl, mix all ingredients well.
Place in a well-greased pan and bake for about 1 hour at 300°.

title: hannah's meat balls
directions: Combine beef, onion, green pepper, corn meal, seasoning, milk and egg; blend thoroughly.
Form into 12 balls.
Roll in flour. Brown in hot grease in skillet.
Add remaining flour and tomatoes; cover and bake in very hot oven, 450°, for 35 to 45 minutes. Serves six.

title: mom's coconut macaroon bars
directions: Heat oven to 350°. Lightly grease 9-inch square baking pan. Stir together coconut, sugar, flour and salt in large bowl. Add egg whites, whole egg and almond extract. Stir until well blended. Stir in chocolate chips. Spread mixture into prepared pan, covering all chocolate pieces with coconut mixture. Bake 35 minutes or until lightly browned. Cool completely in pan on wire rack. Cover with foil; allow to stand at room temperature about 8 hours or overnight. Cut into bars.

title: babka
directions: Measure flour onto wax paper.
Combine flour, yeast, sugar, salt and cinnamon in large bowl of electric mixer.
Stir well, then add melted butter and lukewarm milk gradually.
Beat at low speed for 2 minutes, scraping sides of bowl occasionally.
Add 4 yolks and 1 cup flour; beat at medium speed for 2 minutes, scraping sides of bowl occasionally, until thick and elastic.

title: ritz delights
directions: Cook these three until thickened.
Spread over Ritz crackers. Bake 10 minutes at 350° (if thickens while spreading, add hot water).

title: thousand island dressing
directions: Combine all ingredients and mix well.
Refrigerate until ready to use.
Makes 2 quarts.

title: princess brownies
directions: Follow directions on brownie mix.
Save 1/3 cup batter in separate dish.
Cream sugar and cheese. Stir in egg and vanilla. Pour and spread on top of brownies.
Dot top of mixture with leftover brownie batter and swirl with a fork.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: light green punch
directions: Mix all ingredients together and serve.

title: cornbread salad
directions: Bake cornbread according to directions on package.
Cool and crumble into chunks.
Place cornbread in bowl and add remaining ingredients.
Mix well.
May be served immediately or may be refrigerated first.

title: aunt pearl's potatoes
directions: While potatoes and eggs are boiling, prepare enough medium white sauce for your casserole.
Slice and cube the potatoes and eggs and then layer all the ingredients in buttered casserole: sauce, potatoes, eggs, cheese and seasonings.
Continue layering with cheese on top.
Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: shrimp dip with wonton chips
directions: Cut wontons into strips or triangle shapes.
Crumble them up a bit as you drop them into the hot oil.
Fry until golden, drain on rack or on paper towel.
Keep in sealed container or bag.

title: brooke's pecan sticks
directions: Cream margarine and sugar. Beat egg yolks and vanilla with sugar and margarine. Add flour, sifted with cinnamon and salt. Grease 2 jelly roll pans. Divide dough and spread evenly and flatten with hands. Brush top of dough with slightly beaten egg whites, then press chopped nuts into dough. Bake at 325° for 25 minutes. Cut into squares or fingers while hot. Remove from pan when cool.

title: chocolate chip scones
directions: Mix together dry ingredients and cut in butter.
Crack egg into liquid measuring cup and add milk until 2/3 cup.
Stir liquid and chips into flour mixture.
Knead 6 to 8 times.
Pat into 6 x 9-inch shape.
Cut into 6 squares.
Cut each square diagonally to make 12 scones.
Bake at 425° for 12 to 15 minutes.

title: chicken piquant
directions: Mix all above ingredients together, except chicken.
Pour on chicken.
Marinate overnight.
Cook at 375° for approximately 1 hour and 15 minutes.
Enjoy!

title: chocolate cake
directions: Mix flour, cocoa, baking soda, sugar and salt in a baking pan until well mixed.
Make 3 wells in dry ingredients and into first well place cooking oil, into second well place vinegar and into third well place vanilla.
Over this, pour cold water.
Mix all together well.
Bake in a loaf pan for 45 minutes at 350°.

title: margaret holiday jell
directions: Mix all and refrigerate.

title: shrimp dip for chips
directions: Boil shrimp.
Cool and drain.
Dice up (fine little tiny pieces) in large bowl.
Pour in dips and powder; blend well. Serve with rippled potato chips.

title: barbecued spareribs
directions: Select pumpkin that will set straight and firm.
Cut meat into 1 1/2-inch cubes.
Brown meat, onion and garlic in hot oil in large, heavy pot.
Add tomatoes, green pepper, salt, pepper, honey, apricots, white and sweet potatoes and broth.
Cover and simmer 1 hour.

title: jello popcorn balls
directions: In a medium saucepan heat sugar and corn syrup.
Using a candy thermometer, or by dropping a spoonful into chilled water to see if it turns to a hard ball.
When at correct temperature, remove from heat.
Stir in dry Jell-O very well and pour over popped corn. This may be formed into balls or spread on wax paper until cooled and broken into pieces.
Store in a covered container.

title: veg-all casserole
directions: Combine all ingredients except cracker crumbs.
Place in a 13 x 9-inch casserole dish.
Top with cracker crumbs and dot with butter.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until bubbly.

title: chili-beef flavored turkey
directions: Brown turkey, stirring frequently to prevent large lumps. Add remaining ingredients; bring to boil, lower heat and cook slowly for 1 1/2 hours.
You may want to add additional water for desired consistency.
Also you might add more beef crystals for a more pronounced beef flavor.
Stir frequently.
Use the Louisiana hot sauce only if you want hot seasoned chili.
Personally, I do not use it!
I use a 5-quart heavy pot to prepare this dish.

title: hot chocolate mix
directions: Mix this all together.
Store in jars or tight containers. Makes 3 quarts.
Use 1/3 cup mix for 1 cup chocolate.
Use boiling water.

title: simple but delicious cheese biscuits
directions: Mix Bisquick mix with milk until soft dough is formed.
If dough is too sticky, add enough flour to make dough easy to handle.
Add cheese.
Dip by small spoonfuls onto ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake 8 to 10 minutes at 450° or until golden brown.
Serve while hot with meal.

title: hot fudge sauce
directions: Bring cream to simmer in saucepan.
Remove from heat; add chocolate chips.
Stir until melted.
Add remaining ingredients; stir until well blended and smooth.
Serve warm.

title: brown mountain cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Beat in eggs, 1 at a time.
Sift dry ingredients together.
Add alternately with buttermilk to creamed mixture.
Stir in vanilla and warm water.
Bake in lightly greased and floured 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan at 350° for approximately 45 minutes.
Cool.
Frost with fudge icing.

title: apple-berry sauce
directions: Peel and core apples.
Slice 1/2-inch thick.
In 2-quart casserole, cook apples and margarine or butter on high 3 to 4 minutes until apples are tender-crisp, stirring halfway through cooking. Add jam.
Cook 1 1/2 to 2 minutes until jam is melted and apples are tender, stirring halfway through cooking. Serve over waffles or pancakes.

title: tuna supreme
directions: In saucepan, cook celery and onion in butter until tender. Blend in soup; gradually stir in milk.
Add tuna and pimiento. Heat; stir now and then.
Garish with parsley.
Serve over toast. Serves 4.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli and rice.
Saute onion in margarine.
Add Cheez Whiz and soup.
Put rice and broccoli in casserole dish.
Pour liquid over and mix.
Bake at 350° for approximately 25 minutes or until brown.
This is a must at all family get-togethers.

title: bread dip with meat
directions: Make cavity in lower part of bread and save center and top of bread to use for dipping.
Cut into bite size pieces.
Mix and chill the remaining ingredients.

title: fruit salad
directions: Drain canned fruits and mix juice with instant pudding.
Mix until smooth.
Slice bananas.
Mix all of the fruit with the juice.
Chill and serve.

title: apple muffins
directions: Sift together flour, baking powder, sugar and salt.
Beat egg, add milk and stir into dry ingredients, add melted fat, add apples last.
Half fill muffin pans and sprinkle with sugar, cinnamon and nuts.
Set oven at 375° and bake for about 10 to 15 minutes.

title: dole golden layer cake
directions: Combine undrained pineapple, whipped topping and pudding mix. Let stand 5 minutes.
Cut cake lengthwise in thirds.
Drizzle with liqueur.
Spread 1/3 pudding mixture over bottom layer of cake. Top with second layer.
Repeat layering, ending with pudding. Chill 30 minutes.

title: apple brown betty
directions: Place apples in greased fruit pie dish. Cover with orange juice. Sift flour, sugar, nutmeg, cinnamon and salt. Cut in butter until crumbly. Cover apples. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: corn casserole
directions: Combine all ingredients and sprinkle top with grated cheese. Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: cherry-nut cookies
directions: Mix thoroughly the shortening, sugars and eggs.
Stir in evaporated milk and vanilla.
Sift together the flour, soda and salt.
This goes into the first mixture.
Blend in nuts and cherries.
Chill 1 hour.
Heat oven to 375° and drop rounded tablespoonfuls about 2 inches apart on greased cookie sheet.
Bake about 10 minutes or until delicately browned.
While warm, frost with Burnt Butter Glaze.

title: glue
directions: This was named by my children about 29 to 30 years ago.

title: guacamole
directions: Pit, peel or scoop and mash avocados. Chop green onions and tops; add to avocados. Add tomato, 3 or 4 dashes of Tabasco sauce, lemon juice, salt, pepper and Worcestershire sauce. Mix well. Flavor improves with time. Put seed in mixture to avoid discoloration, but remove seed before serving.

title: barbecue chicken and rice
directions: Brown chicken in hot oil in large skillet.
Stir in barbecue sauce and water.
Cover and cook over medium heat for 20 minutes. Stir in rice and corn.
Cover, reduce heat and simmer for 5 minutes.
Garnish with green and red peppers as desired.

title: blueberry tea cake
directions: Sift flour, baking powder and salt.
Cream butter; gradually put in sugar.
Add egg and milk; beat until smooth.
Add dry ingredients; fold in blueberries.
Spread batter in greased and floured 8-inch or 9-inch square pan.
Sprinkle with Crumb Topping. Bake in hot oven (375°) 40 to 45 minutes.

title: hidden valley ranch dip
directions: Mix all together and serve with chips or raw vegetables.

title: broccoli and english pea casserole
directions: Cook broccoli according to directions and drain well.
Beat eggs and mix everything except broccoli, peas and bread crumbs. Butter a 2-quart casserole and alternate layers of broccoli, peas and sauce.
Make 2 layers.
Top with bread crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: mincemeat cookies
directions: Sift the flour again with the baking powder.
Cream the shortening, gradually adding the sugar and stirring.
Add the egg and mix well.
Add the mincemeat alternately with the flour mixture, beating after each addition.
Drop by teaspoonfuls on a greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: wassail
directions: Bring apple cider, nutmeg, allspice and cinnamon sticks to a boil and simmer for 20 minutes.
Add ginger ale and serve warm with orange slices.

title: zucchini relish
directions: Mix zucchini, onion and salt.
Let stand overnight.
Rinse in cold water and drain in the morning.
Next day, mix green and red peppers, vinegar, sugar, mustard, celery seed, nutmeg, turmeric, black pepper and cornstarch.
Mix together with zucchini.
Cook 30 minutes.
Seal in jars.
May add green food coloring.
Gives a better looking relish.

title: my favorite cranberry mold
directions: Dissolve jello into 1 1/2 cups boiling water.
Add crushed pineapple and cranberries.
Mix well.
Add the rest of ingredients.
Pour into a large oiled mold or into two smaller molds.
Chill overnight.
Unmold and garnish.
You may also cut ingredients into half using one small package of jello.

title: veggie squares
directions: Roll out crescent rolls onto an ungreased 9 x 13 pan. Bake 7 to 8 minutes at 350°. Cool completely. Mix cream cheese and dressing mix together; add mayonnaise. Spread over rolls. Spread vegetables and cheese on top. Refrigerate. Cut into squares and serve cool.

title: nacho dip
directions: Brown and drain hamburger meat.
Add taco seasoning and 1 can refried beans.
Spread mixture in Pyrex dish.
Mix 1 cup of sour cream with taco sauce.
Spread over meat mixture.
Grate cheese on top (1 cup).
Bake 15 minutes at 350°.

title: tortilla roll-ups
directions: For each serving, spread mayonnaise and salsa on tortilla. Sprinkle with cheese.
Top with lettuce and meat.
Roll up.

title: pound cake
directions: Cream sugar and Crisco until smooth.
Add all other ingredients. Beat well.
Bake at 250° for

title: apple fritters
directions: Fold in egg mixture, stirring just until flour is moistened. Drop by teaspoonfuls into hot deep fat fryer (350°).
When fritters rise to surface, turn.
Fry until golden brown, about 3 minutes.
Drain.
Sprinkle powdered sugar over them while still warm.

title: chuck's sausage cheese party snacks
directions: Mix ingredients.
Knead for 1 minute.
Shape into 1 1/2-inch balls.
Freeze.
Coat baking sheet and bake at 325° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Drain.

title: peach crumb
directions: Arrange peaches in a greased pan.
Pour liquid over peaches. Mix remaining ingredients and pour over peaches.
Bake at 375° for 20 minutes or until top is golden brown.

title: jalapeno pepper jelly
directions: In a large Dutch oven, bring the ingredients to a rolling boil.
Turn off stove; let set for 4 minutes.
Then add 1 bottle of Certo and 2 drops of green food coloring.
Stir well.
Pour into sterilized jars and seal.
Makes 7 (8 ounce) jars.

title: popovers(bread)
directions: Mix eggs, milk, flour and salt for 1 1/2 minutes with electric mixer.
Add oil; beat 30 seconds more.
(Don't overbeat.)
Fill 6 to 8 well-greased muffin cups 1/2 full.
Bake in a very hot oven (475°) for 15 minutes; without opening oven, reduce temperature to 350° and bake for 25 minutes longer or until browned and firm. Prick with fork to allow steam to escape.
Great with butter or use as custard cups.

title: cranberry-apple salad
directions: Combine cranberries, apple and sugar and let stand while preparing jello.
Chill jello until partially set.
Add remaining ingredients and pour into mold.

title: caramel popcorn
directions: Combine all ingredients, except popcorn and soda, in saucepan. Cook 5 minutes.
Remove from heat.
Add soda.
Pour over popcorn and mix.
Put on cookie sheet and bake in 200° oven for 1 hour, stirring every 15 minutes.
Peanuts may be added.

title: bean dip
directions: Chop green onions from top to bottom and set aside.
Mix the sour cream and dry taco seasoning mix together in a small bowl and set aside.

title: cucumber salad
directions: Mix together Miracle Whip, sugar and vinegar.
Pour over vegetables and noodles.
Mix.
Make one day ahead.

title: hamburger casserole
directions: Mix ground beef, onions and 1/2 of sour cream.
Roll meat into small balls and cook until brown.
Drain off excess grease.
Next, stir in carrots, potatoes, cream of celery soup and remaining sour cream.
Let simmer for 20 to 30 minutes.
Pour into a 9 x 11-inch baking dish and top with biscuits.
Place in oven at 300° until biscuits are done.

title: white chocolate macadamia nut parfait with raspberry sauce* * * * *
directions: The fat on the roast pork gets almost black and doesn't look very good, but all you need to do is cut it off.
My mother thought this was the best pork roast she had ever tasted.
The dessert was from a friend in Washington, D.C.
who belonged to a gourmet club.
It is rich, expensive and oh, so delicious!

title: lasagne
directions: Cook noodles in salted, boiling water until tender; drain. Combine Ricotta, eggs, pepper, nutmeg, parsley and Mozzarella. Grease 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish; add a layer of noodles, 1/2 Ricotta mixture and half of meat sauce and sprinkle with Parmesan. Repeat layers.
Top with remaining meat sauce and Parmesan.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Let stand 10 minutes before serving.

title: slow cooker stuffing
directions: Mix all together. Cook in slow cooker on high for 45 minutes. Reduce to low and cook for 6 hours.

title: steak casserole
directions: Put sliced potatoes in water to soak while browning meat.
Add the onion and brown slightly.
Drain potatoes and put potatoes and onion in bottom of casserole.
Layer the steak on top.
Mix buttermilk, soup and spices; pour over steak-potato mixture.
Bake in 350°
oven for 1 hour, or until meat is tender.

title: buttermilk pie
directions: Combine ingredients.
Pour into unbaked pie shell and bake at 375° until knife inserted into filling comes out clean, about 1 hour and 45 minutes.

title: baked pork chops
directions: Mix first four ingredients together.
Next, put pork chops on top and then salt and pepper.
Bake in a cake pan at 350° until done.

title: chicken fingers
directions: Cut chicken into strips.
Moisten chicken with water and dip in the bread crumbs.
Place the chicken on a Pam sprayed cookie sheet and bake for 30 minutes at 350°.

title: shrimp mousse
directions: Heat the soup and add the cheese and stir until melted. Dissolve gelatin in 1/2 cup cold water.
Beat into the hot soup. Cool.
Add everything else.
Pour into oiled mold.
Set 2 to 5 hours in refrigerator.

title: banana nut bread
directions: Combine milk, soda and set aside. Cream shortening and sugar. Beat eggs. Add milk mixture and remaining ingredients. Bake in 2 greased and floured loaf pans at 300° for 1 hour.

title: pound cake
directions: Cream butter, shortening and sugar.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each addition.
Add flour and milk alternately. Add flavorings and baking powder.
Beat well.
Bake in tube pan for 1 hour and 35 minutes at 300°.
Do not preheat oven.

title: fish stew with vegetables
directions: Heat soup, water, rice, carrots, onion, salt and pepper to boiling.
Simmer 15 minutes.
Add vegetables and fish.
Heat to boiling.
Reduce heat and cook until vegetables are tender and fish flakes.

title: apple cake
directions: Mix first 9 ingredients.
Add raisins, nuts and apples last. Batter will be stiff.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 50 minutes in greased 9 x 12 x 2-inch pan.

title: peanut butter banana bread
directions: Mix bananas and cereal and let set until soft.
Mix sugar, flour, baking soda, baking powder and salt and set aside.
Add margarine and egg to cereal mixture.
Mix in flour mixture until blended.
Add peanut butter until blended.
Put in greased 9 x 5-inch pan and bake for 1 hour at 350°.

title: green tomato pie
directions: Slice tomatoes in rings.
Cover with boiling water and let stand 10 minutes; drain.
Place in pie shell.
Combine all other ingredients and pour over tomatoes.
Dot with butter.
Place top crust and bake at 425° for 15 minutes, then at 375° for 30 additional minutes.

title: italian chicken
directions: Melt the margarine or butter in pan or baking dish.
Salt and roll chicken in flour; place in baking dish with melted margarine. Brown in oven for 15 minutes on each side.
Arrange cooked rice around and in between chicken.
Add the chopped onions, celery and drained tomatoes.
Salt and pepper; top with small dots of margarine.
Cover with foil.
Bake on a lower heat (200°) for 1 hour.

title: peaches for freezer
directions: Slice peaches and mix with water, sugar and Fruit-Fresh.
Pour into cartons and place in freezer.

title: clare's quiche
directions: Mix all ingredients together and pour in pie shell.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.
Let set for 10 minutes and cut.

title: mediterranean rice
directions: Mix together rice and salted water.
Cook on High for 10 minutes.
Stir well.
Cook again on High for 10 minutees.
Stir well.
Add 1/2 cup water and return to microwave for 10 minutes more on High.
Brown ground meat in large skillet.
Remove meat but leave drippings.
Saute chopped green pepper and onion in drippings.
Return meat to skillet and stir; heat to warm.
Add spaghetti sauce; rinse jar with 1/2 cup water adding this to skillet.
Add rice.
Stir well, adding Italian seasoning, if desired.
Cover and let stand over low heat for 5 minutes.

title: hot fudge sauce(like shoney's)
directions: Melt chips and butter over low heat.
Add sugar and milk. Boil eight minutes, stirring often.
Remove from heat and add vanilla.
Serve over cake or ice cream.

title: vegetable dip
directions: Mix all ingredients and chill overnight before serving.

title: glazed carrots
directions: Cook carrots in small amount of water; drain.
Reserve 2 teaspoons of liquid.
In skillet, heat sugar, butter and liquid. Add carrots and heat.

title: strawberry pie
directions: Mix dry ingredients together.
Add water and bring to a boil 2 minutes. Cool. Put strawberries in pie shells. Add jello mixture and let set in refrigerator.

title: lemon dessert
directions: Cook above ingredients together, stirring constantly.
When thick like custard, remove and let cool.
Chill and whip one large can of evaporated milk.
Add to cooled custard.
Line dish with vanilla or graham crumbs.
Pour mixture in and cover with crumbs. Freeze.
Serves 12 to 16.

title: chicken oriental(serves 1)
directions: In a frying pan coated with vegetable cooking spray, combine chicken and spices.
Brown, then dissolve chicken soup in water. Pour over chicken.
Add vegetables and simmer until vegetables are tender.

title: frogmore stew(yield: 6 servings)
directions: 1. In a stockpot, combine the seafood boil and salt with 6 quarts of water and bring to a boil.

title: lazy betty dessert
directions: Layer the pie filling in a 9x13-inch ungreased baking pan. Sprinkle DRY cake mix on pie filling.
Top with nuts.
Drizzle melted margarine over the top.
Bake at 350° for one hour.
Serve hot or cold, with or without whipped cream or ice cream.

title: beef sticks
directions: Mix seasoning well and divide into four equal amounts.
Divide meat into four equal parts as well.

Mix the seasoning and the meat together by combining 1/4 meat with 1/4 seasoning and when all portions are well mixed, combine all four together and mix well. Put into a 9 x 13 pan and cover tightly and refrigerate.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Mix Jell-O with hot water.
Slightly jell.
Fold in the sour cream, nuts and cranberry sauce.
Chill.

title: mexican corn bread
directions: Preheat oven

large bowl, mix together eggs, sour cream, oil and corn.
In separate bowl, mix together corn meal,

peppers,
cheese and pecans.
Combine the 2 mixtures. Pour into
