greased (3 tablespoons oil) 8-inch loaf pan or 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Bake 1 hour.

title: banana nut bread
directions: Mix dry ingredients.
Add with liquid ingredients.
Bake in preheated 350° oven for 45 minutes.

title: mexican-style eggs
directions: Whisk eggs, salt and pepper in bowl.
Heat butter in a large skillet over medium heat, add onion, tomato, jalapeno and cilantro.
Saute 2 to 3 minutes, until onion is slightly soft. Add egg mixture to skillet.
Cook, stirring, about 4 to 6 minutes.

title: meat loaf
directions: Mix beef and egg together.
Work with hands.
Add salt, pepper, celery, mushrooms, onion, seasonings, Worcestershire sauce, barbecue sauce and ketchup.
Add bell pepper; mix thoroughly.
Add a little Dawn Fresh sauce.
Add cracker crumbs. Shape with hands.
Cover with remaining steak sauce.
Bake on greased cookie sheet for 1 hour at 400°.

title: beef roast
directions: Put roast in oblong glass dish.
Pour the packs of onion soup over roast.
Spread both cans of mushroom soup over roast.
Take 1/2 cup of water and put flour in it.
Mix flour and water until creamy.
Add remaining water.
Pour around roast.
Cover with aluminum foil.
Preheat oven to 375°.
Cook about 2 hours or until tender.

title: tuna tango spread
directions: In a large bowl, mix together tuna, sour cream, mayonnaise, lemon juice, mustard, pepper sauce and salt.
Fold diced vegetables into tuna mixture and chill. Serve on crackers, chips or crisp bread.
Makes about 3 1/2 cups.

title: hershey's 5 minute recipe deep dark chocolate cake
directions: Combine dry ingredients in large mixing bowl.
Add remaining ingredients, except boiling water.
Beat at moderate speed 2 minutes.
Remove from mixer; stir in boiling water (batter will be thin).
Pour into 2 greased and floured 9 or 8-inch loaf pans or a 13 x 9-inch or spring-form pan with center horn.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes for layers, 35 to 40 minutes for 13 x 9-inch pan, etc., until cake tester comes out clean when inserted in center of cake.
Cool 10 minutes on rack.
Remove from pans; cool completely. Top with favorite frosting.

title: soup
directions: Brown meat.
Add chopped vegetables and let simmer a little. Salt and pepper.
Add tomatoes, sauce, paste and water to meat mixture.
Cook with lid on low and simmer until meat is almost tender, then add carrots.
Simmer, then add potatoes.
The remaining vegetables will not take long to cook (corn, peas, green beans, garlic salt and nutmeg).

title: baked steak
directions: Salt and pepper round steak and brown on both sides.
Place in 13 x 9-inch baking dish.
Add onion, green pepper, mushroom soup and water.
Bake at 325° for 1 1/2 hours.
Serves 5 hungry meals.

title: beef burgundy
directions: Filling:
Peel and cook potatoes until soft; drain off water and mash.
Add 1 (8 ounce) can sauerkraut or add 1/2 pound cheese to mashed potatoes with 1 teaspoon pepper.

title: spiced sesame bars
directions: Sift together flour, salt, soda and spices; set aside.
Beat egg; gradually add sugar and mix well.
Stir in butter, then dry ingredients.
Sprinkle half the sesame seed over bottom of greased 8 x 8 x 2-inch baking pan; pour in batter; top with remaining seed. Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Let cool; cut in bars.
Makes 32.

title: sausage stuffed mushrooms
directions: Rinse mushrooms in cold water and pat dry. Remove stems.
Chop stems and combine with sausage, garlic and parsley.
Cook until sausage is browned, stirring occasionally.
Drain.
Stir in cheese, mixing well.
Spoon mixture into mushroom caps and place in a 13 x 9-inch baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Makes approximately 2 dozen.

title: chinese chicken salad
directions: In a small skillet, simmer the chicken breast in the broth, covered with wax paper and lid, for 4 minutes.
Transfer chicken to a plate.
Let cool and shred.
In a wok or heavy skillet, heat oil over high heat to 375°.
In it, fry the rice sticks in batches for 3 seconds on each side (they quadruple in volume instantly) and transfer them to paper to drain.
In a bowl, whisk together the vinegar, sugar, sesame oil, soy sauce, dry mustard and minced ginger until sugar dissolves.
In a large bowl, toss the lettuce, chicken, rice sticks and scallions together with the dressing. Divide the salad among 4 salad plates and sprinkle each with slivered almonds.
Serves 4.

title: irish cream
directions: Mix milk and heavy cream until smooth.
Make a paste out of cocoa, coffee and coconut extract.
Add to milk and cream mixture. Add Irish whiskey.
Enjoy!

title: cottage cranberry christmas salad
directions: Dissolve gelatin in 1 cup hot water.
Stir in orange juice and cranberry sauce.
Pour into 9-inch square glass cake pan.
With electric beater, beat cottage cheese.
Fold in Cool Whip and nuts. Spoon onto cranberry layer after it is set.
Refrigerate for 1 hour or more.

title: zucchini whoopie pies
directions: Mix together zucchini, sugar, baking soda, baking powder, 6 tablespoons shortening, egg and vanilla.
Add alternately flour, cocoa and salt with milk.
Drop by generous teaspoonfuls on lightly greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 375° for 9 to 12 minutes.
Cool.

title: homemade rolls
directions: Combine first 3 ingredients; let stand 10 minutes.
Add remaining water, sugar and 3 cups flour; mix for a couple of minutes, then add eggs, 3 1/2 cups flour and salt.
Cover and let stand 20 minutes.
Knead and place in a greased bowl; let rise until double.
Shape into rolls.
When double bake at 375° until brown.
This is good for cinnamon rolls too.

title: pat's butter beans
directions: Soak beans overnight.
Drain and rinse beans.
Saute the onion, pepper, celery and garlic until brown.
Add the ham seasoning, then add the beans, water, Worcestershire sauce, ham hocks, parsley and red pepper.
Cook for 3 hours until it thickens.
You can also cook red beans this way.

title: potato casserole
directions: Boil potatoes in their skins. Chill.
Heat butter, sour cream and milk. Grate potatoes. Add cheese and chopped chives or green onions.
Add salt, pepper and lemon pepper to taste.
Mix together. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Serves 8.

title: helen's boomerangs (buckeyes)
directions: Mix first 5 ingredients together.
Form dough mixture into 1-inch balls and let them cool.
In double boiler, melt chocolate chips and wax until soft.
Dip each ball into hot chocolate mixture using a fork.
Place on wax paper or foil. Refrigerate until set.
Can be frozen. Keeps well in refrigerator for 3 months.

title: cracker salad
directions: Chop onion and tomato.
Mix together.
Add mayonnaise until it is mixed and juicy.
Salt and pepper to your taste.
Can be refrigerated until ready to serve.

title: baklava
directions: Make syrup in medium saucepan.
Combine sugar and water. Bring to boiling, stirring to dissolve sugar.
Add honey, cinnamon stick, lemon and orange slices.
Reduce heat and simmer uncovered 10 minutes.
Strain.
Cool and it should measure approximately 2 1/2 cups.
Remove pastry leaves from package.

title: freezer cucumber pickles
directions: Combine cucumbers, onions, salt and water in two large bowls. Let stand at room temperature for 2 hours.
Add sugar and vinegar; stir until sugar dissolves.

title: lemon applesauce pie
directions: Mix together sugar, applesauce, beaten eggs and flour.
Melt butter and add to mixture.
Mix real well.
Add lemon extract. Pour in an unbaked pie shell.
Bake at 350° until brown.

title: orange-almond salad
directions: In a screw-top jar, combine oil, sugar, vinegar and almond extract.
Cover and shake well to dissolve sugar.
Chill.

title: german cream cheese brownies
directions: Melt chocolate and 3 tablespoons butter over very low heat, stirring constantly.
Cool.
Cream remaining butter with cream cheese until softened.
Gradually add 1/4 cup sugar, creaming until light and fluffy.
Blend in 1 egg, 1 tablespoon flour and 1 teaspoon vanilla.
Set aside.
Beat remaining eggs until thick and light in color.
Gradually add remaining 3/4 cup sugar, beating until thickened.
Add baking powder, salt and remaining 1/2 cup flour.
Blend in cooled chocolate mixture, nuts, almond extract and remaining 1 teaspoon vanilla.
Measure 1 cup chocolate batter and set aside.

title: hummy's stir-fry
directions: *Can add pea pods and carrots.

title: pumpkin pie cake
directions: Mix together; eggs, pumpkin, sugar, seasoning, salt, and milnot. Pour into an ungreased 13 x 9 inch baking pan. Sprinkle 1 box yellow cake mix (dry) over pumpkin. Melt butter and pour over mix. Sprinkle with nuts. Bake at 350°F. 45-60 minutes.

title: blackberry crumb pie
directions: Combine the first 4 ingredients; stir well.
Place blackberries in unbaked pie shell; sprinkle 1 tablespoon sugar over berries.
Spread sour cream mixture over berries.
Combine breadcrumbs, 1 cup sugar and melted butter.
Sprinkle over top of pie.
Bake at 375° for 45 to 50 minutes, or until center of pie is firm.

title: sweet and sour chops and cabbage
directions: Remove any excess fat from chops.
Put chops in large skillet and brown on both sides.
Mix remaining ingredients, except cabbage, and put in skillet with chops.
Cover and cook over high heat until steaming well.
Lower heat and simmer 30 minutes.
Add cabbage.
Cover; cook 10 minutes.
Remove chops and toss cabbage in sauce.

title: tom and jerry batter
directions: Beat egg whites until stiff.
Gradually add white sugar, then add 2 cups powdered sugar.
Beat egg yolks until light. Add rest of powdered sugar and milk.
Fold into whites.
This mixture will hold about 1 week in the refrigerator.

title: cheese cake cookies
directions: Mix brown sugar, walnuts and flour.
Stir in butter and mix until crumbly.
Reserve 1 cup.
Press rest into 8-inch square pan. Bake at 350° for 12 to 15 minutes.

title: tenderizing marinade
directions: Marinate in icebox for at least 2 hours before cookin' meat. Will flavor the worst meat and make the best taste bettah!
For the toughest meat tastes like prime steaks, especially on steaks cooked on an outdoor grill.

title: apple taffy salad
directions: Combine first the juice from pineapple (reserve pineapple on side), 1/2 cup sugar, flour, cider vinegar and beaten egg .
Mix together in saucepan; heat on stove until thick.
Refrigerate for 1 hour.

title: french stew
directions: In 2 to 3-quart casserole, combine stew
meat, potatoes, carrots, celery, onions, peas, vegetable juice, tapioca, sugar, salt and pepper.
Stir to combine ingredients.
Cover casserole with tight fitting lid. Bake at 250° for 3 to 4 hours.

title: my favorite
directions: Place several ice cubes in 1 rock glass.
Add a generous supply of Absolute.
Add a dash of water and a lemon twist (optional).

title: german potato salad(from 1975 edition)
directions: Boil potatoes; when soft, peel and dice.
Add celery, sliced eggs and onion.
Fry bacon until crisp and brown.
Beat eggs; add sugar, spices, vinegar and water.
Mix well.
Pour egg mixture into hot bacon fat and stir until mixture thickens (about 10 minutes).
Pour over potatoes and mix lightly.

title: banana nut bread
directions: * To make sour milk, measure 4 tablespoons milk plus 1 tablespoon vinegar.

title: banana nut bread
directions: Cream sugar and margarine.
Add eggs; beat well after each one.
Add bananas, vanilla, salt, baking powder, baking soda, flour and sour cream.
Beat well.
Add nuts, if desired.
Pour into 2 greased and floured loaf pans.
Bake for 45 to 60 minutes at 350°.

title: sweet potato casserole
directions: Mix and spread over potato mixture.
Bake at 350°, uncovered, for 35 minutes.

title: apple dumplings
directions: Sift flour, baking powder and salt. Cut in shortening. Add and mix to smooth out dough. Turn onto floured board and divide into 6 portions. Roll each large enough to cover one apple. Place apple on each piece of dough. Fill with cinnamon and sugar. Wet edges of dough and fold over apple. Place on greased baking sheet and bake in moderate oven (300° to 350°) until apples are tender (about 1/2 hour).

title: pork tenderloin(gourmet style)
directions: Mix half the flour (1/4 cup) with 1 1/2 teaspoons salt and paprika; dredge pork slices in the mixture.
Melt butter in a large skillet and brown meat well on both sides.
Arrange in shallow 2-quart baking dish.

title: corn casserole
directions: Melt oleo and saute onion and green pepper.
Mix everything else together.
Spray casserole dish with Pam.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes, covered.
Uncover and bake for 30 more minutes.

title: tomato soup dressing
directions: Place all ingredients in blender and blend well.
Let stand for one hour before serving.
Refrigerate.

title: pepperoni bread
directions: Thaw bread dough and allow to rise according to package directions.
Divide risen dough in half and roll one-half into a 12 x 10-inch rectangle on a lightly floured counter.
Brush lightly with olive oil and spread generously with pepperoni and then cheese. Roll from the long end 3 times, tucking pepperoni and cheese in gently.
Seal ends with wet fingertips and place seam side down on greased baking sheet.
Repeat with remaining bread dough.
Bake at 375° for 30 minutes or until brown.
Some cheese may leak out, this is normal.
Slice and serve warm. May be wrapped in foil and reheated at 400° for 10 to 15 minutes.
Makes 2 loaves, about 10 slices each.

title: bible cake
directions: Season to taste with spices in great abundance (2 Chronicles 9:9).
Cream together butter and sugar.
Add dry ingredients, alternately with milk.
Fold in raisins and chopped figs.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: sweet potato casserole
directions: First Layer:
Mix Ritz crackers and 1 stick melted margarine. Put into pan.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 15 minutes.
Cool.

title: grandpa's shrimp creole
directions: Boil the shrimp for 12 minutes in water with the caraway seed in it and 1 teaspoon salt.
Do not boil any longer, as shrimp will become tough.
Remove shrimp from water; cool and peel.

title: tangy barbecue sauce
directions: Combine all ingredients in saucepan.
Bring to a boil; stir occasionally.
Reduce heat; cover and simmer 30 minutes.
Discard bay leaf.
Use to baste chicken, ribs or chops.
Also great to use as a chip dip.

title: egg casserole
directions: Mix all but meat together and pour into a 9 x 13-inch pan the night before serving.
In the morning, bake at 325° for 1 hour. Put bacon or sausage on top for the last 1/2 hour.
Cut in squares to serve.

title: shrimp salad(serves 6 to 8)
directions: Mix mayonnaise, lemon juice, garlic salt and soy sauce.
Allow to blend overnight.
Add shrimp, peas, celery and onion.
Chill. Just before serving, add noodles and almonds.

title: cheese ball
directions: Let cream cheese soften to room temperature.
Combine all ingredients, except 1 cup nuts.
Use this cup of nuts to roll ball in.
Serve with crackers.
Can be frozen.
Decorate with pineapple ring and cherries.

title: layered taco dip
directions: Mix taco seasoning into sour cream.
Mix in bean dip.
Spread in round dish to serve in.
Top with onions, tomato, cheese and olives.
Serve with Tostitos chips.

title: fresh vegetable dip
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Refrigerate overnight.
Serve with mixed raw vegetables.
Makes 1 cup.

title: hash stuffed peppers
directions: Cut a thin slice from the stem of each green pepper; scoop out seeds.
Bring water and salt to a boil in a large saucepan.
Add peppers.
Simmer, covered, for 5 minutes.
Remove peppers and drain.
Melt butter in a medium saucepan.
Add onion and saute for 2 minutes.
Stir in remaining ingredients.
Spoon mixture into pepper shells.
Place in a greased 10 x 6 x 1 1/2-inch baking pan. Bake uncovered in a preheated oven at 350° for about 30 minutes. Serves 6.

title: refrigerator rolls
directions: Mix ingredients well; store in refrigerator up to a week.
To make rolls, stir dough well.
Start with a lot of flour, enough to handle dough.
Roll and cut with biscuit cutter.
Rub each side with melted butter; fold over to bake.
Bake for 12 to 15 minutes in a 450° oven.

title: perfect chocolate cake
directions: Combine cocoa and boiling water, stirring until smooth; set aside. Cream butter. Gradually add sugar. Beat at medium speed. Add eggs, one at a time. Combine flour and next 3 ingredients and add to creamed mixture. Beat at low speed. Stir in vanilla. Pour into 3 greased cake pans. Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: easy green chili stew
directions: Place cooked, crumbled hamburger, chilies, corn, potatoes and onion in large saucepan.
Add 2 cups of water.
Bring to boil, then simmer approximately 1 hour or until thick and potatoes are tender. Add water, salt and pepper during cooking, as needed.

title: easy cheese ring
directions: Mix all together, except preserves.
Spray a ring mold with Pam.
Place mixture in mold and refrigerate until firm.
Turn out when ready to use.
Fill center of ring with strawberry preserves. Serve with crackers.

title: lemon lush
directions: Bake on low heat until it barely browns.
It burns easily. Cool before adding second layer.

title: meat loaf
directions: Put ground chuck in a large bowl.
Cut up onion fine; mash up crackers in buttermilk.
Let crackers get real soft.
Add to meat. Add egg, pepper and salt.
Then add ketchup; mix real good and bake about 1 hour at 400°.
Then drain good and put more ketchup on top and bake another 15 minutes.

title: rhubarb cake
directions: Cream together first 8 ingredients, then fold in rhubarb and nuts.
Pour into a 9 x 13 greased and floured pan.
Mix cinnamon and 1/2 cup of sugar together and sprinkle on top of cake mixture. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: mac-apple dips
directions: Mix all together and chill.
Cut apples before serving.
Also yummy with veggies.

title: taco salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together (or add hamburger to salad as needed).

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Mix all together.
Place in Pam sprayed casserole dish.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: breast of chicken shirley
directions: Pre-heat oven to 350°. Season chicken with salt and paprika. Melt butter in a large skillet on medium high. Brown chicken quickly on both sides of each piece on medium high. Transfer to shallow pan large enough to accomodate pieces in a single layer. Combine soup and curry and pour over the chicken. Cover and bake for 1 hour. Remove chicken and stir in sour cream, mushrooms and almonds into sauce. Return chicken to dish and spoon sauce over all. Bake uncovered until bubbly and brown.

title: pinwheel tortillas
directions: Mix sour cream with cream cheese.
Add cheese, olives, onions and seasonings.
Chill mixture for 2 hours.
Spread tortilla with refried beans, then with cheese mixture.
Roll up, wrap in Saran Wrap and chill.
Cut into bite-size pieces.
Serve with salsa.

title: hamburger baked beans
directions: Cook ground beef and chopped onion in a small amount of fat in a heavy skillet.
Cook slowly.
Add remaining ingredients and mix well.
Put in a casserole dish and bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: rosemary's own root beer
directions: Dissolve sugar in some hot water, combine it with the rest of the ingredients.
Put the mixture into jars.
Cover them and set them in the sun for 4 hours.

title: rum balls
directions: Place unopened can of milk in a 2-quart saucepan full of water.
Bring to a boil.
Continue to boil for 1 1/2 hours.
Take can out and let cool.
Open can an mix with walnuts and wafers. Form 3/4-inch balls and roll them in confectioners sugar.

title: fettucine alfredo
directions: Melt butter; add all ingredients except grated pasta cheese. After fettucine is cooked and drained, coat with pasta cheese, then add saucepan mixture.

title: sunshine punch
directions: Combine in punch bowl the orange juice, lemonade and limeade with 1 quart water. Mix well, then stir in ginger ale and ice cubes. Serves 12.

title: crunchy pea salad
directions: Garnish with cooked, crumbled bacon.

title: bleu cheese biscuits
directions: Melt butter and cheese together and pour over biscuits.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes. Serve hot.

title: mexican casserole
directions: Brown hamburger meat; drain.
Mix the milk, soups, chiles and enchilada sauce together until it boils on medium heat.
Add the meat to the soup mixture and stir well.
In bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan, place the Doritos.
Pour the mixture over the chips and top with cheese.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: easy salad
directions: Mix cream and Cool Whip together and then stir in rest of ingredients.
Chill overnight.

title: monkey bread
directions: Cut each biscuit into 4 pieces.
Mix white sugar and 2 teaspoons of cinnamon in a bowl.
Roll pieces of biscuit dough until covered.
Arrange covered pieces evenly in a Bundt pan.

title: oven stew
directions: Put first five ingredients in pot.
Add salt, soup and 1/2 can of water.
Bake 4 1/2 hours at 275°.
If cooked in slow cooker, cook on medium for 6 hours.

title: lasagna
directions: Brown ground beef in skillet.
Add spaghetti sauce and water to beef.
In 9 x 13-inch baking dish, assemble lasagna:
thin layer of sauce, half the noodles (uncooked), all cottage cheese, 3/4 pound Mozzarella cheese, half of sauce, remaining noodles, remaining Mozzarella cheese, remaining sauce.
Cover with aluminum foil; bake at 300° to 325° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: zucchini relish
directions: Grind vegetables together.
Add salt and cover with water. Let stand overnight.
Next day, rinse vegetables twice in colander.
Mix 1/4 cup vinegar with the cornstarch.
Add all ingredients to vegetables and cook slowly in stainless steel or enameled kettle 30 minutes or until thickened.
Seas in hot jars. Makes approximately 4 pints.

title: pecan pie
directions: Mix all ingredients together and put into a 9-inch unbaked pie shell.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 50 minutes or until firm on top.

title: breakfast casserole dish
directions: Place the eggs in blender; mix on low. Add the milk and salt, then blend. In a greased 9 x 13-inch casserole dish, place the bread rounds, covering bottom of pan. Layer the ham, cheese and bread rounds. Over this, pour egg mixture, then sprinkle with paprika. Cover and refrigerate overnight. Bake, uncovered, at 325° for 55 minutes.

title: squash au gratin
directions: Cook
onion and squash in small amount of boiling water until tender.
Break
the
bread in small pieces and mix with egg, butter, salt and pepper.
Add the drained vegetables; mix well. Spoon
into
a baking dish and sprinkle with the cheese over the top.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.

title: caramel corn
directions: Place popped corn and peanuts in large roaster.
Mix sugar, Karo and butter.
When mixture starts to boil, boil for 5 minutes. Stir while boiling.
Pour syrup mixture over popcorn and peanuts. Bake in a 250° oven for 1 hour.
Mix often (about every 15 or 20 minutes).
When cool, store in tight container.

title: chicken easy
directions: Mix ingredients and pour over chicken.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: barb's meat pies
directions: Have meat ground together. Cook potatoes with skins on.
Dry bread. Grind onion. Take skins off potatoes and chop into small pieces. Crumble bread. Add together with water to make medium thick.
Cook 1 hour on low heat. Stir often.
Put into pie crust. Bake at 350° until light brown, 15 minutes.
Cool. Cover with foil and freeze.
When ready to use, bake at 375° for 1 hour. Make any size, 8 or 9-inch or individual size.

title: cabbage salad(pickled cabbage)
directions: Bring
vinegar,
salt, celery seed and dry mustard to a boil. Add
oil
to
vinegar
mixture; do not boil.
Pour over cabbage and
onions.
Let
stand
at
least 8 hours, stirring often. Serves 8 to 12 and keeps several days.

title: zucchini pickles
directions: Put first four ingredients in large pan.
Salt heavy and put ice cubes over all and let stand at least 2 hours or until ice melts or put in refrigerator at night and stand overnight.
Put up next day.
Drain very well (don't rinse).
Boil together remaining ingredients.
Add zucchini, onion, green pepper and garlic. Boil 5 to 6 minutes.
Place in jars and seal.
Cauliflower may be added.

title: butterscotch bread pudding
directions: Combine bread and raisins; add milk.
Let stand for 15 minutes.
Cook butter and brown sugar together over low heat until syrupy (about 10 minutes).
Mix eggs, seasonings and vanilla; add with sugar mixture to moisten bread.
Pour into greased 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.
Serves 6.

title: breakfast brunch eggs
directions: Line greased 9-inch pie pan with slices of cheese.
Mix eggs, milk, bacon and mushrooms and pour into pie pan.
Bake at 350° for 40 or 45 minutes.
Let stand a few minutes before serving.

title: chili con carne
directions: Brown meat and onion.
Stir in remaining ingredients.
Cover and simmer 1 hour.
Remove bay leaf and serve.

title: shrimp kabobs with marinade
directions: Peel and devein shrimp; set aside.
Cut one lime into 6 wedges.
Wrap and set wedges aside.
Finely shred 1/2 teaspoon peel from the other lime.
Cut that lime in half and juice to get 2 tablespoons lime juice.

title: layered sombrero dip
directions: Blend refried beans and chiles; spread on a very large round serving plate leaving a 3-inch border.
Layer guacamole, salsa and sour cream over bean mixture; top with cheese.
Garnish with tomatoes, olives and scallions, if desired.
Serve with tortilla chips arranged around outside edge of platter.
Makes 10 to 12 servings.

title: hot dog casserole
directions: Cook macaroni as directed on package.
Slice up hot dogs.

Mix macaroni and hot dogs in a large skillet or casserole dish. Combine contents of both cans of soup with macaroni and hot dogs. Heat until piping hot in skillet on medium heat or in oven in the casserole dish.
Serves about 6.

title: brunswick stew
directions: Cook chicken and beef until done.
Save broth from both. Skin, debone and cut up chicken.
Pull apart stew beef.
Place all ingredients, including broth from chicken and beef and juices from vegetables, in a 12-quart pot.

Add enough water to fill pot. Cover; cook on medium heat, stirring occasionally to avoid sticking, until potatoes have softened and the stew has thickened. The potatoes and carrots will have begun to come apart and will be small in size.
Can be frozen.

title: southern cobbler
directions: If using fresh fruit, coat with sugar first.
Any fruit will do.

title: maraschino cherry salad
directions: Beat cream cheese and cherry juice.
Add chopped cherries. Add rest of ingredients and mix well.
Sprinkle nuts on top and let set overnight.

title: applesauce cake
directions: When using cake pan with a hole in it, double recipe.
Cream shortening; add sugar and cream it.
Add egg and beat well.
Add applesauce.
Sift flour and all dry ingredients together.
Add to mixture.
Bake at 350° about 1 hour and 5 to 10 minutes when recipe is doubled.

title: sugar cream cake
directions: Mix yellow cake mix, 2 eggs and butter.
Pour into greased and floured 9 x 13 baking pan.
Mix cream cheese, powdered sugar and 2 eggs until creamy.
Pour over cake mixture.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: crunchy top potatoes
directions: Place butter/margarine in casserole.
Put in preheated 350° oven.
Put peeled and sliced potatoes in melted butter or margarine and coat.
Mix remaining ingredients.
Sprinkle over top of potatoes.
Bake 30 minutes or until done and crisp.

title: baked summer squash
directions: Boil squash and onion for 20 minutes.
Melt butter and add bread stuffing; mix well.
Drain squash; mix with sour cream and soup.
Sprinkle with pepper.
In 2-quart baking dish, layer squash and bread stuffing.
Repeat.
Bake for 30 minutes at 350° until top crumbs are golden brown.

title: peanut butter krispies
directions: Bring sugar and Karo syrup to a boil; mix peanut butter and Cocoa Krispies.
Pour hot syrup over.
Drop by teaspoonfuls on cookie sheet.
Do not cook.

title: layered salad
directions: Layer as listed in 9 x 13-inch pan and refrigerate.

title: shrimp salad
directions: Mix equal portions of frozen green peas and salted Spanish peanuts with Miracle Whip to taste.
Serve immediately.

title: breakfast pizza
directions: Put hash browns on bottom of greased 13 x 9-inch cake pan. Put cheese on top of hash browns.
Add meat already cooked and drained.
Mix eggs, soup and milk together; pour over hash browns, cheese and meat.
Set in refrigerator overnight.
Bake at 350° for 1 to 1 1/2 hours.

title: rice salad
directions: Cook rice until tender; drain.
Cool.
Dissolve jello in water; cool.
Whip powdered sugar and cream together.
Fold into the previous ingredients.
Chill.

title: french market soup
directions: Simmer dried peas or beans in water and chicken stock with Bouquet garni for 2 1/2 to 3 hours in a large pot, covered.
Add can of tomatoes, onions, celery and garlic.
Simmer 1 1/2 hours more, covered.
Add sausage and chicken.
Simmer 30 to 40 minutes. Add wine, parsley and chick peas.
Makes 4 quarts.
Freezes well.

title: brown-eyed susans
directions: Cream the first 5 ingredients together. Stir in flour.
Chill for 1 hour.
Shape into 1-inch balls and place on ungreased cookie sheets.
Place candy wafer on top and push to flatten cookie. Bake in hot oven at 400° for 8 to 10 minutes.
Makes 4 dozen.

title: kansas strawberry pudding salad
directions: Bring jello, pudding and water to a boil.
Add marshmallows and stir until dissolved.
Add berries and juice.
Stir until melted. Put in a bowl or flat pan and chill until set.
This may also be used for pie by pudding it on a graham cracker crust and topping with Cool Whip.

title: impossible quiche
directions: Pour into a 9-inch pie pan.
Sprinkle with 1 cup shredded Swiss cheese and 1/2 cup ham or bacon, cut into small pieces. Push down gently with back of spoon.

title: lisa's bundt cake
directions: Grease Bundt pan with Pam.
Sprinkle half of nuts and raisins. Place frozen rolls in pan.
Pour butterscotch pudding over rolls. Sprinkle remaining nuts and raisins.
Melt butter; combine sugar and cinnamon.
Mix well and pour over contents in pan.
Cover with tea towel and let stand to rise at least 12 hours.
Bake in preheated 325° oven for 20 to 25 minutes.
Let stand 5 minutes. Go around edge with knife and invert onto plate.

title: corn casserole
directions: Melt oleo and mix other ingredients.
Put into casserole dish and bake at 400° until lightly browned.

title: broccoli-sausage quiche
directions: Line unbaked pie shell with a double thickness of foil.
Bake at 450° for 8 minutes. Remove foil.
Bake 4 to 6 minutes more or until golden brown.
Remove from oven; set aside. Reduce oven temperature to 375°.
Meanwhile, in a large skillet, cook sausage and mushrooms. Drain.
In a medium bowl, combine egg, soup, onion and pepper. Stir in sausage mixture, broccoli and 3/4 cup of the cheese.
Pour mixture into the baked shell.
Bake at 375° for 40 to 50 minutes or until knife inserted near the center comes out clean.
Sprinkle with remaining cheese.
Let stand about 10 minutes.
Makes 6 main dish servings.

title: chocolate and coconut cookies
directions: Melt together the condensed milk and chocolate (watch that it doesn't burn), then add coconut, nuts and vanilla.
Make into small balls.
Place on greased baking sheet.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.
Cookies will firm up after out of oven.

title: mom's peach stuff
directions: First Layer:
Melt butter and stir in flour.
Spread over the bottom of a large Pyrex dish.
Add chopped pecans.
Press into dough.
Bake at 350° until golden brown.
Let cool completely.

title: brown butter icing
directions: Heat butter until golden brown, add sugar and vanilla.
Add enough milk to make frosting, enough to cover.

title: doc's famous shopska salad(bulgaria)
directions: Arrange vegetables in overlapping circles.
Sprinkle with oil, vinegar, salt and pepper, parsley and dill.
Crumble cheese over the top.
Serve with dark bread to soak up the sauce.

title: diaper cookies
directions: Mix and refrigerate for 1 hour.
Roll dough into a rectangle on a pastry sheet.
Cut into 3-inch squares.
Place 1/2 teaspoon of jam into middle of square.
Fold each corner to middle and place on foiled cookie sheet.
Bake in hot oven at 400° for 7 to 10 minutes or until light brown.
Remove from cookie sheet immediately.
Cool and enjoy!

title: crustless coconut pie
directions: Mix all together; pour into pie pan.
No crust is needed. Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: mama moland's chicken stew
directions: Stew hen and
remove unwanted parts.
Add chopped onion and potatoes.
Cook
until
partial done stage.
Add remaining ingredients and cook
on
low
heat
until	desired thickness. Stir often and take care that it does not stick and burn.

title: blonde brownies
directions: Mix well.
Bake at 350° for 20-25 minutes.

title: easy apple cake
directions: Cream together sugar and butter.
Add egg and vanilla; mix well.
Stir in flour and baking powder.
Spoon over apples, spreading as best as you can.
Bake for 30 minutes.

title: shrimp mold
directions: Mix and heat tomato soup, salt and gelatin.
In mixing bowl, mix well mayonnaise, celery, cream cheese and onions.
Add soup mix and shrimp.
Mix well.
Put in oiled mold.
Chill several hours. Unmold and serve with crackers.

title: poppy seed cake
directions: Mix all ingredients for 1 to 2 minutes with electric mixer. Bake in 2 large loaf pans at 350° for 1 hour.
Cool for 5 minutes.

title: lemon poached salmon
directions: Thaw salmon, if frozen.
In large skillet, combine water, lemon juice, onion, celery, salt and pepper.
Bring to boil; simmer 5 minutes.
Add salmon; simmer, covered, 7 to 10 minutes or until fish flakes easily with a fork.
Remove salmon from liquid with spatula.
Chill or serve hot.
Serve salmon with lemon wedges.
If desired, top salmon with tartar sauce and garnish with fresh dill weed.
Makes 4 servings.

title: angel food cake
directions: Have egg whites at room
temperature.
Preheat
oven to 375°. Measure sifted flour.
Add 1/2 cup sugar.
Sift together 4 times. Combine egg whites, cream
of
tartar,
salt
and flavorings in large bowl.
Beat with
beater
until soft peaks form.
Add remaining sugar in 4
additions, beating until well blended
each time.
Sift in flour mixture
in
additions, folding in with large spoon each time;
turn bowl often.
Pour into
ungreased 10-inch tube pan.
(If
you've
baked
another kind of cake in pan, pour boiling water over it
and
dry with paper towel before pouring in cake.) Bake at 375° for 35 to 45 minutes.
Invert cake until cool, then loosen
from
sides and remove from pan.

title: fried steak with mushroom gravy
directions: Chop up the onions and bell pepper to be fried in the skillet with the meat.
Tenderize the meat with a meat tenderizer or you can buy the meat cubed, either is fine.
Season the meat with the Tony's Creole seasoning or your preferred seasoning.
Bread the meat with flour.
Heat the oil in the skillet on the highest temperature and add the breaded meat.
Turn the temperature down and fry the meat until brown and thoroughly cooked.
Add the onions and bell pepper when the meat is almost finished cooking to allow the flavors of the onions and peppers to get in the meat. Drain the grease from the skillet.
Add the golden mushroom soup to the meat in the skillet.
Also add a can full of water to thin the soup.
Simmer the meat and soup for about 10 to 15 minutes. This dish is best if served with
mashed potatoes.

title: chicken enchiladas
directions: Simmer the chicken breast in water to cover with one onion, garlic and celery until the meat is ready to slip off the bones. Return the bones to the soup and cook down to 1 cup.
Shred the chicken and mix with the sour cream and cheese.
If you use the club type, breaking up with fork is enough.
Otherwise, grate the cheese coarsely.

title: swedish meat balls
directions: Mix and roll into balls. Brown and drain grease off.
Pour 1 large can tomato sauce and 1 can of water.
Simmer for 1 hour (add water if necessary).

title: chili con carne con queso
directions: Mix all ingredients in a 1 1/2-quart baking dish.
Bake at 250° for 2 hours, stirring occasionally to blend.
Serve with Fritos or Tostados corn chips.
Great for a football party.
Men love it!

title: yellow squash casserole
directions: Stir squash, tomatoes, red peppers or pimientos, onions and seasonings together. Alternate layers of squash mixture, cheese and bread crumbs. Sprinkle parsley flakes on top. Bake at 350 until golden brown on top.

title: coconut cookies
directions: Mix first three ingredients as pie crust.
Press in 8 x 12-inch pan.
Bake 10 minutes at 400°.
Mix rest of ingredients and pour on crust. Bake 20 minutes longer at 400°.

title: sourdough bread starter
directions: Mix together sugar, dry potatoes, flour and warm water.
Let stand covered (not in refrigerator) 12 hours.
This will not rise only bubble, then keep in refrigerator 5 days, then feed with ingredients every 3 to 5 days.
Take one cup starter out to make bread and return remaining starter to refrigerator.
If you do not make bread, throw 1 cup of starter away, but it must be fed.

title: poppy seed chicken
directions: Cook chicken and pull apart into small strips.
Mix together sour cream and chicken soup.
Mix chicken into the soup mixture. Melt a stick of butter in a frying pan and crumble the Ritz crackers into butter.
Add poppy seeds.
Cook on low heat until crispy (not brown).
Butter a Pyrex dish and pour chicken into dish.
Add the cracker mixture on top.
Bake at 350 for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: amber's microwave lasagne
directions: Crumble beef in casserole.
Cover and microwave on High (100%) 3 minutes.
Break up and stir.
Cover and microwave 2 to 3 minutes longer; drain.
Stir in spaghetti sauce, tomato sauce and oregano. Microwave on High (100%) to boiling, 3 to 4 minutes.

title: pumpkin pie
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
A tablespoon of corn syrup added with the sugar gives the filling a little more firmness. Bake at 375° until brown.

title: carrot casserole
directions: Melt butter in a 1 1/2-quart casserole dish.
Add cooked carrots and coat with butter.
Stir in croutons and cheese.
In a small bowl, mix half and half, Worcestershire sauce, eggs and salt.
Add mixture to casserole and mix with other ingredients. Bake, uncovered, at
400° for 20 to 30 minutes or until golden brown.
Serves 6.

title: holiday nut breads
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease and flour loaf pan.
Blend all ingredients
in large mixer bowl on low speed for 15 seconds. Beat on medium speed for 30 seconds, scraping bowl constantly. Pour into pan.
Bake until wooden toothpick inserted in center comes out clean, 60 to 65 minutes.
Immediately cool on wire rack. Garnish top of nut bread with maraschino cherries and green sliced candied pineapple, if desired.
For better slicing, refrigerate overnight.

title: mamie's popcorn balls
directions: Works best if mixed in clean sink that has been greased with butter.

title: mexican shredded beef
directions: Prepare beef brisket as directed for corned beef.
Remove from cooking liquid and discard liquid.
Cut beef into shreds.
Return to 3-quart casserole.
Stir in tomato sauce, taco seasoning mix and water.
Cover.
Microwave at High for 5 to 7 minutes, or until hot, stirring once.
Use in tacos, burritos or enchiladas.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: baked curried fruit
directions: Drain and save juices from pineapple, peaches, pecans, raisins, pears and apricots or any type fruit.
Put in casserole. Cook butter, brown sugar, curry powder, sherry and juice in top of double boiler and stir until thick.
Pour over fruit.
Bake at 350° until hot and bubbly.

title: chocolate and peanut drops
directions: Melt chocolate chips and shortening in double boiler over hot water, stirring occasionally.
Add peanuts.
Stir until coated with chocolate.
Drop by spoonfuls onto greased waxed paper. Chill until firm.
Store in cool place.

title: champagne punch
directions: Fill punch bowl with 1 fifth each of champagne and Sauterne and 3/4 quart of soda.
For an attractive garnish, float whole strawberries with hulls.
Refill bowls as needed with the same proportions.
Yields 4 gallons and 1 pint or 104 (5-ounce) servings.

title: lemon cream cheese pie
directions: Beat cream cheese, condensed milk and lemon juice until smooth. Pour into prepared crust and refrigerate until firm. This also can be done with lime juice.

title: cornbread salad
directions: Break cornbread in pieces.
Mix in order as given.
Toss lightly.
Chill overnight.
Toss again when served.

title: pound cake
directions: Combine all ingredients in a large mixing bowl and mix on medium speed until well blended and smooth (approximately 6 minutes).
Pour into a tube pan and bake at 325° for 1 hour and 15 minutes, or until toothpick inserted in center comes out clean. Cool in pan on a wire rack for 10 minutes.
Take cake out of pan and continue cooling on a wire rack.

title: pap's barbecue sauce
directions: Cook corn oil, onion and garlic 10 minutes, stirring often. Add Worcestershire sauce, pepper and oregano and simmer 10 minutes more.
Add catsup, chili sauce, molasses, vinegar and Tabasco. Simmer 30 to 40 minutes, stirring frequently.
Apply to meats during 5 to 10 minutes of grilling.
May store in refrigerator 1 to 2 weeks.

title: old-world manicotti
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. Spray 13 x 9-inch baking dish with nonstick cooking spray. Cook pasta according to package directions. Drain; rinse with cool water. Let pasta dry on paper towels.

title: apple squares
directions: Mix and spread on top while warm.
Cut into squares.

title: three cheese ball
directions: Let cheese set at room temperature for about 2 hours.
Place ingredients in mixing bowl.
Whip with mixer until all ingredients are thoroughly combined.
Shape into a ball or roll.
Roll in 2 cups chopped walnuts.
Wrap in waxed paper and refrigerate until completely chilled.

title: 4 bean salad
directions: Wash each can of beans separately.
Drain well.
Mix all ingredients together.
Refrigerate overnight.

title: chicken noodle soup
directions: Cook noodles directly in broth for 20 minutes.
Cook celery and carrots together and save the liquid.
Add cooked carrots, celery and chicken to noodles.
Salt and pepper to taste.

title: mama j's cheeseball
directions: Beat cream cheese until smooth with fork.
Gradually stir in pineapple, onion and garlic.
Shape into a ball and roll in crushed pecans.
Serve with choice of crackers.

title: bread dip
directions: Chop and mix all ingredients together in food processor.
Put in hollowed out loaf of French bread.
Sprinkle more Cheddar cheese on top and bake at 350° until bubbly.

title: lemon icebox pie
directions: Mix ingredients thoroughly and pat into 9 inch pie pan.
Line sides of pan with whole wafers.

title: bite size lemon tarts
directions: Cream margarine, cream cheese and powdered sugar until light and fluffy.
Gradually mix in flour until dough is smooth.
Press dough into 1 1/2-inch muffin tins.
Pierce each shell with a fork. Bake in a 350° oven until golden brown (18 to 20 minutes).
Cool in pan.
Makes 2 dozen small tarts.

title: mexican pizza
directions: Combine biscuit mix and corn meal.
Add 1/2 cup water.
Mix until soft dough forms.
Roll dough into a 12-inch pizza pan. Brown ground meat and drain.
Add taco seasoning and 3/4 cup water to meat.
Simmer until thick.
Spread beans on dough.
Layer with chili, beef, cheese, lettuce, tomatoes, onions and chili.
Bake at 350°, uncovered, for 10 minutes to 20 minutes until crust is brown.

title: hamburger romanoff casserole
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Cook and stir ground beef, onion and green pepper in 10-inch skillet until beef is brown; drain.
Stir in mushrooms, sauce mix and water.
Heat to boiling.
Pour hot sauce mixture over noodles in ungreased pan (12 x 7 1/2 x 2-inch) or 2 quart casserole dish.
Cover and bake 15 minutes with aluminum wrap.
Arrange tomato slices or wedges on beef mixture.
Sprinkle with cheese and parsley.
Bake uncovered 10 minutes.

title: chicken creole
directions: Wash chicken pieces; pat dry.
Toss pieces in salt and pepper. Heat 1 tablespoon oil in skillet; cook chicken in oil at medium-high heat for approximately 5 minutes, or until chicken is lightly browned, tossing frequently.
Remove chicken and juices; set aside.
Heat 3 tablespoons oil in the same skillet.
Add vegetables and garlic; saute until tender.
Stir in tomatoes and juice, breaking into smaller pieces.
Add 1/2 cup water and the seasonings; stir and bring to a boil.
Cover; simmer over medium-low heat for about 10 minutes.
Add chicken, juices and Joe's Stuff (to taste) to the sauce, stirring well.
Uncover; simmer over low heat for 10 to 15 minutes, or until chicken is tender.
Makes 4 servings.

title: egg white for pie
directions: Add sugar to egg whites before they get too stiff.
May also add vanilla.

title: creamy broccoli soup
directions: In a 2-quart saucepan, saute onions in margarine until tender. Reduce heat to medium. Add milk and cream cheese; stir until cream cheese is melted.
Add remaining ingredients.
Heat thoroughly, stirring occasionally.
Makes 5 (1 cup) servings.

title: pumpkin bars
directions: Combine the above ingredients in large bowl.
Mix well.
Pour into 17 x 11-inch baking sheet.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.
Cool.

title: ham roll-ups
directions: Let cream cheese soften, then mix onion soup to taste. Spread cream cheese mixture on a dry slice of ham.
Place pickles lengthwise on bottom edge of ham, then roll up.
Place seam side down in a pan and cover with a moist towel.
Chill for several hours, then slice and serve.
Serves 8 to 10.

title: rhubarb surprise
directions: Crumble together like a pie crust.
Press into an 8 x 8-inch pan.
Bake for 15 minutes at 350°.

title: hot zucchini and pepper salad
directions: Heat Dressing over moderate heat.
Add zucchini and pepper strips.
Cook and stir about 3 minutes over low heat.
Place in serving dish and sprinkle with parmesan and serve.
Makes 4 servings.

title: granny walker's pound cake
directions: Grease pan.
Bake at 300° to 325° for 45 minutes (approximately).

title: senore chicken
directions: Put first 5 ingredients into a bowl and mix well.
Brown the chicken, add salt and pepper to taste.
Grease a large casserole dish, crunch up tortilla chips and place in the bottom.
Spoon on the soup mixture, then a layer of chicken, then a layer of cheeses. Repeat layers until pan is full.
Bake at 350°f. 180°c. gas mark 4 for about 30 minutes.

title: soft lemonade cookies
directions: In mixing bowl, cream margarine and sugar; add eggs.
Add flour and soda; stir.
Add 1/3 cup lemonade concentrate; mix well.
Drop by teaspoonfuls onto ungreased baking sheet.
Bake at 400° for 8 minutes.
Brush with remaining lemonade and sprinkle with sugar. Makes 6 dozen.

title: baked potato soup
directions: In soup pot, put oil and butter.
Add onion, carrots and celery.
Season with onion salt, garlic salt and pepper.
Cook these ingredients in the oil and butter, stirring to prevent burning, about 5 minutes.
Add flour to thicken, or make a paste with milk and flour.
Add water and cook a few minutes.
Add 2 cups milk.
Meanwhile, microwave potatoes, then peel and dice; put in cooked mixture.
Ladle into soup mugs, top with white cheese. Microwave 30 seconds.
Serve with toast or rolls.

title: favorite chicken divan
directions: Combine soup, mayonnaise, sour cream, curry powder and lemon juice in bowl; mix well.
Bone chicken breasts; cut each into 2 strips.
Layer broccoli and chicken in 9 x 11-inch baking dish. Spread soup mixture over top.
Sprinkle with bread crumbs and cheese.
Drizzle with butter.
Sprinkle with paprika.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes or until bubbly.
Serve over rice. Yield:
6 servings.

title: ambrosia
directions: Mix together thoroughly and refrigerate overnight.

title: german potato cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Mix butter and sugar; add eggs.
Then add milk and all dry ingredients.
Add nuts.
Add hot potatoes last, blend thoroughly.
Pour into tube pan or 13 x 9-inch greased pan.

title: don's cheesecake
directions: Combine cracker crumbs, butter and 3 tablespoons sugar and press on bottom of 9 1/2-inch springform pan; set aside. Combine cream cheese, sour cream, eggs, cornstarch, sugar and vanilla. Beat together in mixer until well blended and smooth. Pour over crumb crust. Bake at 400° for 10 minutes. Reduce heat to 200° and cook for 45 minutes. When done, remove from oven and allow to cool. Refrigerate for several hours or overnight. Release sides of pan. Cover with your favorite topping.

title: turkey casserole
directions: Mix turkey, eggs mushrooms celery, almonds and onions; stir soup into miracle whip. Toss this mix with turkey. Put in greased 2 quart pan.
Sprinkle with noodles and bake 30 minutes at 350°.

title: "toffee-like" bars
directions: Melt oleo and boil together with sugar for 2 minutes.
Pour over graham crackers which have been put on a cookie sheet (they just fit) and sprinkle with chopped nuts over top.
Bake at 350° for 12 to 15 minutes, until golden and bubbly.
Remove immediately and place on foil or they will stick to the pan.

title: homemade chili
directions: Cook beans and salt together.
Heat oil, onions, green pepper, garlic and ground beef.
Brown and drain.
Add the rest of the ingredients.

title: sausage and cheese balls
directions: Leave cheese and sausage out to soften at room temperature for several hours.
Mix cheese and sausage together.
Add paprika. Add Bisquick (1 cup at a time).
Mix well.
Roll in small balls. Cook at 350° for 15 minutes or until brown.
Makes about 125 balls.

title: stuffed zucchini
directions: Cook whole zucchini in boiling salted water about 10 minutes or until tender; drain.
Cut in half lengthwise.
For zucchini curl, cut a thin horizontal slice from top of each zucchini half, cutting to, but not through, each end.
Roll up.
Scoop out centers, leaving a 1/4-inch shell.
Chop center portion and set aside.

title: lemonade pie
directions: Mix lemonade and milk.
Add Cool Whip and pour into crust. Keep refrigerated.
This is very rich, but very yummy.

title: mexican corn bread
directions: Combine ingredients and bake in greased iron skillet or 9 x 13 pan. Amount of hot pepper to your taste (jalapeno). Bake at 400° for 45 minutes.

title: fresh apple cake
directions: Mix the first 3 ingredients; let stand for 1 hour.
Stir often so mixture makes its own juice.
Sift together the flour, cinnamon or nutmeg, soda and salt.
Add mixture to apples.
Add the remaining ingredients by hand.
Pour into greased and floured tube pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour and 15 minutes.

title: eggplant parmesan(microwave)
directions: Microwave on High the onion and garlic in butter in a covered casserole for 2 to 3 minutes. Add tomato sauce, sugar, oregano and basil.

title: chunky fruit salad
directions: Mix pudding with drained juices from fruit and add water to make 2 cups.
Cook
until thick. Cool and pour over fruit; mix and chill.

title: chicken with cashews (szechwan style)
directions: *One
teaspoon	finely chopped dried chili pepper and 1 tablespoon soy sauce can be substituted for the chili paste.

title: broccoli-cheese soup
directions: In a large saucepan, melt butter.
Add onion and cook until tender, about five minutes.
Stir in flour, blending well.
Add chicken broth slowly while stirring.
Cook until mixture starts to thicken.
Add milk.
Heat until just boiling.
Add broccoli and cheese.
Heat, stirring until cheese melts and soup is hot.
Yields 6 to 8 servings.

title: hearty pasta salad
directions: Combine rotini, celery and cheese. Mix mayonnaise, onion, Season-All, pepper and bacon. Pour over salad and toss to mix well. Chill.

title: chili with beans
directions: Brown ground beef and drain fat off,
In stockpot, put cooked ground beef and all other ingredients together and stir.
Bring to a boil.
Change heat to simmer and cook for 50 minutes.
Also good in
a crock-pot on low all day.

title: molded fruit salad-dessert
directions: I usually cook the chicken the night before and refrigerate the broth, then I can remove the fat easily.

title: carrot-pecan muffins
directions: Beat eggs until frothy; add sugar or honey, oil and vanilla. Beat until well blended.
Add carrots.
Sift together dry ingredients.
Mix just until blended.
Stir in nuts and raisins. Spoon into well-greased muffin tins.
Bake at 400° for 15 to 20 minutes.
Cool 10 minutes in pans.

title: oatmeal macaroons
directions: Combine the first seven ingredients and beat well.
Sift flour with soda.
Add to first mixture.
Add oats and coconut.
Drop on baking sheet by teaspoonful or tablespoonful.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 15 minutes.
These are also good with chocolate chips added.

title: corn pudding
directions: Put eggs, flour, salt, sugar, butter and half and half into blender and mix well.
Add corn and barely pulse.
Pour into baking dish.
Bake at 375° for 40 minutes or until center is set.

title: squash casserole
directions: Cook squash until tender; drain.
Add onion, eggs, Tabasco sauce, parsley flakes, salt and pepper.
Beat all together.
Put into casserole dish.
Mix margarine and cracker crumbs; put on top. Bake 35 minutes at 350°.

title: mexican bean dip
directions: Spread refried beans in the bottom of a 9 x 12-inch pan. Brown hamburger; add taco seasoning mix, then spread on top of refried beans.
Spread salsa on top of seasoned hamburger. Sprinkle jalapenos on top of salsa.
Spread sour cream on top of jalapenos.
Sprinkle cheese over sour cream.
Sprinkle finely chopped onions over cheese.
Sprinkle diced tomatoes on top. Serve cold with tortilla chips (room temperature) or bake at 350° for 20 minutes and add sour cream on top afterwards.

title: teddy's favorite dessert
directions: Serves 6 hungry teddy bears.
Make sure to have plenty of napkins on hand, as this dessert has been known to cause sticky paws.

title: cook's delite!
directions: Any vegetable is excellent in this dish!

title: breakfast casserole
directions: Break bread into a 13 x 9-inch casserole.
Layer cooked sausage on bottom.
Sprinkle cheese over sausage.
Mix eggs, 2 1/4 cups milk, mustard and salt.
Pour on top.
Mix soup and 1/4 cup milk.
Spread over other mixture.
Cover with wrap and refrigerate overnight.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 50 minutes.

title: christmas cheer candy
directions: Bring sugar, syrup and cream to a boil in a heavy aluminum boiler.
Boil for 8 minutes, stirring constantly, until mixture forms a soft ball in water.
Remove from heat and add vanilla. Beat until mixture begins to thicken, or is very light in color. Add fruits and nuts.
Stir and pour into 10 x 15-inch buttered pan.
Cool and cut.

title: fat-free waldorf salad
directions: Toss together chopped apple and lemon juice in medium mixing bowl.
Stir in raisins or dates, grapes and celery.
In separate mixing bowl, stir together mayonnaise or salad dressing and yogurt.
Fold dressing into apple mixture.
Cover and chill for 2 hours.
Yields 4 servings at 110 calories and 0 fat grams.

title: mississippi mud cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar together.
Stir in cocoa and eggs, one at a time.
Sift together flour and baking powder.
Stir into batter.
Blend until smooth.
Fold in nuts and coconut.
Bake in prepared oblong pan at 350° for 50 minutes.

title: stuffed boneless breast of chicken
directions: Make stuffing as per label directions. Generously butter a baking dish (8 x 8 x 2-inch).
Divide stuffing into 4 equal mounds in baking dish.

title: broccoli cheese soup
directions: Cook broccoli until tender.
Mix milk, cheese, onion, sugar and butter.
Add broccoli to milk.
Add 1/2 cup broccoli water; cook.

title: lite cheesecake
directions: Beat Neufchatel cheese until smooth; gradually beat in sugar. Blend in Mock Sour Cream and vanilla.
Fold in whipped topping, blending well.
Spoon into crust.
Chill until set, at least 4 hours.
Garnish with fresh strawberries, if desired.
Yield: 8 servings.
Per serving (including crust): 186 calories, 203 mg. sodium and 24 mg.
cholesterol.
Exchanges: 1 starch and 2 fats.

title: mom's chicken soup
directions: Put chicken, water, salt, onion, peppercorns, 3 stalks celery, all the celery leaves and 3 carrots in a soup kettle.
Cover and bring to boil.
Skim off the foam.
Reduce heat to simmer and cook for 2 hours or until meat is tender.
(I usually cook this in the crock-pot 6 to 8 hours or until the meat is tender.)
Remove the meat, vegetables and peppercorns.
Strain stock, if desired. Chill stock, then skim fat layer.
Dice remaining carrots and celery; add to the stock.
Cook until the vegetables are tender. Meanwhile, remove chicken from the bones and dice.
Add chicken, cooked rice or noodles and parsley.
Heat through.
Stir in food coloring.
Yields 10 to 12 servings.

title: chocolate reesie pie
directions: Mix the first 4 ingredients well.
Put egg yolks and 1/2 cup milk into chocolate mixture and mix.
Add rest of milk.
Cook and stir until thick.
Add vanilla, peanut butter and butter.
Cool and pour into pie shell.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook and drain broccoli.
Mix soup and milk; pour over broccoli.
Sprinkle cheese on top.
Mix Bisquick and margarine together.
Sprinkle on top.
Bake at 400° for 25 minutes.

title: monkey bread
directions: Dissolve yeast in 1 cup lukewarm water.
In large bowl, add 1 cup Crisco, sugar, salt and boiling water.
Dissolve, then add yeast mixture and beaten eggs.
Add flour, 1 cup at a time, mixing well.
Scrape sides of bowl and smooth top.
Let rise in a warm place until doubled in size.
Punch down and knead.
Pull off small pieces.
Dip in melted margarine and place in greased Bundt pan until about half full.
Let rise again.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: cinnamon mocha cream with tortilla crisps
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
In a small bowl, combine sugar and cinnamon.
Spray tortillas with nonstick cooking spray.
Sprinkle each tortilla with about 1 teaspoon sugar-cinnamon mixture.
Cut each tortilla into 6 wedges.
Place on ungreased cookie sheet. Bake at 375° for 7 to 10 minutes or until crisp and edges are lightly golden brown.
Cool.

title: turnip casserole
directions: In a saucepan, cook turnips in water for 15 to 20 minutes or until tender.
Drain and mash.
Add the egg, sugar, butter and salt; mix well.
Transfer to a greased 1-quart baking dish. Sprinkle with cinnamon.
Bake, covered, at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes or until heated through.
Yields 4 to 6 servings.

title: lebanon bologna spread
directions: Grind Lebanon bologna (or use processor). Set aside.
Soften cream cheese. Using mixer, mix the cream cheese, mayonnaise and horseradish.
Add more mayonnaise for the consistency you prefer and more horseradish to taste.
Mix in Lebanon well. Chill for 2 hours (overnight is better).
Good on toast as sandwich or in an egg omelet. Do not substitute mayonnaise.

title: holiday pecans
directions: Mix egg white and sugar with a fork and beat until fluffy. Stir in pecans and toss until coated.
Place nuts on baking sheet lined with foil.
Sprinkle cinnamon on top.
Bake at 300° for 30 minutes.
Stir twice while baking.
Cool.
Store covered.

title: corn bread
directions: Stir ingredients just to blend.
Pour into well-greased 8 or 9-inch bread pan.
Bake in preheated oven at 425° for approximately 20 minutes or until well browned.

title: pineapple-orange jello salad
directions: Drain pineapple; add water to make 3/4 cup and heat to boiling.
Add to jello.
Add pineapple and Mandarin oranges. Chill until jelly-like.
Add orange juice to Dream Whip and beat until thick.
Fold into jello and fruit.
Fold in nuts and marshmallows.
If desired, garnish with Mandarin orange segments, maraschino cherries and mint sprigs.
Can also be molded.

title: double apple salad
directions: Boil 1 cup of juice and mix with jello and salt.
Chill.
When partially set, add apples, celery and nuts.
Mix well and firmly set.

title: cappuccino parfaits
directions: Dissolve coffee in hot water in medium bowl.
Add milk, pudding mix and cinnamon.
Beat with wire whisk 1 to 2 minutes. Let stand 5 minutes.
Fold in whipped topping.
Spoon 1/2 the pudding mixture into 5 dessert dishes.
Sprinkle with crushed cookies.
Spoon remaining pudding mixture over crushed cookies. Garnish each serving with additional 1 tablespoon whipped topping. Chill until ready to serve.

title: artichoke dip
directions: Mix all ingredients and put in a casserole.
Top with bread crumbs, paprika and Parmesan cheese.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes. Serve with chips, crackers or Tostitos.
Makes a lot.
